00:11:25.767 --> 00:11:27.133
MATT: Yes, you would
actually, so yeah.

00:11:27.167 --> 00:11:29.567
So you take some
of the-- the mostly

00:11:29.601 --> 00:11:32.100
or completely emptied healing
potion vials and collect--

00:11:32.133 --> 00:11:33.834
LAURA: I lick,
I lick the bottle

00:11:33.834 --> 00:11:37.501
for all the
remaining healing.

00:11:37.534 --> 00:11:38.901
-MATT: Little straw.
-LAURA: Like a Capri-Sun.

00:11:38.934 --> 00:11:40.601
MATT: Yeah, exactly.

00:11:40.634 --> 00:11:43.067
Okay.

00:11:43.100 --> 00:11:46.801
MARISHA: I head back
into the chamber

00:11:46.834 --> 00:11:49.000
and see if I can
find any of, like,

00:11:49.033 --> 00:11:52.668
Raishan's scales or,
like, Raishan blood or...

00:11:52.668 --> 00:11:54.234
LAURA: Maybe give it a moment

00:11:54.267 --> 00:11:56.801
just to let the lair actions
die down a little bit.

00:11:56.834 --> 00:11:58.167
LIAM: What?

00:11:58.200 --> 00:12:00.868
LAURA: The-- you know, all the lava
stuff happening in there.

00:12:00.901 --> 00:12:03.334
MARISHA: I'll watch from a distance
and make sure that, you know,

00:12:03.367 --> 00:12:04.434
it's not boiling over.

00:12:04.467 --> 00:12:06.000
-LAURA: It's safe?
-MARISHA: Yeah.

00:12:06.033 --> 00:12:07.901
LIAM: I'm gonna limp up to you.

00:12:07.934 --> 00:12:09.734
You're burnt all over.

00:12:09.767 --> 00:12:11.234
-MARISHA: Yeah.
-LIAM: Hold still for a second.

00:12:11.267 --> 00:12:12.300
MARISHA: That really sucks.

00:12:12.334 --> 00:12:14.400
I want to assume
that was karma.

00:12:14.434 --> 00:12:15.801
-Yeah.
-LIAM: Alright.

00:12:15.834 --> 00:12:17.033
I do have--

00:12:17.067 --> 00:12:18.767
MARISHA: I feel really bad
for that duergar now.

00:12:18.801 --> 00:12:19.834
That sucks.

00:12:19.868 --> 00:12:21.167
That's a
rough way to go.

00:12:21.200 --> 00:12:22.868
(laughter)

00:12:22.901 --> 00:12:24.767
LIAM: I cover her mouth with
my hand for a second

00:12:24.801 --> 00:12:27.167
and use the last of
Lay on Hands and I--

00:12:27.200 --> 00:12:29.167
I checked with CritRoleStats,
I do have ten left.

00:12:29.200 --> 00:12:30.467
MATT: Okay.

00:12:30.501 --> 00:12:32.801
LIAM: So I'm gonna use
eight, eight of those

00:12:32.834 --> 00:12:34.901
to heal you up a bit.

00:12:34.934 --> 00:12:36.868
-MARISHA: Okay.
-LAURA: Eight whole points.

00:12:36.901 --> 00:12:38.734
-LIAM: I only got ten.
-LAURA: Romeo.

00:12:38.767 --> 00:12:40.701
What do you do
with those last two?

00:12:40.734 --> 00:12:42.200
TALIESIN: I just imagine
like light slapping

00:12:42.234 --> 00:12:43.901
in the face
just eight times.

00:12:43.934 --> 00:12:46.033
Pow, hit point, hit point.

00:12:46.067 --> 00:12:49.234
MARISHA: Lay on Hands,
Lay on Hands.

00:12:49.267 --> 00:12:53.667
LIAM: One, two, three,
four, five, six.

00:12:53.701 --> 00:12:57.133
MATT: The Oath of Annoyance Paladin.

00:12:57.167 --> 00:12:58.834
Coming soon in the
Tal'Dorei campaign book.

00:12:58.868 --> 00:13:00.234
LIAM: Thordak died like this.

00:13:00.267 --> 00:13:02.133
(laughter)

00:13:02.167 --> 00:13:06.300
MATT: Alright, so as
Vax heals you up

00:13:06.334 --> 00:13:09.234
with some of the remnants
of his divine power still--

00:13:09.267 --> 00:13:12.467
still in his body.

00:13:12.501 --> 00:13:15.701
Kima's kind of walking
up to Keyleth

00:13:15.734 --> 00:13:17.467
and Gilmore goes over
and starts helping you

00:13:17.501 --> 00:13:20.834
gather and
separate some of the--

00:13:20.868 --> 00:13:22.000
What little blood you can.

00:13:22.033 --> 00:13:23.501
A lot of its kind
of just dug into the--

00:13:23.534 --> 00:13:26.300
the rock and the dust
but there are a little bit

00:13:26.334 --> 00:13:27.901
that you can kind
of pull into it.

00:13:27.934 --> 00:13:29.834
It's not too
clustered and filled

00:13:29.868 --> 00:13:33.801
with the equivalent
of coffee grinds.

00:13:33.834 --> 00:13:35.634
What else are
you guys doing?

00:13:35.667 --> 00:13:38.667
TALIESIN: Once the lair is safe, I want to
get in and start examining it.

00:13:38.701 --> 00:13:39.934
-MARISHA: Same.
-LAURA: Yeah.

00:13:39.968 --> 00:13:41.801
MATT: Okay.

00:13:41.834 --> 00:13:45.534
It takes, I'd say,
probably a good two minutes

00:13:45.567 --> 00:13:49.868
or so before the--

00:13:49.901 --> 00:13:53.801
the general tremors of
the lair begin to subside.

00:13:53.834 --> 00:13:58.200
The presence of Thordak
being long enough removed

00:13:58.234 --> 00:14:01.300
that the volcanic
activity begins

00:14:01.334 --> 00:14:03.734
to come to a
small, gentle end.

00:14:03.767 --> 00:14:05.834
LAURA: Actually, before
we go back in,

00:14:05.868 --> 00:14:08.801
can I peek up on
the surface level

00:14:08.834 --> 00:14:10.601
and see if it looks like
the fighting has died down?

00:14:10.634 --> 00:14:12.234
LIAM: I was just about
to say the same.

00:14:12.267 --> 00:14:13.334
MATT: Uh, okay, you
guys go up there?

00:14:13.367 --> 00:14:14.367
-LAURA: Yeah.
-LIAM: Yeah.

00:14:14.400 --> 00:14:15.801
MATT: Okay.

00:14:15.834 --> 00:14:17.124
Everyone else staying down?

00:14:17.124 --> 00:14:18.334
-TRAVIS: Yep.
-(Same) Yeah.

00:14:18.367 --> 00:14:19.701
MATT: Okay, while you
guys are waiting,

00:14:19.734 --> 00:14:21.801
the two of you
rush up to the surface.

00:14:21.834 --> 00:14:24.634
The outside of the opening
to Thordak's lair.

00:14:24.667 --> 00:14:26.621
Both of you guys
make perception checks.

00:14:26.621 --> 00:14:27.655
TRAVIS: Don't die.

00:14:32.968 --> 00:14:34.934
-LAURA: Twenty-seven.
-LIAM: Twenty-nine.

00:14:34.968 --> 00:14:36.300
MATT: Okay.

00:14:36.334 --> 00:14:40.067
As you both
peek through the--

00:14:40.100 --> 00:14:42.000
the heated clouds
of soot and ash

00:14:42.033 --> 00:14:43.868
that are billowing
out from inside,

00:14:43.901 --> 00:14:46.868
your vision clarifies and
you can see up into the sky

00:14:46.901 --> 00:14:48.834
the thunderstorm that
has been encompassing

00:14:48.868 --> 00:14:50.033
the vicinity of Emon.

00:14:50.067 --> 00:14:51.667
It's still rolling
and firing off

00:14:51.701 --> 00:14:53.284
bolts of lightning
and thunder.

00:14:53.284 --> 00:14:54.901
(imitates thunder clap)

00:14:54.934 --> 00:14:56.767
In the distance.

00:14:56.801 --> 00:14:58.367
It is beginning
to slowly subside

00:14:58.400 --> 00:14:59.868
to the size that it began,

00:14:59.901 --> 00:15:02.334
but you also notice
that the wyvern riders

00:15:02.367 --> 00:15:06.234
that once rapidly
swung through the air

00:15:06.267 --> 00:15:07.734
are all retreating en masse.

00:15:07.767 --> 00:15:10.634
The few that still remain
into the southwest end of,

00:15:10.667 --> 00:15:13.577
now maybe, about a
half mile off Emon,

00:15:13.577 --> 00:15:15.200
and a number of
them are fleeing

00:15:15.234 --> 00:15:16.794
and catching up with them.

00:15:16.794 --> 00:15:19.934
It looks like they're
being fended off

00:15:19.968 --> 00:15:21.801
and the tides, at least,
have turned somewhat

00:15:21.834 --> 00:15:25.734
from where they
began here in Emon.

00:15:25.767 --> 00:15:27.968
You also do
notice that the--

00:15:28.000 --> 00:15:29.701
the two doors that you
guys originally entered,

00:15:29.734 --> 00:15:31.868
that you pushed through?

00:15:31.901 --> 00:15:33.868
One of the doors is now
pushed off of its hinges

00:15:33.901 --> 00:15:35.067
and has fallen
to the ground.

00:15:35.100 --> 00:15:36.701
The other is kind
of partway off that--

00:15:36.734 --> 00:15:39.767
that giant gate doorway,
and just beyond it,

00:15:39.801 --> 00:15:43.634
you see what looks
to be battle still ensuing.

00:15:43.667 --> 00:15:48.634
You hear the muffled screams
echoing from outside that gate

00:15:48.667 --> 00:15:51.300
and streets beyond in Emon
of hundreds of soldiers

00:15:51.334 --> 00:15:52.834
shouting into battle.

00:15:52.868 --> 00:15:57.801
Large heaving war cries
of deep voiced giant-kin.

00:15:57.834 --> 00:15:59.767
You see bursts of
flame in the distance

00:15:59.801 --> 00:16:00.868
and what looks
to be bodies

00:16:00.901 --> 00:16:02.200
occasionally flung
through the air

00:16:02.234 --> 00:16:07.033
to disappear past the
horizon beyond the gate top.

00:16:07.067 --> 00:16:10.067
This-- there is still
warfare raging in this city.

00:16:10.100 --> 00:16:14.334
LIAM: Can we see through that gate to
where we parted with Kashaw?

00:16:14.367 --> 00:16:16.601
MATT: From this distance, you
cannot get that much more.

00:16:16.634 --> 00:16:17.834
You can just
see the motion of--

00:16:17.868 --> 00:16:19.133
You have to get closer.

00:16:19.167 --> 00:16:21.133
LAURA: So, we can't-- can
I reach into my shirt

00:16:21.167 --> 00:16:23.701
and grab out that note
that was on the arrow?

00:16:23.734 --> 00:16:25.334
I never read it.

00:16:25.367 --> 00:16:27.200
-MATT: Oh, yeah.
-LAURA: What is it?

00:16:27.234 --> 00:16:30.067
MATT: It says, My gift to you,
darling, use it well.

00:16:30.100 --> 00:16:32.601
LAURA: Oh, I knew it!

00:16:32.634 --> 00:16:35.534
We have to find them.

00:16:35.567 --> 00:16:37.090
LIAM: Let's go look.

00:16:40.234 --> 00:16:43.167
-Just a look.
-LAURA: Just stealth.

00:16:43.200 --> 00:16:46.534
To see if it looks
like the giant is gone,

00:16:46.567 --> 00:16:48.267
and if Zahra and
Kash are around.

00:16:48.300 --> 00:16:49.934
LIAM: Why don't we just cover
like half the distance?

00:16:49.968 --> 00:16:51.167
-See what we can see from there.
-LAURA: Yeah, yeah, yeah.

00:16:51.200 --> 00:16:52.267
MATT: Okay, stealth
check both you guys.

00:16:52.300 --> 00:16:55.834
♪

00:16:55.868 --> 00:16:57.000
LIAM: Twenty-eight.

00:16:57.033 --> 00:17:00.400
♪

00:17:00.434 --> 00:17:03.534
LAURA: Twelve.

00:17:03.567 --> 00:17:04.834
-MATT: Wow.
-LAURA: I know.

00:17:04.867 --> 00:17:07.165
MATT: Okay.

00:17:07.200 --> 00:17:10.400
LAURA: I'm-- you know, I've--
I'm injured grievously.

00:17:10.434 --> 00:17:12.501
MATT: You are.

00:17:12.534 --> 00:17:14.834
You snatched from the
jaws of death temporarily,

00:17:14.867 --> 00:17:17.934
you find yourself
physically affected

00:17:17.968 --> 00:17:19.334
more than you
would have expected

00:17:19.367 --> 00:17:21.334
and what seemed to you as
just an instant of darkness,

00:17:21.367 --> 00:17:23.434
and as you begin to try and
follow after your brother,

00:17:23.467 --> 00:17:25.968
you find yourself stumbling
and falling to one knee

00:17:26.000 --> 00:17:27.133
and trying
best to keep up.

00:17:27.165 --> 00:17:28.267
LAURA: Oh, shit.

00:17:28.300 --> 00:17:30.367
MATT: At this time, you
notice two figures

00:17:30.400 --> 00:17:34.000
running from the opening in
that gate in your direction.

00:17:34.033 --> 00:17:37.267
You see it first, but you
see it for a moment after him.

00:17:37.300 --> 00:17:39.834
You see bloodied, bruised,
but still in a full sprint

00:17:39.868 --> 00:17:43.434
both Kashaw and Zahra
rushing in your direction

00:17:43.467 --> 00:17:47.567
and you hear Kash
just yelling out,

00:17:47.601 --> 00:17:49.567
"Vox Machina!

00:17:49.601 --> 00:17:51.067
You're alive, right?"

00:17:51.100 --> 00:17:52.968
LAURA: Keep it down, you fuck!

00:17:53.000 --> 00:17:56.267
Come on, come on
into this hole.

00:17:56.300 --> 00:17:58.934
MATT: "Hole?"
"Yes, the hole, darling."

00:17:58.968 --> 00:17:59.934
"Right."

00:17:59.968 --> 00:18:01.200
And they both rush up

00:18:01.234 --> 00:18:05.100
and as you guys are
catching up with them,

00:18:05.133 --> 00:18:08.667
you notice, by the gate,
pushing through

00:18:08.701 --> 00:18:11.434
what looks to be
another fire giant

00:18:11.467 --> 00:18:13.300
wielding a sword
kind of dragged behind,

00:18:13.334 --> 00:18:16.167
kind of pour through.

00:18:16.200 --> 00:18:18.033
(yells)

00:18:18.067 --> 00:18:20.200
And just begins
going into a--

00:18:20.234 --> 00:18:21.868
a large bounding
sprint in your direction.

00:18:21.901 --> 00:18:23.734
-LAURA: Oh, God.
-LIAM: Running.

00:18:23.767 --> 00:18:25.400
LAURA: Giants, giants at the door.

00:18:25.434 --> 00:18:26.834
-Giants!
-TALIESIN: I am moving towards it.

00:18:26.868 --> 00:18:28.300
TRAVIS: Yeah, now we're all going
on up towards the hole.

00:18:28.334 --> 00:18:30.934
-MATT: Okay.
-LAURA: Can I shoot an arrow at him?

00:18:30.968 --> 00:18:33.968
MATT: As you're saying "giants"
into your ear,

00:18:34.000 --> 00:18:37.968
you watch as two
crossbow bolts kinda...

00:18:39.367 --> 00:18:41.534
into the back of the head
of the giant and giant goes...

00:18:41.567 --> 00:18:43.667
and stops and looks
over the shoulder

00:18:43.701 --> 00:18:47.467
and you see a flash
of light behind him.

00:18:47.501 --> 00:18:51.267
An impact into the back of the
black ironed giant's armor.

00:18:51.300 --> 00:18:54.367
Like a sudden impact of a fiery
meteor just slams into it.

00:18:54.400 --> 00:18:55.400
(yells)

00:18:55.434 --> 00:18:56.567
And the giant
stumbles to one knee

00:18:56.601 --> 00:18:58.300
before another blow
hits him right across

00:18:58.334 --> 00:18:59.667
the back of the head
and the fire giant

00:18:59.701 --> 00:19:03.400
just falls on face first
unconscious onto the ground.

00:19:03.434 --> 00:19:07.534
Little cloud of dust and dirt
kind of billows up to the sides.

00:19:07.567 --> 00:19:10.000
There you see, by
the front of the gate,

00:19:10.033 --> 00:19:13.701
you see Jarret with crossbow
right there and standing,

00:19:13.734 --> 00:19:16.300
and now stepping up onto the
back of the giant's armor

00:19:16.334 --> 00:19:20.234
and slamming a flashing
bright radiant war hammer

00:19:20.267 --> 00:19:21.968
into the back of its neck.

00:19:22.000 --> 00:19:24.834
You see,
in chain mail,

00:19:24.868 --> 00:19:28.133
long beard,
white streaked,

00:19:28.167 --> 00:19:29.734
billowing war torn
hair pulled into

00:19:29.767 --> 00:19:33.067
a tight ponytail
towards the back,

00:19:33.100 --> 00:19:34.167
a familiar face.

00:19:34.200 --> 00:19:36.968
You see Kerrek,
currently of white--

00:19:37.000 --> 00:19:41.300
of Westruun standing,
wipes his brow

00:19:41.334 --> 00:19:43.400
and looks up and takes notice
of your presence immediately.

00:19:43.434 --> 00:19:45.167
Patrick, if you want
to come on the stage.

00:19:45.200 --> 00:19:46.334
LAURA: What the fuck?

00:19:46.367 --> 00:19:49.400
(applause, cheers)

00:19:49.434 --> 00:19:52.334
SAM: Geez, Louise!
Patrick Rothfuss.

00:19:52.367 --> 00:19:57.334
LAURA: Scooch on by since it's
so easy to make your way.

00:19:57.367 --> 00:19:58.467
(laughing)

00:19:58.501 --> 00:20:01.267
MATT: Our set is so conducive
to movement.

00:20:01.300 --> 00:20:03.701
TRAVIS: Oh!

00:20:03.734 --> 00:20:04.767
I didn't break it.

00:20:04.801 --> 00:20:07.767
-LAURA: The whole set falls down.
-MATT: I know!

00:20:07.801 --> 00:20:09.267
LAURA: Kerrek, you can fight!

00:20:09.300 --> 00:20:10.467
PATRICK: I get to sit
next to my besty.

00:20:10.501 --> 00:20:12.000
MARISHA: Yeah!

00:20:12.033 --> 00:20:13.761
My new besty.

00:20:16.534 --> 00:20:18.267
-LIAM: What in the fuck?
-LAURA: I thought you were--

00:20:18.300 --> 00:20:22.033
I thought--
you can fight?

00:20:22.067 --> 00:20:23.834
PATRICK: Uh.

00:20:23.868 --> 00:20:26.968
LAURA: Uh, yeah, you just brought
down a giant, no big deal.

00:20:27.000 --> 00:20:30.067
PATRICK: Uh, team effort.

00:20:30.100 --> 00:20:31.434
Like is everything cool now?

00:20:31.467 --> 00:20:33.000
Like is this
the last of them?

00:20:33.033 --> 00:20:34.467
MATT: For one, I think you might
want to move a little bit over

00:20:34.501 --> 00:20:35.567
to get into the camera.

00:20:35.601 --> 00:20:37.300
TRAVIS: Yes, come on over.

00:20:37.334 --> 00:20:38.434
MATT: Just a smidge
for the audience.

00:20:38.467 --> 00:20:40.434
-LAURA: Yeah.
-LIAM: Yeah, yeah.

00:20:40.467 --> 00:20:42.267
MATT: There you go,

00:20:42.300 --> 00:20:44.501
and as you've been in this
fray for quite some time

00:20:44.534 --> 00:20:47.467
and the exhaustion's starting
to mount on you a bit,

00:20:47.501 --> 00:20:49.434
and the--

00:20:49.467 --> 00:20:50.968
the two individuals
that you and your--

00:20:51.000 --> 00:20:53.167
your allies have come upon,
being the smaller unit,

00:20:53.200 --> 00:20:55.303
you manage to penetrate
further into the city

00:20:55.303 --> 00:20:59.200
then the main armies that were
pushing towards the gates.

00:20:59.234 --> 00:21:02.801
You saw the
golden-armored human

00:21:02.834 --> 00:21:05.534
and the Tiefling
currently struggling with,

00:21:05.567 --> 00:21:07.868
what looked to be,
five fire giants.

00:21:07.901 --> 00:21:11.734
Three that had come up behind
the two that they had ensnared,

00:21:11.767 --> 00:21:14.367
and after minutes of battle

00:21:14.400 --> 00:21:15.601
and tearing through them

00:21:15.634 --> 00:21:16.968
it looks like you
finally gain the upper hand.

00:21:17.000 --> 00:21:18.534
You've lost a number
of allies through this--

00:21:18.567 --> 00:21:20.100
this incursion, however,

00:21:20.133 --> 00:21:22.767
these are the really, really
familiar welcome faces

00:21:22.801 --> 00:21:26.067
given the perpetual
onslaught that you've seen

00:21:26.100 --> 00:21:29.450
since you first
arrived in Emon.

00:21:31.033 --> 00:21:34.601
PATRICK: He--he probably just says,

00:21:34.634 --> 00:21:36.300
"Is it done?"

00:21:36.334 --> 00:21:37.467
LAURA: Is it?

00:21:37.501 --> 00:21:39.067
PATRICK: That's his--
that's his opener.

00:21:39.100 --> 00:21:42.067
LAURA: I mean, eh.

00:21:42.100 --> 00:21:43.100
LIAM: Ish.

00:21:43.133 --> 00:21:45.801
LAURA: Thordak was killed.

00:21:45.834 --> 00:21:49.300
MATT: Kashaw pipes up and says,
"So you killed the thing?

00:21:49.334 --> 00:21:50.868
You killed it,
it's dead, right?"

00:21:50.901 --> 00:21:51.968
LAURA: Mm-hmm.

00:21:52.000 --> 00:21:52.968
MATT: "Please tell me
you killed the thing."

00:21:53.000 --> 00:21:53.968
LAURA: Yes, the thing is dead.

00:21:54.000 --> 00:21:55.540
-LIAM: We killed thing.
-LAURA: And gone.

00:21:55.540 --> 00:21:57.067
Literally, gone.

00:21:57.100 --> 00:21:58.801
-MATT: "Great."
-LAURA: Stolen.

00:21:58.834 --> 00:22:01.200
MATT: "Fantastic, that's--
that's wonderful, great."

00:22:01.234 --> 00:22:03.467
-"We can go home."
-PATRICK: Stolen?

00:22:03.501 --> 00:22:05.434
LAURA: Can I hug Zahra?

00:22:05.467 --> 00:22:07.701
MATT: Yeah, she-- she
eagerly puts her arms out

00:22:07.734 --> 00:22:10.334
and as you guys kind
of embrace real fast,

00:22:10.367 --> 00:22:13.467
she kind of-- both of you
almost, from the impact,

00:22:13.501 --> 00:22:15.434
stop, the bruising sets in.

00:22:15.467 --> 00:22:17.467
-MATT: "Darling, careful."
-LAURA: Yeah, yeah, I know, darling.

00:22:17.501 --> 00:22:18.968
Injured.

00:22:19.000 --> 00:22:21.667
PATRICK: How-- how do
these guys look?

00:22:21.701 --> 00:22:24.434
MATT: You don't see them yet,
you just see these two.

00:22:24.467 --> 00:22:25.968
And after a moment
of these hugs happen,

00:22:26.000 --> 00:22:27.567
you kind of
catch your breath.

00:22:27.601 --> 00:22:29.434
You notice a few
more figures appear

00:22:29.467 --> 00:22:31.467
from out of this large
craterous hole in the ground

00:22:31.501 --> 00:22:33.300
in the center of
this ruined district,

00:22:33.334 --> 00:22:35.868
and from there you watch
as the familiar Percival,

00:22:35.901 --> 00:22:38.434
Scanlan, oh no,
you stay behind?

00:22:38.467 --> 00:22:43.033
Grog and Keyleth all
emerge from the hole.

00:22:45.601 --> 00:22:47.133
PATRICK: How's she look?

00:22:47.167 --> 00:22:48.601
SAM: Whoo!

00:22:48.634 --> 00:22:51.067
MATT: A little-- a little
singed, a little burned.

00:22:51.100 --> 00:22:53.854
A little worse
for wear, but alive.

00:22:53.854 --> 00:22:55.344
Can't say that
much different

00:22:55.344 --> 00:22:57.100
from the rest of
her allies as well.

00:22:57.133 --> 00:22:58.634
PATRICK: Okay.

00:23:03.367 --> 00:23:07.167
I might actually kind of lumber
a little bit in that direction

00:23:07.200 --> 00:23:11.601
as if I were going in for a hug,
and then stop when I remember

00:23:11.634 --> 00:23:13.400
that maybe I'm not
that sort of person.

00:23:13.434 --> 00:23:15.367
(laughter)

00:23:15.400 --> 00:23:17.467
It looks-- it looks
actually very awkward.

00:23:17.501 --> 00:23:20.701
(laughter)

00:23:20.734 --> 00:23:21.934
TALIESIN: Oh, good.

00:23:21.968 --> 00:23:23.734
This is-- this is a face
I would like to see.

00:23:23.767 --> 00:23:26.667
MARISHA: Kerr?

00:23:26.701 --> 00:23:29.467
LAURA: He just killed
a giant with his

00:23:29.501 --> 00:23:32.467
giant hammer of
blazing white--

00:23:32.501 --> 00:23:34.934
MARISHA: Keyleth just
closes the distance

00:23:34.968 --> 00:23:38.000
and runs up and
just hugs Kerr.

00:23:38.033 --> 00:23:41.400
PATRICK: Big bear hug,
big bear hug.

00:23:41.434 --> 00:23:44.244
MARISHA: What are you doing here?

00:23:45.267 --> 00:23:47.300
PATRICK: Same as everyone.

00:23:47.334 --> 00:23:52.167
Been doing-- doing as
much as a person can do.

00:23:54.000 --> 00:23:56.167
MARISHA: I got your gift.

00:23:56.200 --> 00:23:59.767
PATRICK: I'm so glad of that.

00:23:59.801 --> 00:24:02.601
-MARISHA: It meant everything.
-PATRICK: Oh.

00:24:02.634 --> 00:24:05.901
MARISHA: Maybe even a little
too literally, like--

00:24:05.934 --> 00:24:08.968
like 20 minutes ago.

00:24:09.000 --> 00:24:12.133
A lot of passing through
fire here lately.

00:24:12.167 --> 00:24:14.434
PATRICK: Yeah.

00:24:14.467 --> 00:24:16.634
TALIESIN: To break the
awkward briefly, dear.

00:24:16.667 --> 00:24:18.667
TRAVIS: Yeah, much
war still happening.

00:24:18.701 --> 00:24:20.968
-LAURA: Maybe we should go down.
-TALIESIN: Wait!

00:24:21.000 --> 00:24:24.567
MARISHA: I sky write up in the air,
is there like a--

00:24:24.601 --> 00:24:27.100
like a sigil of Emon?

00:24:27.133 --> 00:24:28.400
Like a--

00:24:28.434 --> 00:24:31.200
MATT: I mean, there is a
crest for the city.

00:24:31.234 --> 00:24:33.334
You can do a simplified
version of it, if you like.

00:24:33.367 --> 00:24:36.267
MARISHA: I do that into the
sky with Sky Write.

00:24:36.300 --> 00:24:38.367
MATT: Okay, so the storm,
which is still raging,

00:24:38.400 --> 00:24:41.100
but it's moving itself
southwest to almost follow the--

00:24:41.133 --> 00:24:44.033
the wyvern riders that have
survived this battle so far

00:24:44.067 --> 00:24:46.467
and are fleeing
from the scene.

00:24:46.501 --> 00:24:49.267
The clouds then begin
to shift and shape

00:24:49.300 --> 00:24:51.200
and the darkness separates
into what looks like

00:24:51.234 --> 00:24:52.601
little plumes of white

00:24:52.634 --> 00:24:56.334
that spell out a very basic
rendition of the symbol of Emon.

00:24:56.367 --> 00:24:59.267
♪

00:24:59.300 --> 00:25:01.133
What else you wanna do?

00:25:01.167 --> 00:25:02.234
TRAVIS: Is Kash there?

00:25:02.267 --> 00:25:03.887
MATT: Kash is there
with you guys.

00:25:03.887 --> 00:25:05.901
-TRAVIS: How's he look?
-TALIESIN: Yeah.

00:25:05.934 --> 00:25:08.100
MATT: He looks pretty messed up.

00:25:08.133 --> 00:25:10.234
There are a few large
sections of armor

00:25:10.267 --> 00:25:12.200
that have been
just cloven through

00:25:12.234 --> 00:25:17.167
and you see a number
of flesh wounds sustained

00:25:17.200 --> 00:25:19.200
but nothing mortal, but he--

00:25:19.234 --> 00:25:21.501
He holds himself
with a kind of a

00:25:21.534 --> 00:25:23.467
knowing confidence
with his arms crossed,

00:25:23.501 --> 00:25:24.868
but as soon as any sort
of physical movement,

00:25:24.901 --> 00:25:26.467
there is a little
bit of a wheeze

00:25:26.501 --> 00:25:28.300
and a trying to cover
for the physical impact

00:25:28.334 --> 00:25:29.934
of the battle
he's just sustained.

00:25:29.968 --> 00:25:32.841
TRAVIS: You look a little
worse for the wear there.

00:25:33.504 --> 00:25:35.434
MATT: "I don't know what
you mean, I'm sorry."

00:25:35.467 --> 00:25:38.701
TRAVIS: Oh, I'm sorry.
Z, did he go unconscious?

00:25:38.734 --> 00:25:40.767
MATT: "Actually, no, he
fought quite bravely."

00:25:40.801 --> 00:25:42.634
-TRAVIS: Are you lying?
-MATT: "No."

00:25:42.667 --> 00:25:44.467
-TRAVIS: Shit.
-MARISHA: She's lying.

00:25:44.501 --> 00:25:47.968
TRAVIS: Good job,
I guess, Kash.

00:25:48.000 --> 00:25:50.534
MATT: He goes, "You didn't
too bad yourself, big man."

00:25:50.567 --> 00:25:51.667
Smacks you on the
shoulder and goes...

00:25:51.701 --> 00:25:53.434
(whimpering)

00:25:53.467 --> 00:25:54.701
TRAVIS: No, that would
never hurt me.

00:25:54.734 --> 00:25:56.834
LIAM: I'm gonna walk up
to him as well,

00:25:56.868 --> 00:25:58.901
cause he looks
fucked up and say,

00:25:58.934 --> 00:26:00.467
"Hey, thank you for
the assist, Spanky."

00:26:00.501 --> 00:26:02.534
And I'm gonna give
him two slaps of the cheek

00:26:02.567 --> 00:26:04.267
and leave a couple of
black feathers stuck there

00:26:04.300 --> 00:26:07.300
with sweat and use the last
of my Lay on Hands on him.

00:26:07.334 --> 00:26:10.067
TALIESIN: Now that-- now that we've
sent the word, maybe now--

00:26:10.100 --> 00:26:11.634
(indistinct talking)

00:26:11.667 --> 00:26:13.467
The conversation's
underground.

00:26:13.501 --> 00:26:14.767
MARISHA: Okay.

00:26:14.801 --> 00:26:16.868
LIAM: Everything hurts.

00:26:16.901 --> 00:26:19.767
MATT: What's your
armor class?

00:26:19.801 --> 00:26:21.801
LIAM: Twenty-one.

00:26:21.834 --> 00:26:24.934
MATT: He knees you gently
enough in the nuts

00:26:24.968 --> 00:26:26.467
to get you to
drop to one knee.

00:26:26.501 --> 00:26:27.801
TRAVIS: "Gently enough."

00:26:27.834 --> 00:26:29.033
MATT: "That's two."

00:26:29.067 --> 00:26:31.534
(laughter)

00:26:31.567 --> 00:26:32.567
TRAVIS: Yes, good
throwback!

00:26:32.601 --> 00:26:35.501
LIAM: I laugh through it.

00:26:35.534 --> 00:26:36.534
TRAVIS: Good callback.

00:26:36.567 --> 00:26:37.534
TALIESIN: Are there-- are
there any soldiers

00:26:37.567 --> 00:26:38.534
running around
by the way?

00:26:38.567 --> 00:26:39.834
Right now, any
of our people?

00:26:39.868 --> 00:26:41.334
MATT: Right now, some soldiers
are beginning to pour in

00:26:41.367 --> 00:26:43.300
through the gate
that they emerged from.

00:26:43.334 --> 00:26:45.314
Some of your allies,
some from other armies

00:26:45.314 --> 00:26:46.868
that are starting
to find their way

00:26:46.901 --> 00:26:48.750
towards the center
core of the city.

00:26:48.750 --> 00:26:51.601
Not everyone's been
made aware that the--

00:26:51.634 --> 00:26:53.601
the center of this battle

00:26:53.634 --> 00:26:57.367
has already been
won, essentially.

00:26:57.400 --> 00:26:58.400
TRAVIS: Damn it.

00:26:58.434 --> 00:27:00.300
MATT: So, people are
starting to come in

00:27:00.334 --> 00:27:01.501
and calm down a bit
and then rush back out

00:27:01.534 --> 00:27:02.868
to see what else is there.

00:27:02.901 --> 00:27:04.734
You watch as a few wyvern riders
try and scoot through the sky

00:27:04.767 --> 00:27:06.961
to catch up with the rest of
them as a bolt of lightning...

00:27:06.961 --> 00:27:08.467
Slams into one
and you see it...

00:27:08.501 --> 00:27:09.501
(yells)

00:27:09.534 --> 00:27:11.534
Streak and tumble
and then crash somewhere

00:27:11.567 --> 00:27:14.191
on the outside
of the district.

00:27:14.191 --> 00:27:16.167
TALIESIN: I'm gonna fire a couple
of times into the air

00:27:16.200 --> 00:27:17.834
just to get some
attention and just,

00:27:17.868 --> 00:27:20.601
"Spread the word,
Thordak has fallen!

00:27:20.634 --> 00:27:21.901
Spread the word!"

00:27:21.934 --> 00:27:23.381
Now, we can go down.

00:27:23.381 --> 00:27:25.234
MATT: You see some of the
soldiers immediately

00:27:25.267 --> 00:27:26.767
kind of look at each other
and you can hear the--

00:27:26.801 --> 00:27:28.534
sound of the shouting and
whispering back and forth.

00:27:28.567 --> 00:27:32.300
Voices are shouting, "Thordak
has fallen! Thordak has fallen!

00:27:32.334 --> 00:27:33.968
Thordak has fallen!"

00:27:34.000 --> 00:27:36.834
It starts just carrying
throughout the city and echoing.

00:27:36.868 --> 00:27:39.267
MARISHA: Call the locksmith!

00:27:39.300 --> 00:27:40.501
MATT: Everyone goes, "What?"

00:27:40.534 --> 00:27:42.267
"Sorry, Thordak has fallen!"

00:27:42.267 --> 00:27:44.137
(laughter)

00:27:46.334 --> 00:27:48.960
So, as you--
you follow them

00:27:48.960 --> 00:27:50.901
and gather into the
area, or you want to--

00:27:50.934 --> 00:27:54.200
PATRICK: I'd say, just as--
and I have to go talk.

00:27:54.234 --> 00:27:56.968
I'm like,
"Samantha, it's you.

00:27:57.000 --> 00:27:58.367
Circle everyone up.

00:27:58.400 --> 00:28:00.400
Make sure the people
are taken care of."

00:28:00.434 --> 00:28:02.334
MATT: "Yes."

00:28:02.367 --> 00:28:05.300
PATRICK: And it's just
like, 30--

00:28:05.334 --> 00:28:07.501
SAM: Another campaign going on.

00:28:07.534 --> 00:28:10.901
lots of campaigns have
just briefly touched.

00:28:10.934 --> 00:28:13.901
PATRICK: It's a couple--
a couple dozen

00:28:13.934 --> 00:28:17.267
moderately well armored,

00:28:17.300 --> 00:28:20.400
but you know, like...

00:28:20.434 --> 00:28:22.367
These-- these are not
maybe crack troops.

00:28:22.400 --> 00:28:24.567
They have a
lot of heart.

00:28:24.601 --> 00:28:27.200
LIAM: Do they have
any hit points?

00:28:27.234 --> 00:28:30.968
PATRICK: More than you
might expect.

00:28:31.000 --> 00:28:33.067
Yeah, and so I just,
I square them away.

00:28:33.100 --> 00:28:34.868
They can take care
of themselves by now,

00:28:34.901 --> 00:28:36.667
at least for a bit.

00:28:36.701 --> 00:28:38.300
MATT: Yeah, they set
up a small perimeter

00:28:38.334 --> 00:28:40.367
to the entrance ways
to the district

00:28:40.400 --> 00:28:43.868
and are awaiting
other forces to arrive

00:28:43.901 --> 00:28:45.267
and inform them
of what's going on

00:28:45.300 --> 00:28:47.534
and still stay alert for any
stragglers of the battle.

00:28:47.567 --> 00:28:49.491
LIAM: What a world,
what a world.

00:28:50.634 --> 00:28:52.701
MATT: As you--
What'd you do?

00:28:52.734 --> 00:28:56.267
MARISHA: I just-- I grab Kerr and I start
ushering him down into the hole.

00:28:56.300 --> 00:28:57.868
PATRICK: Okay.

00:28:57.901 --> 00:29:00.434
MARISHA: Into the hole!

00:29:00.467 --> 00:29:01.734
MATT: Laura.

00:29:01.767 --> 00:29:03.167
LAURA: I'm so sorry!

00:29:03.200 --> 00:29:06.434
MATT: You are-- you're my
favorite 13 year old.

00:29:06.467 --> 00:29:08.734
PATRICK: It's-- it's
a lovely hole.

00:29:08.767 --> 00:29:11.067
(laughter)

00:29:11.100 --> 00:29:13.133
-LIAM: That's what they tell me.
-MATT: There's room for everyone.

00:29:13.167 --> 00:29:16.434
PATRICK: It's been a long
time for me, you know.

00:29:16.467 --> 00:29:17.901
I haven't done
this recently.

00:29:17.934 --> 00:29:20.367
LIAM: I'm in here
all the time.

00:29:20.400 --> 00:29:22.234
All the time.

00:29:22.267 --> 00:29:25.267
MATT: While this is
happening, Scanlan,

00:29:25.300 --> 00:29:28.367
you stayed down there
with Kima and Gilmore.

00:29:28.400 --> 00:29:31.767
SAM: Yeah, I sort of moseyed my
way back to the beginning--

00:29:31.801 --> 00:29:33.601
to the opening
of the lair,

00:29:33.634 --> 00:29:35.400
like, where I had
tossed the flute.

00:29:35.434 --> 00:29:36.434
MATT: Yeah.

00:29:36.467 --> 00:29:37.868
LIAM: And I pick it up,

00:29:37.901 --> 00:29:40.634
and I carefully divide

00:29:40.667 --> 00:29:44.000
my sachet of Suude
into three parts.

00:29:44.033 --> 00:29:47.834
Three thirds.

00:29:47.868 --> 00:29:51.100
And I'm going to
snort one third of it.

00:29:51.133 --> 00:29:53.100
MATT: Okay.

00:29:53.133 --> 00:29:55.834
The large brass dragon
that has currently

00:29:55.868 --> 00:29:58.434
-been heading at the end--
-SAM: He can watch.

00:29:58.467 --> 00:30:00.777
They can watch, they
can watch, they can watch.

00:30:00.777 --> 00:30:04.467
MATT: At the end of the
tunnel, Devo'ssa,

00:30:04.501 --> 00:30:08.164
they've slowly brought down
to their hands and knees

00:30:08.164 --> 00:30:10.033
after travelling through
and scoping out

00:30:10.067 --> 00:30:13.534
the interior
of the lair.

00:30:13.567 --> 00:30:16.234
Approaches you as you're pulling
out your stash and you know,

00:30:16.267 --> 00:30:19.100
Gilmore and Kima
approaching as well.

00:30:19.133 --> 00:30:22.133
"What have you there?"

00:30:22.167 --> 00:30:24.801
SAM: I've had a...

00:30:24.834 --> 00:30:27.767
Not a great
day, Devo'ssa.

00:30:29.968 --> 00:30:31.934
Thank you for coming.

00:30:31.968 --> 00:30:34.334
For answering our call.

00:30:34.367 --> 00:30:37.801
I just need a second to
myself if you don't mind.

00:30:39.400 --> 00:30:41.567
LAURA: Isn't Pike
still down there?

00:30:41.601 --> 00:30:44.471
MATT: Technically, Pike would
still be down there with him.

00:30:45.834 --> 00:30:48.868
SAM: Maybe just
turn a wing?

00:30:48.901 --> 00:30:51.334
(laughter)

00:30:56.334 --> 00:30:57.701
MATT: They give a
curious glance

00:30:57.734 --> 00:31:00.458
as Gilmore
kind of walks up

00:31:00.458 --> 00:31:01.954
and brushes
his hair back,

00:31:01.954 --> 00:31:03.767
which it catches
your eye interestingly.

00:31:03.801 --> 00:31:05.804
There is like a glowing
rune of some kind

00:31:05.804 --> 00:31:07.701
in the center of
Gilmore's forehead.

00:31:07.734 --> 00:31:10.434
He kind of brushes the hair
out of the way and he goes,

00:31:10.467 --> 00:31:13.634
"If a man wants some privacy,
give him some privacy.

00:31:13.667 --> 00:31:15.434
I just want to ask
you a few questions.

00:31:15.467 --> 00:31:19.167
It's not very often
I get to talk to...

00:31:19.200 --> 00:31:20.601
J'Mon."

00:31:21.834 --> 00:31:26.801
And Gilmore walks up
as the dragon sits back up

00:31:26.834 --> 00:31:30.801
and puts out a claw and kind
of lifts Gilmore into his claw.

00:31:30.834 --> 00:31:33.200
They both begin having a
conversation back and forth,

00:31:33.234 --> 00:31:35.054
which, at this point
Pike is also curious

00:31:35.054 --> 00:31:36.400
and begins to
pay attention

00:31:36.434 --> 00:31:37.634
and sidles
up next to you

00:31:37.667 --> 00:31:39.234
as you begin
divvying out and goes--

00:31:39.267 --> 00:31:40.760
SAM: Are they talking
in their language,

00:31:40.760 --> 00:31:42.334
the Marquet
language or--

00:31:42.367 --> 00:31:43.930
MATT: If you want
to listen in--

00:31:43.930 --> 00:31:46.167
SAM: No, no, I'm just curious.

00:31:46.200 --> 00:31:48.834
MATT: Marquesian, and
yes, they are.

00:31:48.868 --> 00:31:51.534
-SAM: Exciting.
-TALIESIN: I don't speak that.

00:31:51.567 --> 00:31:54.901
MATT: As you begin
taking it out

00:31:54.934 --> 00:31:57.467
and you're getting ready to go
ahead and snort one portion.

00:31:57.501 --> 00:31:58.601
SAM: One third.

00:31:58.634 --> 00:32:01.047
MATT: One third of
your Suude.

00:32:01.701 --> 00:32:03.167
Pike approaches
from behind

00:32:03.200 --> 00:32:05.868
and claps her gauntlet
onto your shoulder and says,

00:32:05.901 --> 00:32:07.834
"Scanlan, you okay?"

00:32:07.868 --> 00:32:10.000
SAM: Oh, yeah, I just--

00:32:10.033 --> 00:32:14.601
This is some, some
healing herbs that I got.

00:32:14.634 --> 00:32:19.000
MATT: "Okay, well, if I--
I'm trained in--

00:32:19.033 --> 00:32:22.037
in medicinal applications
if you need my help."

00:32:23.701 --> 00:32:25.000
(laughter)

00:32:25.033 --> 00:32:26.234
SAM: I put it away.

00:32:26.267 --> 00:32:28.901
(laughter)

