in front with their
jaw resting on the edge

00:54:06.300 --> 00:54:07.901
and just kind of watching,

00:54:07.934 --> 00:54:10.767
and the-- the dragon's voice
kind of billows up forth.

00:54:10.801 --> 00:54:14.501
"Ah, the drama of
such short lives.

00:54:16.100 --> 00:54:18.234
It's heartwarming for us

00:54:18.267 --> 00:54:21.868
who don't get the chance
to see it often enough.

00:54:21.901 --> 00:54:25.167
It's lonely in the tower."

00:54:25.200 --> 00:54:28.200
LAURA: You know, you can come down
and join us whenever you like.

00:54:28.234 --> 00:54:30.167
MATT: "I appreciate
the offer,

00:54:30.200 --> 00:54:33.067
however, the longer
I'm away from my city,

00:54:33.100 --> 00:54:35.767
the more in danger
I leave it.

00:54:35.801 --> 00:54:39.067
I have many enemies,
as does Ank'Harel,

00:54:39.100 --> 00:54:41.834
and I can guarantee you
the moment that I absconded

00:54:41.868 --> 00:54:44.501
with your magic to aid you,

00:54:44.534 --> 00:54:46.934
that's the opening
they've been waiting for,

00:54:46.968 --> 00:54:51.200
so I have to return
to my city and my people,

00:54:51.234 --> 00:54:56.067
but I believe our
debt is collected.

00:54:56.100 --> 00:54:58.734
Your victory against
Thordak complete

00:54:58.767 --> 00:55:01.133
from where
I once left it.

00:55:01.167 --> 00:55:02.467
I wish you luck."

00:55:02.501 --> 00:55:06.067
SAM: Would you--
would you like--

00:55:06.100 --> 00:55:09.834
You lent me this symbol,
this necklace.

00:55:09.868 --> 00:55:11.367
Necklace? Symbol.

00:55:11.400 --> 00:55:14.634
Would you
like it back?

00:55:14.667 --> 00:55:17.734
MATT: The large brass dragon
face kind of shifts down

00:55:17.767 --> 00:55:20.067
right up to you and the
immensity to distance

00:55:20.100 --> 00:55:21.567
is already intimidating,

00:55:21.601 --> 00:55:24.234
but when the front
of the snarling jaws,

00:55:24.267 --> 00:55:26.133
the immensity of
the nostrils flare

00:55:26.167 --> 00:55:30.203
right at the presence of
a gnome sized individual...

00:55:30.203 --> 00:55:33.200
You've grown up fighting the
sensation of feeling small

00:55:33.234 --> 00:55:35.334
in comparison to
the world around you.

00:55:35.367 --> 00:55:37.868
You feel truly
small this close

00:55:37.901 --> 00:55:40.334
to the front of
the dragon's maw.

00:55:40.367 --> 00:55:42.367
The teeth curl into a grin

00:55:42.400 --> 00:55:45.501
and the voice
kinda billows out,

00:55:45.534 --> 00:55:48.567
like, a slow rolling
landslide into your face

00:55:48.601 --> 00:55:50.534
with the warmth
of its breath.

00:55:50.567 --> 00:55:54.310
"Nah, keep it."

00:55:56.534 --> 00:55:57.534
MARISHA: J'Mon!

00:55:57.567 --> 00:55:58.567
MATT: And just steps
over and starts

00:55:58.601 --> 00:56:02.033
making its way
up the hall--

00:56:02.067 --> 00:56:05.200
the cavern
towards the district.

00:56:05.234 --> 00:56:09.000
MARISHA: Before you leave?

00:56:09.033 --> 00:56:13.334
If you were fighting
a green dragon

00:56:13.367 --> 00:56:16.234
named the Diseased Deceiver,

00:56:16.267 --> 00:56:20.334
who wanted ultimate
power over her domain,

00:56:20.367 --> 00:56:22.067
where would you start?

00:56:25.667 --> 00:56:27.701
MATT: "In my opinion,

00:56:27.734 --> 00:56:32.434
entities that are
this intelligent,

00:56:32.467 --> 00:56:34.167
you never want
to wait for them

00:56:34.200 --> 00:56:35.634
to fight on
their terms."

00:56:40.033 --> 00:56:44.267
-TRAVIS: Good answer.
-LIAM: Yeah.

00:56:44.300 --> 00:56:49.067
MATT: And the slow
rolling impacts

00:56:49.100 --> 00:56:50.801
of the dragon's feet

00:56:50.834 --> 00:56:54.300
grow quieter and quieter
before you hear eventually...

00:56:54.334 --> 00:56:55.767
The wings lifting
up and you see

00:56:55.801 --> 00:56:59.501
as a cloud of
smoke and ash

00:56:59.534 --> 00:57:01.434
kind of pulls forth
into the tunnel,

00:57:01.467 --> 00:57:05.000
showing the lift off
as you can only ascertain

00:57:05.033 --> 00:57:08.033
J'Mon Sa Ord,
leader of Ank'Harel,

00:57:08.067 --> 00:57:12.067
the brass dragon begins flight
back towards their home.

00:57:12.100 --> 00:57:15.434
LAURA: Oh, shit, did J'Mon
fly here that entire way?

00:57:15.467 --> 00:57:18.934
SAM: No, I don't
I don't think so.

00:57:18.968 --> 00:57:20.400
TRAVIS: Flash.

00:57:20.434 --> 00:57:21.400
SAM: Maybe.

00:57:21.434 --> 00:57:24.634
LAURA: I was joking,
I was joking.

00:57:24.667 --> 00:57:27.334
SAM: As terrible as
this day has been,

00:57:27.367 --> 00:57:30.367
there is some gold at
the end of the tunnel.

00:57:30.400 --> 00:57:34.534
TRAVIS: Which is probably
rigged to explode.

00:57:34.567 --> 00:57:37.634
TALIESIN: I think it's
probably-- well--

00:57:37.667 --> 00:57:38.801
SAM: Want to go
check it out?

00:57:38.834 --> 00:57:40.868
LAURA: Kind of feel like,
we should, you know--

00:57:40.901 --> 00:57:42.367
Heal up a bit.

00:57:42.400 --> 00:57:43.901
I've been here before.

00:57:43.934 --> 00:57:47.901
It didn't go so well.

00:57:47.934 --> 00:57:49.868
PATRICK: Yeah, how knocked
about are they?

00:57:49.901 --> 00:57:52.501
I mean, obviously, singes
and abrasions and--

00:57:52.534 --> 00:57:54.701
LAURA: Like really, really
knocked to shit.

00:57:54.734 --> 00:57:57.601
TRAVIS: Raise your hand if you have
less than 30 hit points.

00:57:57.634 --> 00:57:59.200
MARISHA: I'm at 30.

