the distance echoing.

00:58:41.234 --> 00:58:43.534
LIAM: Clarota, Asum, Rothfuss.

00:58:43.567 --> 00:58:45.400
Never ends!

00:58:45.434 --> 00:58:47.300
PATRICK: But no, if
people are that--

00:58:47.334 --> 00:58:51.901
are that bad,
like, I'll--

00:58:51.934 --> 00:58:54.167
You know.

00:58:54.200 --> 00:58:55.400
How are you?

00:58:55.434 --> 00:58:57.467
You're obviously, like,
it's gonna be, like,

00:58:57.501 --> 00:58:59.701
are you like visibly
like knocked about?

00:58:59.734 --> 00:59:02.300
-LAURA: I mean she's--
-MARISHA: I kinda fell in a pit of lava.

00:59:02.334 --> 00:59:04.400
LAURA: She's basically black
cinder right now.

00:59:04.434 --> 00:59:06.167
PATRICK: Oh, really?

00:59:06.200 --> 00:59:07.934
-Okay.
-LAURA: She face planted into lava.

00:59:07.968 --> 00:59:09.767
LIAM: She's burned,
she's burned.

00:59:09.801 --> 00:59:13.300
PATRICK: I'm like, Do you really want to
go looking for gold right now?

00:59:13.334 --> 00:59:15.033
Because you--

00:59:15.067 --> 00:59:18.701
♪

00:59:18.734 --> 00:59:20.033
Would you like to come
over here and sit down?

00:59:20.067 --> 00:59:21.434
I can take a look at--

00:59:21.467 --> 00:59:23.467
TRAVIS: As they discuss, can I
just walk over to a pile of--

00:59:23.501 --> 00:59:25.367
LAURA: Kash, how low are
you on healing?

00:59:25.400 --> 00:59:27.701
Can you heal us?

00:59:27.734 --> 00:59:30.100
MATT: Kash and Zahra, who
just kind of sitting off

00:59:30.133 --> 00:59:33.033
of the edge of the cavern,
kind of taking a breather.

00:59:33.067 --> 00:59:37.300
"Um, well, I got a
little bit, I guess."

00:59:37.334 --> 00:59:40.534
Zahra, by the way,
is like healed to full.

00:59:40.567 --> 00:59:43.667
TRAVIS: Of course.

00:59:43.701 --> 00:59:45.501
MARISHA: Yeah, I just--

00:59:49.167 --> 00:59:52.100
Keyleth just
bursts into tears.

00:59:52.133 --> 00:59:54.133
She just start--

00:59:54.167 --> 00:59:56.734
I'm so tired!

00:59:56.767 --> 00:59:59.167
I'm so tired.

00:59:59.200 --> 01:00:01.367
PATRICK: I'll kinda just kinda
usher her off a little bit

01:00:01.400 --> 01:00:07.300
wherever, like, is a little less
in the middle of everything.

01:00:07.334 --> 01:00:08.868
And I've got
my little pack

01:00:08.901 --> 01:00:10.400
and we can lay
it on the blanket.

01:00:10.434 --> 01:00:13.300
And she needs to get
some of these charred,

01:00:13.334 --> 01:00:15.601
smoldering clothes off of her.

01:00:15.634 --> 01:00:17.300
And so I can
look at these burns

01:00:17.334 --> 01:00:21.133
and start, um, you know...

01:00:21.167 --> 01:00:23.033
LAURA: I nudge Vax.

01:00:23.067 --> 01:00:28.434
I think that guy's puttin'
moves on your woman.

01:00:28.467 --> 01:00:32.367
-Okay.
-TRAVIS: Super worried.

01:00:32.400 --> 01:00:34.441
MARISHA: I do the same to Kerr,

01:00:34.441 --> 01:00:37.801
I just...my eyes.

01:00:37.834 --> 01:00:40.501
MATT: Kash kind of walks up and
slaps you on your shoulder,

01:00:40.534 --> 01:00:45.968
Vex, and kind of a jolt
and you heal 14 points.

01:00:46.000 --> 01:00:47.868
Cure wounds a little too,

01:00:47.901 --> 01:00:51.334
but as a bit of a
jolt through your body.

01:00:51.367 --> 01:00:53.601
LAURA: It's good, it's good.

01:00:53.634 --> 01:00:56.300
-Thank you.
-MATT: "You're welcome."

01:00:56.334 --> 01:00:59.167
He turns back around and
walks back to Zahra.

01:00:59.200 --> 01:01:01.501
PATRICK: And I just kind of
do the slow talk.

01:01:01.534 --> 01:01:03.067
You know, we're kind of like,

01:01:03.100 --> 01:01:04.868
it's like, oh,
this isn't as bad

01:01:04.901 --> 01:01:06.534
as it looks
at first, you know.

01:01:06.567 --> 01:01:08.300
And, 'cause this
was the old thing

01:01:08.334 --> 01:01:10.234
that I did in town for years.

01:01:10.267 --> 01:01:12.200
Somebody would come to
me hurt and I'd be like,

01:01:12.234 --> 01:01:16.734
oh, it's like--nobody
knew who I was in town

01:01:16.767 --> 01:01:18.167
for 20 years.

01:01:18.200 --> 01:01:24.400
So I do the gentlest, least
obtrusive laying on of hands.

01:01:24.434 --> 01:01:26.234
You know, where it's like,
oh, you know,

01:01:26.267 --> 01:01:28.467
this probably stung
like the dickens,

01:01:28.501 --> 01:01:30.000
but, you know--

01:01:30.033 --> 01:01:31.067
Look at this,
look at this,

01:01:31.100 --> 01:01:32.901
it's just rubbing,
this is just--

01:01:32.934 --> 01:01:35.167
TRAVIS: Oh, you skinned your knees,
let me blow on that.

01:01:35.200 --> 01:01:36.801
(cross talk)

