TRAVIS: You give me
like chastity belts or--

01:15:03.901 --> 01:15:06.367
MATT: Look, man, the last
thing I expected was Grog

01:15:06.400 --> 01:15:08.901
to be the first to loot
for magical items.

01:15:08.934 --> 01:15:11.400
And roll a decent
investigation check.

01:15:11.434 --> 01:15:15.667
And yet, here you are,
discovering this deck.

01:15:15.701 --> 01:15:17.601
All right, so...

01:15:17.634 --> 01:15:20.133
With this...

01:15:20.167 --> 01:15:24.534
You pull the card out and it
looks like this beautiful

01:15:24.567 --> 01:15:28.067
tarot like design of what
looks like a metallic key

01:15:28.100 --> 01:15:30.801
that is currently
held aloft in space

01:15:30.834 --> 01:15:33.200
behind what looks
like almost like the stars

01:15:33.234 --> 01:15:39.167
converging into some sort of
a pattern in the night sky.

01:15:39.200 --> 01:15:40.977
TRAVIS: That's good, stars are nice.

01:15:40.977 --> 01:15:42.167
MATT: At this point--

01:15:42.200 --> 01:15:43.467
TRAVIS: Orion wouldn't fuck us.

01:15:43.501 --> 01:15:45.400
LIAM: Nope.

01:15:45.434 --> 01:15:50.200
PATRICK: That's not a
sword on his belt.

01:15:50.234 --> 01:15:51.667
MATT: As you pull the card
and look at it,

01:15:51.701 --> 01:15:55.501
the card bursts into flames,

01:15:55.534 --> 01:15:57.868
and you feel this slight
tingling in the hand

01:15:57.901 --> 01:16:01.567
that held the card.

01:16:01.601 --> 01:16:04.267
Suddenly, you watch as
there's a flash of light

01:16:04.300 --> 01:16:06.267
within your grasp with
what looks to be extending

01:16:06.300 --> 01:16:08.801
from where the card once was.

01:16:08.834 --> 01:16:12.601
You immediately feel
something steel in your hand

01:16:12.634 --> 01:16:14.400
and as you clutch your fingers
instinctually around it,

01:16:14.434 --> 01:16:16.100
and try to crush
whatever it is,

01:16:16.133 --> 01:16:20.868
you look and watch as this
beautiful looking scimitar

01:16:20.901 --> 01:16:23.334
like blade is now
in your grasp.

01:16:23.367 --> 01:16:25.968
TRAVIS: Oooh!

01:16:26.000 --> 01:16:27.400
Whoa.

01:16:27.434 --> 01:16:33.400
MATT: It's beautifully made,
an ornate hilt and hand guard.

01:16:33.434 --> 01:16:36.334
And it has like a chain dangling
from the bottom of the pommel

01:16:36.367 --> 01:16:39.100
that has, looks like
a small blue gem.

01:16:39.133 --> 01:16:40.934
It's a beautiful
looking piece of weaponry.

01:16:40.968 --> 01:16:42.033
And as you whip
it back and forth,

01:16:42.067 --> 01:16:43.367
it's perfectly balanced.

01:16:43.400 --> 01:16:47.200
TRAVIS: Does it make any noise
when I swing it?

01:16:47.234 --> 01:16:49.267
LAURA: A card turned into a sword?

01:16:49.300 --> 01:16:51.567
SAM: We should pull the other cards
to see what swords they'll make.

01:16:51.601 --> 01:16:53.234
PATRICK: You can do that 12 more times!

01:16:53.267 --> 01:16:55.701
TRAVIS: I'm apparently the
most powerful sorcerer

01:16:55.734 --> 01:16:57.667
that has ever lived.

01:16:57.701 --> 01:17:00.634
SAM: This is a deck
of weapon cards.

01:17:00.667 --> 01:17:02.934
LAURA: I mean seriously, though.

01:17:02.968 --> 01:17:05.334
TRAVIS: I have to hit
something with it.

01:17:05.367 --> 01:17:06.567
LAURA: Well, go hit
something with it.

01:17:06.601 --> 01:17:09.901
TRAVIS: Is there like a tall
statue around or anything?

01:17:09.934 --> 01:17:13.100
MATT: I mean, you can see
there are a few marble busts

01:17:13.133 --> 01:17:17.100
and things that have been
collected from the more--

01:17:17.133 --> 01:17:18.667
TRAVIS: A marble bust is good,
that's perfect.

01:17:18.701 --> 01:17:20.204
TALIESIN: Please don't
decimate the antiquities.

01:17:20.204 --> 01:17:21.634
TRAVIS: Can I pick it up?

01:17:21.667 --> 01:17:23.000
Lob it--

01:17:23.033 --> 01:17:25.400
LAURA: Grog, also don't forget
this is property of Emon.

01:17:25.434 --> 01:17:26.734
TRAVIS: It just broke because
you distracted me.

01:17:26.767 --> 01:17:29.968
(laughing)

01:17:32.501 --> 01:17:34.701
I've got to go
find another bust.

01:17:34.734 --> 01:17:36.027
Is there another?

01:17:36.027 --> 01:17:37.457
MATT: There are a few, yeah.

01:17:37.457 --> 01:17:39.100
TRAVIS: Thank God there's another.

01:17:39.133 --> 01:17:41.841
MATT: You need to recognize,
some of these used to exist

01:17:41.841 --> 01:17:43.230
in the Alabaster Lyceum.

01:17:43.234 --> 01:17:47.033
These are actually busts
of old heralded teachers

01:17:47.067 --> 01:17:50.680
within the arcane halls
of the lyceum.

01:17:50.680 --> 01:17:53.133
-TRAVIS: They wrote on stuff, right?
-MATT: Yeah.

01:17:53.167 --> 01:17:55.967
TRAVIS: Okay, then nobody cares
what they looked like, cool.

01:17:55.967 --> 01:17:58.234
Take it and lob it
in the air, big swing.

01:17:58.267 --> 01:18:00.531
-MATT: Make an attack roll.
-TRAVIS: Okay.

01:18:01.894 --> 01:18:03.767
Can I make this
a reckless attack?

01:18:03.801 --> 01:18:05.667
MATT: You can.

01:18:05.701 --> 01:18:08.144
TALIESIN: Is it a strength
or dex weapon?

01:18:08.144 --> 01:18:09.467
MATT: It's a strength weapon.

01:18:09.501 --> 01:18:10.270
TALIESIN: Ah.

01:18:10.270 --> 01:18:11.567
TRAVIS: Twenty seven.

01:18:11.601 --> 01:18:14.400
MATT: Twenty seven.
Um, roll damage.

01:18:14.434 --> 01:18:17.534
It is considered a scimitar.

01:18:17.567 --> 01:18:18.367
TRAVIS: Okay.

01:18:18.400 --> 01:18:19.567
LAURA: A scimitar.

01:18:19.601 --> 01:18:21.667
MATT: It's a d8, I believe.

01:18:23.801 --> 01:18:26.297
MARISHA: It's considered a scimitar.

01:18:26.297 --> 01:18:27.601
TALIESIN: But really.

01:18:27.634 --> 01:18:30.067
PATRICK: It looks exactly
like a scimitar.

01:18:30.100 --> 01:18:31.340
TALIESIN: It's a meal.

01:18:31.340 --> 01:18:35.300
(cross talk)

01:18:35.334 --> 01:18:38.534
TRAVIS: I'm kind of doing it
off of the blood axe, so like 16?

01:18:38.567 --> 01:18:40.400
No necrotic no--

01:18:40.434 --> 01:18:42.100
MATT: No, no magical bonus on it.

01:18:42.133 --> 01:18:44.154
-TRAVIS: Just 16.
-MATT: 16, okay.

01:18:44.154 --> 01:18:45.868
And with your gauntlets
you have siege,

01:18:45.901 --> 01:18:48.027
which means you
do double damage

01:18:48.027 --> 01:18:49.467
against objects and structures.

01:18:49.501 --> 01:18:50.854
So as you take the sword back

01:18:50.854 --> 01:18:52.467
you strike the
edge of this bust

01:18:52.501 --> 01:18:56.400
and watch it just
turn to gravel and dust.

01:18:56.434 --> 01:18:59.117
Pshhh, it just shatters
and explodes out the side

01:18:59.117 --> 01:19:00.601
with one singular swing

01:19:00.634 --> 01:19:02.847
and you watch as
the small chunks of rock

01:19:02.847 --> 01:19:05.334
that still somewhat
resemble any sort of, you know,

01:19:05.367 --> 01:19:10.033
sculptured structure go
scattering across the black,

01:19:10.067 --> 01:19:12.868
you know, lava and magma
encrusted darkened floor

01:19:12.901 --> 01:19:14.734
of the cavern.

01:19:14.767 --> 01:19:16.334
Blade is untouched.

01:19:16.367 --> 01:19:18.934
TRAVIS: It is really
well balanced, that is,

01:19:18.968 --> 01:19:21.711
and I just hold
it up to my ear.

01:19:22.934 --> 01:19:24.767
(laughing)

01:19:24.801 --> 01:19:26.734
MATT: A moment passes.

01:19:26.767 --> 01:19:28.000
A second moment passes.

01:19:28.033 --> 01:19:29.700
-TRAVIS: We're good.
-LAURA: Yeah.

01:19:29.700 --> 01:19:30.868
TRAVIS: We're totally good.

01:19:30.901 --> 01:19:32.161
SAM: It's a cool weapon.

01:19:32.161 --> 01:19:33.133
TRAVIS: It is, yeah.

01:19:33.167 --> 01:19:38.854
And I stealthily try
and pocket the other cards.

01:19:39.868 --> 01:19:41.501
LAURA: What are you doing?

01:19:41.534 --> 01:19:45.133
TRAVIS: But I haven't showered in
a few days and my bum itches.

01:19:45.167 --> 01:19:47.431
MATT: Make a slight of
hand check, Grog.

01:19:47.431 --> 01:19:50.160
(laughing)

01:19:50.160 --> 01:19:52.133
TRAVIS: Shit, that's a natural 1!

01:19:52.167 --> 01:19:54.767
(laughing)

01:19:54.801 --> 01:19:56.300
God damn it!

01:19:56.334 --> 01:20:00.200
MATT: You watch as Grog so
discreetly takes the cards

01:20:00.234 --> 01:20:02.601
and just kind of throws them.

01:20:02.634 --> 01:20:05.817
(laughing)

01:20:05.817 --> 01:20:07.580
Somehow throws
them closer to you

01:20:07.580 --> 01:20:09.133
and in between
him and you guys,

01:20:09.167 --> 01:20:10.971
trying to hide them
and just go thdummp.

01:20:10.971 --> 01:20:12.367
LAURA: I pick them up.

01:20:12.400 --> 01:20:13.734
SAM: Does anyone know
what these are?

01:20:13.767 --> 01:20:15.601
LAURA: Grog just made a sword
out of one of these cards.

01:20:15.634 --> 01:20:16.734
Do we know what this is?

01:20:16.767 --> 01:20:18.367
TRAVIS: They only activate
under my magical touch.

01:20:18.400 --> 01:20:20.837
SAM: I'm gonna look at it
and just see if I happen

01:20:20.837 --> 01:20:22.133
to know anything about it.

01:20:22.167 --> 01:20:23.687
MATT: Roll an arcana check.

01:20:23.687 --> 01:20:26.334
SAM: I don't know
anything about it.

01:20:26.367 --> 01:20:28.834
I rolled a 12, do I
know anything about it?

01:20:28.868 --> 01:20:31.300
MATT: Mmm, they're
apparently magical.

01:20:31.334 --> 01:20:32.501
TALIESIN: Twenty three.

01:20:32.534 --> 01:20:36.167
MATT: Twenty three.
You, being a studious child

01:20:36.200 --> 01:20:38.770
and reading many things,
you've heard rumors,

01:20:38.770 --> 01:20:40.033
you have heard myths,

01:20:40.067 --> 01:20:43.367
you have heard
legends of glory and woe

01:20:43.400 --> 01:20:45.434
based around an
artifact referred to

01:20:45.467 --> 01:20:47.067
as the Deck of Many Things.

01:20:47.100 --> 01:20:48.901
LAURA: I start to open it up and--

01:20:48.934 --> 01:20:50.934
TALIESIN: No, no, no, no.

01:20:50.968 --> 01:20:52.801
No, oh, he looks--

01:20:52.834 --> 01:20:54.868
LAURA: I think these made weapons.

01:20:54.901 --> 01:20:56.868
TALIESIN: They can make
a lot of things.

01:20:56.901 --> 01:20:58.281
SAM: Can they make bad things?

01:20:58.281 --> 01:21:00.133
TALIESIN: They can make a
lot of bad things.

01:21:00.167 --> 01:21:01.767
SAM: And do you know
what activates them,

01:21:01.801 --> 01:21:03.100
just looking at a card?

01:21:03.133 --> 01:21:05.868
TALIESIN: If I recall,
it doesn't take much.

01:21:05.901 --> 01:21:08.957
LAURA: I just shut the little
case and stuff it in my...

01:21:08.957 --> 01:21:10.284
SAM: Let's keep it.

01:21:10.284 --> 01:21:12.200
TALIESIN: I was going to say
let's put it somewhere

01:21:12.234 --> 01:21:14.080
where no one will
ever find it,

01:21:14.080 --> 01:21:16.000
but that will
be fine for now.

01:21:16.033 --> 01:21:19.100
TRAVIS: May, may I--I actually,
I found that.

01:21:19.133 --> 01:21:20.901
LAURA: Oh, Grog, that's sweet.

01:21:20.934 --> 01:21:23.501
TRAVIS: But I don't, I want to
hold on to it, it's mine.

01:21:23.534 --> 01:21:24.501
LAURA: No.

01:21:24.534 --> 01:21:26.501
TRAVIS: You can keep
all the other gold.

01:21:26.534 --> 01:21:28.968
LAURA: Yeah, no, I don't
trust you with it.

01:21:29.000 --> 01:21:29.801
TRAVIS: Why not?

01:21:29.834 --> 01:21:30.884
LAURA: Because you do stupid things.

01:21:30.884 --> 01:21:32.067
TRAVIS: Look what I made.

01:21:32.100 --> 01:21:33.834
LAURA: You made a beautiful sword
and I'm proud of you.

01:21:33.868 --> 01:21:36.167
TRAVIS: Yeah, I'm sure it's like
reactive its user--

01:21:36.200 --> 01:21:39.464
LAURA: Maybe there's another set
in here, we should find it!

01:21:39.464 --> 01:21:41.133
TRAVIS: And then you can have it.

01:21:41.167 --> 01:21:44.424
LAURA: No, if we find another set,
you can have it.

01:21:45.467 --> 01:21:47.127
LIAM: That's a bad deal, too.

01:21:47.127 --> 01:21:49.847
TRAVIS: I go to look for
another Deck of Many Things

01:21:49.847 --> 01:21:51.361
and nothing else.

01:21:51.361 --> 01:21:52.734
(laughing)

01:21:52.767 --> 01:21:55.634
MATT: For all the gold
that is in this cavern,

01:21:55.667 --> 01:21:59.834
none of it has any
luster or shine to you

01:21:59.868 --> 01:22:02.567
as your singularly focused
on finding another one

01:22:02.601 --> 01:22:04.000
of these deck of cards.

01:22:04.033 --> 01:22:07.100
You are throwing handfuls of
platinum over your shoulder.

01:22:07.133 --> 01:22:08.400
TRAVIS: Garbage.

01:22:08.434 --> 01:22:09.968
Rubbish, filth.

01:22:10.000 --> 01:22:11.434
(laughing)

01:22:11.467 --> 01:22:14.033
Life has no luster
to it anymore.

01:22:14.067 --> 01:22:15.968
You wretched...

01:22:17.567 --> 01:22:21.434
MATT: All right, so continuing off of
your investigation check--

01:22:21.467 --> 01:22:23.567
-LIAM: What a heart attack.
-TALIESIN: Wow.

01:22:23.601 --> 01:22:25.734
MATT: So you do have the
Deck of Many Things

01:22:25.767 --> 01:22:27.200
which now has
12 cards in it.

01:22:27.234 --> 01:22:28.434
LAURA: Oh, my God.

01:22:28.467 --> 01:22:29.634
TALIESIN: Ah!

01:22:29.667 --> 01:22:31.400
MATT: I'm gonna hand that to Laura.

01:22:31.434 --> 01:22:35.267
SAM: Next time I go back to casino,
I'm taking that with me.

01:22:35.300 --> 01:22:37.434
MATT: You do--you
have that tapestry.

01:22:37.467 --> 01:22:41.367
You have--you find what
looks to be a pair of very fine

01:22:41.400 --> 01:22:44.400
crafted dark
green leather boots

01:22:44.434 --> 01:22:46.868
that have almost a silver
or platinum scrolling

01:22:46.901 --> 01:22:48.484
along the edges
of the leather,

01:22:48.484 --> 01:22:50.017
almost like
leaves and branches

01:22:50.017 --> 01:22:52.501
that tangle in towards
the front of the foot.

01:22:52.534 --> 01:22:53.968
LAURA: Do they look Elvish?

01:22:54.000 --> 01:22:56.300
MATT: It looks Elvish in design.

01:22:56.334 --> 01:22:57.968
And you find
what looks to be

01:22:58.000 --> 01:23:03.267
a very, very well
crafted war hammer.

01:23:03.300 --> 01:23:06.898
It has--its shape
and its design is--

01:23:08.000 --> 01:23:10.167
and only because you've seen
this type of handle before--

01:23:10.200 --> 01:23:12.534
it appears to be
Dwarven in make.

01:23:12.567 --> 01:23:16.934
And it has a
series of runes and glyphs

01:23:16.968 --> 01:23:19.834
along the sides of
the war hammer head itself

01:23:19.868 --> 01:23:23.154
that seem to
give you the sense

01:23:23.154 --> 01:23:24.701
that this is a very expensive,

01:23:24.734 --> 01:23:27.467
or at least a very, very
elegantly crafted weapon.

01:23:27.501 --> 01:23:29.000
LAURA: Okay.

01:23:33.567 --> 01:23:35.067
Sweet.

01:23:35.100 --> 01:23:38.133
I can't, can I see if
they're magic, I can't can I?

01:23:38.167 --> 01:23:41.567
MATT: I mean, you can take
the rest of your short rest

01:23:41.601 --> 01:23:43.501
with one of the objects

01:23:43.534 --> 01:23:45.644
to see if you can
ascertain any sort of magic

01:23:45.644 --> 01:23:47.094
or information about it.

01:23:47.094 --> 01:23:49.400
LAURA: I'm gonna do that
on the tapestry.

01:23:49.434 --> 01:23:50.534
MATT: Okay.

01:23:50.567 --> 01:23:52.133
-TALIESIN: I'm with you.
-LAURA: Fly, fly for me.

01:23:52.167 --> 01:23:54.000
MATT: All right,
the rest of you guys,

01:23:54.033 --> 01:23:56.033
is there anything else should
rest, just healing up?

01:23:56.067 --> 01:23:57.937
TALIESIN: Healing up,
fixing my guns,

01:23:57.937 --> 01:23:59.997
and then sort of
trying to navigate

01:23:59.997 --> 01:24:01.467
some of this crazy in here

01:24:01.501 --> 01:24:03.033
and then eventually
looking around the cavern

01:24:03.067 --> 01:24:04.067
to see if there's anything.

01:24:04.100 --> 01:24:05.834
MATT: Has everyone
spent their hit dice?

01:24:05.868 --> 01:24:07.367
What are we at
in point totals here?

01:24:07.400 --> 01:24:08.968
SAM: Sixty eight.

01:24:09.000 --> 01:24:10.334
TALIESIN: I've got 102.

01:24:10.367 --> 01:24:11.701
MARISHA: Seventy nine.

01:24:11.734 --> 01:24:12.667
MATT: I think you're still full.

01:24:12.701 --> 01:24:14.067
LIAM: Ninety nine.

01:24:14.100 --> 01:24:15.534
LAURA: One hundred.

01:24:15.567 --> 01:24:17.434
TRAVIS: I didn't roll any 'cause
I was looking through this

01:24:17.467 --> 01:24:19.974
Deck of Many Things!
90.

01:24:20.767 --> 01:24:22.033
MATT: Ninety, okay.

01:24:22.067 --> 01:24:24.741
At the end
of the short rest,

01:24:26.934 --> 01:24:30.501
Vex, you've taken the
time with the tapestry,

01:24:30.534 --> 01:24:31.934
looking at it.

01:24:31.968 --> 01:24:34.234
Its design kind of
hurts your heart a little bit

01:24:34.267 --> 01:24:37.104
'cause it reminds you of the
flying carpet that you once had

01:24:37.104 --> 01:24:39.767
and you're like
hoping and praying.

01:24:39.801 --> 01:24:42.467
And as it--as you're
concentrating on it,

01:24:42.501 --> 01:24:44.968
and hoping that
something comes to you,

01:24:45.000 --> 01:24:51.567
you're like, "Fly,"
you know, "Go."

01:24:51.601 --> 01:24:53.037
"Traverse, carry."

01:24:53.037 --> 01:24:54.961
You're just throwing
all these words out.

01:24:54.961 --> 01:24:57.364
And as you're just getting
more and more exhausted,

01:24:57.364 --> 01:24:59.667
and the rest of your
party kind of look over

01:24:59.667 --> 01:25:02.067
with this, "Oh, give it up,
girl," kind of look

01:25:02.100 --> 01:25:03.701
and shaking their head,

01:25:03.734 --> 01:25:06.934
a sudden hit of
inspiration hits your mind

01:25:06.968 --> 01:25:08.901
and clarifies--the word "lift."

01:25:08.934 --> 01:25:11.834
You say lift and the tapestry
goes fll fll fll.

01:25:11.868 --> 01:25:15.280
LAURA: Shut the fucking--!

01:25:16.033 --> 01:25:17.000
You guys!

01:25:17.033 --> 01:25:19.434
VAX: (snoring)

01:25:19.467 --> 01:25:22.267
TRAVIS: It's a flying telefaphy.

01:25:22.300 --> 01:25:24.667
LAURA: Lift higher.

01:25:24.701 --> 01:25:27.297
♪ High up in love ♪♪

01:25:28.200 --> 01:25:30.367
SAM: Another flying carpet.

01:25:30.400 --> 01:25:32.234
