01:35:31.667 --> 01:35:35.567
LAURA: We owe The Clasp
half of our loot.

01:35:35.601 --> 01:35:37.000
SAM: What does that mean?

01:35:37.033 --> 01:35:40.434
MARISHA: But that's our loot,
that's not the city's.

01:35:40.467 --> 01:35:45.367
LAURA: If we don't take as much,
then we don't give them as much.

01:35:45.400 --> 01:35:47.834
SAM: I don't think they
would view it that way.

01:35:47.868 --> 01:35:49.790
TALIESIN: That's the deal they made.

01:35:49.790 --> 01:35:52.734
This is not our loot
we just looted.

01:35:52.767 --> 01:35:56.434
LAURA: It's not our money,
it's Emon's.

01:35:56.467 --> 01:35:58.367
MARISHA: The Clasp should
be aware of that.

01:35:58.400 --> 01:36:00.281
SAM: I think we're going
to make an enemy

01:36:00.281 --> 01:36:01.501
out of them by doing this.

01:36:01.534 --> 01:36:03.827
TALIESIN: I think we're going to
keep an enemy out of them

01:36:03.827 --> 01:36:04.968
is really more likely.

01:36:05.000 --> 01:36:07.067
LAURA: How do we even
know who we told?

01:36:07.100 --> 01:36:08.334
It could have
been two underlings,

01:36:08.367 --> 01:36:09.834
nobody would believe
what they said anyway.

01:36:09.868 --> 01:36:12.167
TRAVIS: Sure would be a gesture in
the right direction, though.

01:36:12.200 --> 01:36:14.167
MARISHA: Well we can, I'm sure
we can still throw them

01:36:14.200 --> 01:36:16.501
a little bit
of platinum, but...

01:36:16.534 --> 01:36:17.767
I mean, Percy--

01:36:17.801 --> 01:36:19.267
SAM: What like 5,000,
is that what you're saying,

01:36:19.300 --> 01:36:21.400
half of, half
of what we take?

01:36:21.434 --> 01:36:23.133
How does this work?

01:36:23.167 --> 01:36:25.701
That's nothing to them.

01:36:25.734 --> 01:36:27.267
We promised them
untold riches.

01:36:27.300 --> 01:36:29.200
LAURA: We took 1,000 platinum
for ourselves.

01:36:29.234 --> 01:36:31.567
If we took another 1,000
and gave it to The Clasp,

01:36:31.601 --> 01:36:32.734
that's a lot of money.

01:36:32.767 --> 01:36:34.200
TRAVIS: How about we don't
give them anything

01:36:34.234 --> 01:36:36.200
and we just let them know
it's clear to come down here

01:36:36.234 --> 01:36:37.667
and deal with it as they will.

01:36:37.701 --> 01:36:39.100
SAM: They'll take everything.

01:36:39.133 --> 01:36:41.167
TALIESIN: I don't know if they'll
take everything, actually.

01:36:41.200 --> 01:36:44.534
MARISHA: Well, Percy, you once
said that every good city

01:36:44.567 --> 01:36:46.067
needs a good underbelly.

01:36:46.100 --> 01:36:47.634
TALIESIN: That's true.

01:36:47.667 --> 01:36:50.167
MARISHA: I imagine that
the underbelly would also

01:36:50.200 --> 01:36:52.968
have a vested interest
in a having good city,

01:36:53.000 --> 01:36:54.434
I imagine it
works both ways, right?

01:36:54.467 --> 01:36:55.968
TALIESIN: I'm so proud
of you right now.

01:36:56.000 --> 01:36:57.267
MARISHA: Yeah, thank you.

01:36:57.300 --> 01:36:58.501
TALIESIN: Oh my God.

01:36:58.534 --> 01:37:00.100
MARISHA: I'm learning from you,
just like a little,

01:37:00.133 --> 01:37:01.534
-where it's appropriate.
-TALIESIN: I'm so sorry,

01:37:01.567 --> 01:37:03.000
-but I'm so proud.
-MARISHA: Only where it's appropriate.

01:37:03.033 --> 01:37:04.267
TRAVIS: So what is it,
we hand deliver it

01:37:04.300 --> 01:37:05.868
or we just let them know
it's clear to come down?

01:37:05.901 --> 01:37:08.701
SAM: Hand deliver, we don't want
them coming here at all.

01:37:08.734 --> 01:37:10.033
TRAVIS: I agree, it's more personal.

01:37:10.067 --> 01:37:13.000
You write the limerick and
we give them two platinum.

01:37:13.033 --> 01:37:14.367
(laughing)

01:37:14.400 --> 01:37:15.901
What was the number you said?

01:37:15.934 --> 01:37:18.334
LAURA: That two is what I said, yes.

01:37:18.367 --> 01:37:22.067
PATRICK: Send them an envelope
with half of the deck in it.

01:37:22.100 --> 01:37:24.537
(gasps)

01:37:24.537 --> 01:37:26.667
TRAVIS: It just turns into swords--

01:37:26.701 --> 01:37:29.501
TALIESIN: How are you the cruelest
human I've ever--oh, my.

01:37:29.534 --> 01:37:30.601
That's amazing.

01:37:30.634 --> 01:37:32.890
LAURA: I don't know what
the deck can do.

01:37:32.890 --> 01:37:36.968
Could it, could it cause
the entire city to crumble?

01:37:37.000 --> 01:37:38.300
Potentially?

01:37:42.267 --> 01:37:43.367
Ooh.

01:37:43.400 --> 01:37:44.434
PATRICK: That, I do not know.

01:37:44.467 --> 01:37:45.787
TALIESIN: We can give them the deck.

01:37:45.787 --> 01:37:46.934
LIAM: Vax just woke up.

01:37:46.968 --> 01:37:49.400
MATT: Hi, Vax, welcome back.

01:37:49.434 --> 01:37:51.567
TRAVIS: So, what, five
thousand platinum?

01:37:51.601 --> 01:37:53.000
SAM: Five thousand platinum.

01:37:53.033 --> 01:37:55.234
LAURA: Why five tho--where are you
coming up with these numbers?

01:37:55.267 --> 01:37:58.234
MARISHA: You literally said
different numbers every time.

01:37:58.267 --> 01:38:00.501
TRAVIS: We could give them like
three pizza platinum,

01:38:00.534 --> 01:38:01.767
it doesn't
really matter to me,

01:38:01.801 --> 01:38:03.100
I just want to go.

01:38:03.133 --> 01:38:04.300
-LIAM: Hey, big man?
-TRAVIS: Yeah.

01:38:04.334 --> 01:38:05.634
LIAM: That's a nice sword,
where did you get that?

01:38:05.667 --> 01:38:07.911
TRAVIS: I took out a card
of this little pouch

01:38:07.911 --> 01:38:09.643
and it turned into this thing.

01:38:09.643 --> 01:38:11.367
LIAM: What are you talking about?

01:38:11.400 --> 01:38:13.850
TRAVIS: Yeah, it was like a little card
in like a leather pouch

01:38:13.850 --> 01:38:15.431
and then Vex took it from me

01:38:15.431 --> 01:38:18.367
'cause apparently
I make too many weapons.

01:38:18.400 --> 01:38:21.400
SAM: If we want them
to be our allies,

01:38:21.434 --> 01:38:23.667
and not hate us
and try to kill us,

01:38:23.701 --> 01:38:26.701
we have to give them
a good amount of money.

01:38:26.734 --> 01:38:27.901
LIAM: What, The Clasp?

01:38:27.934 --> 01:38:28.801
SAM: Yes.

01:38:28.834 --> 01:38:30.300
LIAM: We're talking about payment.

01:38:30.334 --> 01:38:33.334
LAURA: We give them 1,000 platinum and
say that's half of what we took.

01:38:33.367 --> 01:38:35.934
LIAM: Oh, they're a crime syndicate,
they're gonna laugh at that.

01:38:35.968 --> 01:38:37.367
SAM: I agree.

01:38:37.400 --> 01:38:41.567
PATRICK: And they know when someone's
running a game on them.

01:38:41.601 --> 01:38:44.167
LAURA: But we didn't take any more,
that's our loot.

01:38:44.200 --> 01:38:46.634
SAM: That's not how
they're gonna see this.

01:38:46.667 --> 01:38:48.547
LIAM: That's a letter
of the law argument,

01:38:48.547 --> 01:38:50.334
they're gonna want
to go spirit.

01:38:50.367 --> 01:38:55.317
MARISHA: We also just saved their
city from utter destruction.

01:38:55.317 --> 01:38:57.501
TRAVIS: Honestly, are we
gonna stay around

01:38:57.534 --> 01:39:00.234
and really regulate what happens
here, we're not, right?

01:39:00.267 --> 01:39:01.467
We've got shit to do.

01:39:01.501 --> 01:39:02.968
TALIESIN: I would honestly say,

01:39:03.000 --> 01:39:05.901
and I cannot believe
that I'm agreeing to this,

01:39:05.934 --> 01:39:07.601
but I think just
if we run into them,

01:39:07.634 --> 01:39:09.737
we let them know
that the dragon's dead

01:39:09.737 --> 01:39:11.801
and that's where it is.

01:39:11.834 --> 01:39:13.567
TRAVIS: I'm with Percy.

01:39:13.601 --> 01:39:15.000
TALIESIN: They're not gonna
bankrupt the city,

01:39:15.033 --> 01:39:16.701
it's not in
their best interests.

01:39:16.734 --> 01:39:17.934
They're gonna
take a look at it

01:39:17.968 --> 01:39:20.000
and they're gonna get
what they can carry.

01:39:22.367 --> 01:39:25.000
SAM: So we're turning over the city
and the city's treasury

01:39:25.033 --> 01:39:26.467
to a bunch of thieves.

01:39:26.501 --> 01:39:28.434
TALIESIN: We turned over the city
to a bunch of thieves,

01:39:28.467 --> 01:39:29.901
they've basically
been running the place

01:39:29.934 --> 01:39:32.534
for the past few months.

01:39:32.567 --> 01:39:34.200
PATRICK: How small town am I?

01:39:34.234 --> 01:39:35.787
Do I know about these folks?

01:39:35.787 --> 01:39:38.133
MATT: You've never dealt
with them directly

01:39:38.167 --> 01:39:42.534
other than scaring off a
couple of younger cutthroats

01:39:42.567 --> 01:39:44.701
you caught in like
an alleyway here or there.

01:39:44.734 --> 01:39:46.491
But you're aware of The Clasp.

01:39:46.491 --> 01:39:48.868
The Clasp, while
largely centered in Emon,

01:39:48.901 --> 01:39:51.567
is a syndicate that is
across all Tal'Dorei

01:39:51.601 --> 01:39:54.434
and has some hand in every
village no matter how small.

01:39:54.467 --> 01:39:56.400
PATRICK: Right.

01:39:56.434 --> 01:39:58.434
LAURA: Maybe we let them
know that it's there,

01:39:58.467 --> 01:40:00.000
but that the
guards are coming.

01:40:00.033 --> 01:40:01.334
They won't have
a lot of time.

01:40:01.367 --> 01:40:04.634
MARISHA: Why don't we just hand
this over to someone else

01:40:04.667 --> 01:40:06.000
and let them handle it?

01:40:06.033 --> 01:40:08.601
PATRICK: If you hand it
over to someone else,

01:40:08.601 --> 01:40:11.567
and send them a letter, it
will take a while to get there.

01:40:11.601 --> 01:40:13.267
SAM: The Clasp?

01:40:13.300 --> 01:40:15.887
They're down the hallway.

01:40:15.887 --> 01:40:16.968
PATRICK: Which one?

01:40:17.000 --> 01:40:18.534
TRAVIS: Over yonder.

01:40:18.567 --> 01:40:20.968
SAM: They're in the sewers
1,000 meters from here.

01:40:21.000 --> 01:40:22.834
PATRICK: Oh.

01:40:24.847 --> 01:40:26.868
MARISHA: Regardless,
I agree with Grog.

01:40:26.901 --> 01:40:30.200
We have more important things
to worry about right now.

01:40:30.234 --> 01:40:31.910
TRAVIS: I'm running for office.

01:40:31.910 --> 01:40:34.701
SAM: T-shirt: Regardless,
I agree with Grog.

01:40:34.734 --> 01:40:37.968
(laughing)

01:40:40.200 --> 01:40:43.567
MARISHA: Things never
been said before.

01:40:43.601 --> 01:40:46.033
PATRICK: Is there any of
the people collected,

01:40:46.067 --> 01:40:47.601
the generals or whatever,

01:40:47.634 --> 01:40:49.934
have you worked
with them as well?

01:40:49.968 --> 01:40:51.000
LAURA: The Clasp or the--

01:40:51.033 --> 01:40:55.033
PATRICK: No, the former
leaders of this city,

01:40:55.067 --> 01:40:56.868
any of the people
that you've--

01:40:56.901 --> 01:40:59.100
SAM: The military, we can put
them in charge of this.

01:40:59.133 --> 01:41:01.534
TALIESIN: There's not
really any military.

01:41:01.567 --> 01:41:03.534
SAM: There's a visiting army.

01:41:03.567 --> 01:41:04.834
Yeah, we can put
them in charge of it,

01:41:04.868 --> 01:41:06.167
at least temporarily.

01:41:06.200 --> 01:41:07.367
They can be trusted.

01:41:07.400 --> 01:41:08.467
TALIESIN: Can they?

01:41:08.501 --> 01:41:12.567
LIAM: Kima, do you feel
like keeping an eye

01:41:12.601 --> 01:41:17.133
on a small group of
soldiers from Syngorn?

01:41:17.167 --> 01:41:18.387
Protecting this?

01:41:18.387 --> 01:41:19.670
A few days?

01:41:19.670 --> 01:41:22.334
MATT: "I could probably run it,
I'd probably have to go

01:41:22.367 --> 01:41:23.767
and check in with Allie.

01:41:23.801 --> 01:41:26.227
I'm sure she'd be interested
in knowing about this

01:41:26.227 --> 01:41:28.033
since she's, you know,
part of the council."

01:41:28.067 --> 01:41:29.467
LAURA: Right, we need to tell her.

01:41:29.501 --> 01:41:33.767
MATT: "We have Asum--I mean
we still have a number

01:41:33.801 --> 01:41:35.367
of standing council members

01:41:35.400 --> 01:41:37.200
and there's a few we still
haven't accounted for."

01:41:37.234 --> 01:41:38.067
LIAM: This is your home.

01:41:38.100 --> 01:41:39.200
TALIESIN: That would be better.

01:41:39.234 --> 01:41:41.430
MATT: "My home is Westruun,
to be honest,

01:41:41.430 --> 01:41:44.467
but I've kind of taken
this as a second home."

01:41:44.501 --> 01:41:47.734
TALIESIN: Far more stories of treasures
being looted by foreigners.

01:41:47.767 --> 01:41:50.667
LAURA: Honestly, we need to get to
Whitestone, speaking of.

01:41:50.701 --> 01:41:53.138
TRAVIS: Yeah, don't we need
to like get a hand

01:41:53.138 --> 01:41:55.567
and plant it under a tree
or something like that?

01:41:55.601 --> 01:41:57.501
LAURA: Yes.

01:41:57.534 --> 01:41:58.220
Yes.

01:41:58.220 --> 01:41:59.530
SAM: Forgot about that.

01:41:59.530 --> 01:42:00.767
TALIESIN: We have a hand.

01:42:00.801 --> 01:42:02.104
MARISHA: We have a hand.

01:42:02.104 --> 01:42:03.934
LAURA: We have ashes to
bury in Vasselheim.

01:42:03.968 --> 01:42:05.167
MARISHA: We have a lot to do.

01:42:05.200 --> 01:42:06.868
LAURA: We have to find out
where the fuck Raishan is.

01:42:06.901 --> 01:42:08.834
Can we see if maybe
she went to Whitestone

01:42:08.868 --> 01:42:10.634
and the whole city's decimated?

01:42:10.667 --> 01:42:14.000
MARISHA: I can try and scry
with the scrying eye,

01:42:14.033 --> 01:42:16.033
but that's it.

01:42:16.067 --> 01:42:18.351
TRAVIS: How about we go to
Whitestone and then scry?

01:42:18.351 --> 01:42:20.767
SAM: Well, we won't need
to if we're there.

01:42:20.801 --> 01:42:22.167
MARISHA: Yeah.

01:42:22.200 --> 01:42:23.968
LAURA: Just find out
if it's all right.

01:42:24.000 --> 01:42:25.743
TALIESIN: Let's crawl upstairs.

01:42:25.743 --> 01:42:28.100
Let's keep some
people on this, Kima,

01:42:28.133 --> 01:42:29.968
and we'll crawl upstairs.

01:42:30.000 --> 01:42:31.334
MARISHA: I can try to scry on Rai--

01:42:31.367 --> 01:42:35.367
Did I find a little, like a
scale of hers, by the way?

01:42:35.400 --> 01:42:37.901
MATT: Glancing about, uh...
roll an investigation check

01:42:37.934 --> 01:42:39.434
specifically
looking for the scale.

01:42:39.467 --> 01:42:41.734
As opposed to looking for
other things about the room.

01:42:41.767 --> 01:42:44.701
TALIESIN: That's crock, that's--
yeah, I know.

01:42:44.734 --> 01:42:46.100
MARISHA: That's slightly better.

01:42:46.133 --> 01:42:47.934
Uh, ten total.

01:42:47.968 --> 01:42:51.734
MATT: Ten total? It takes
you about ten minutes

01:42:51.767 --> 01:42:56.667
and because the
shifting low light in here

01:42:56.701 --> 01:43:00.300
the rocky formations
of the ground itself,

01:43:00.334 --> 01:43:04.467
you're having a hard time
finding any scales of Raishan's.

01:43:04.501 --> 01:43:06.834
MARISHA: Anything, blood?

01:43:06.868 --> 01:43:08.901
MATT: It takes you about
15 or 20 minutes

01:43:08.934 --> 01:43:11.334
before you actually
find a small cluster.

01:43:11.367 --> 01:43:15.400
From one of the wounds
left behind by Grog.

01:43:15.434 --> 01:43:17.100
MARISHA: Yeah, that'll do it, yeah.

01:43:17.133 --> 01:43:19.400
TALIESIN: I'm gonna
grab the bag of colding

01:43:19.434 --> 01:43:23.267
and take samples of the
dragon eggs that we cracked,

01:43:23.300 --> 01:43:28.447
the fluid, the bodies, like I'll
put the whole thing in there.

01:43:30.601 --> 01:43:32.200
We need that.

01:43:32.234 --> 01:43:34.234
PATRICK: They intend?

01:43:34.267 --> 01:43:38.267
-They took the body--
-LAURA: Raishan?

01:43:38.300 --> 01:43:44.100
LIAM: She, uh, no, no, she's been
playing us for a long time.

01:43:44.133 --> 01:43:47.033
We were in a loose
agreement with her

01:43:47.067 --> 01:43:49.701
to get to today
and we've never felt

01:43:49.734 --> 01:43:52.834
like she's told us
the whole picture.

01:43:52.868 --> 01:43:56.434
Uh, we have watched her
gas scores of people

01:43:56.467 --> 01:43:58.601
in front of us.

01:43:58.634 --> 01:44:03.200
She's killed many
of your friends.

01:44:03.234 --> 01:44:04.667
She's not good.

01:44:04.701 --> 01:44:09.634
But no, we don't ultimately
know what her next move is.

01:44:09.667 --> 01:44:13.501
MARISHA: I can try to scry on her
and maybe get lucky

01:44:13.534 --> 01:44:16.901
or I can try and
scry on Whitestone.

01:44:16.934 --> 01:44:19.033
The problem is
is she's smart,

01:44:19.067 --> 01:44:20.434
so even if I try
and scry on her,

01:44:20.467 --> 01:44:22.767
there's a possibility
that she'll resist it.

01:44:22.801 --> 01:44:26.667
TALIESIN: She's exhausted still,
I would assume.

01:44:26.701 --> 01:44:28.714
MARISHA: She did burn all of her
legendary resistance,

01:44:28.714 --> 01:44:30.534
-didn't she?
-MATT: She did.

01:44:30.567 --> 01:44:33.033
TALIESIN: And she's
probably been running.

01:44:33.067 --> 01:44:34.267
LIAM: What could it hurt?

01:44:34.300 --> 01:44:36.334
MARISHA: I'm gonna try
and scry on Raishan.

01:44:36.367 --> 01:44:37.968
MATT: Okay, casting the spell?

01:44:38.000 --> 01:44:39.267
MARISHA: Scrying eye.

01:44:39.300 --> 01:44:41.501
MATT: Scrying eye, okay the reason,
the item's DC,

01:44:41.534 --> 01:44:42.767
not your spell DC.

01:44:42.801 --> 01:44:44.567
MARISHA: I guess so, but I
don't know if you ever put

01:44:44.601 --> 01:44:50.801
the scrying eye DC on here,
it doesn't have a DC.

01:44:50.834 --> 01:44:54.367
MATT: It doesn't--then, uh, then
we'll use your spell DC,

01:44:54.400 --> 01:44:57.000
that's fine, okay, so.

01:44:57.033 --> 01:44:59.501
So as you guys
begin situating,

01:44:59.534 --> 01:45:02.901
Kima walks up at the surface.

01:45:02.934 --> 01:45:05.234
Gilmore's still kind
of rummaging through

01:45:05.267 --> 01:45:06.667
and trying to find some
interesting things.

01:45:06.701 --> 01:45:09.400
And there's a few moments when
you hear Gilmore across from you

01:45:09.434 --> 01:45:13.601
like, "Hah, hah,
this is mine."

01:45:13.634 --> 01:45:16.100
Starting to find things left
over from his destroyed shop

01:45:16.133 --> 01:45:17.367
that have been
scavenged by looters

01:45:17.400 --> 01:45:20.367
and brought back to
Thordak as, you know,

01:45:20.400 --> 01:45:23.501
paying homage to
their new ruler.

01:45:23.534 --> 01:45:25.300
Um, Kima begins to head up

01:45:25.334 --> 01:45:28.701
and you can hear now people
have begun to gather en masse

01:45:28.734 --> 01:45:30.767
into the Cloudtop
it sounds like other--

01:45:30.801 --> 01:45:33.801
the rest of your soldiers
along with Zahra and Kashaw

01:45:33.834 --> 01:45:36.270
are walking up with her
and begin to organize

01:45:36.270 --> 01:45:39.033
and find whoever's been
fighting through the city

01:45:39.067 --> 01:45:43.467
and figuring out how to set up a
perimeter to defend the center

01:45:43.501 --> 01:45:45.923
which essentially the entire
economy of the city

01:45:45.923 --> 01:45:48.467
lies underground.

01:45:48.501 --> 01:45:50.367
You begin to pull
out the scrying eye

01:45:50.400 --> 01:45:53.534
and set up the small
space for the ritual.

01:45:53.567 --> 01:45:56.367
You concentrate on it and
kind of thrust your vision

01:45:56.400 --> 01:45:59.934
towards the center
of the artifact.

01:45:59.968 --> 01:46:01.701
What's the spell DC?

01:46:01.734 --> 01:46:03.801
MARISHA: My spell save DC is 20.

01:46:10.300 --> 01:46:13.067
MATT: All right.

01:46:13.100 --> 01:46:18.901
So as you focus, you feel
your vision kind of lift up

01:46:18.934 --> 01:46:22.200
into the dark clouds
as the storm is drifting

01:46:22.234 --> 01:46:24.634
south--south east of the city

01:46:24.667 --> 01:46:29.667
towards where the wyvern
riders have been escaping.

01:46:29.701 --> 01:46:31.934
Into the clouds and the dark,
the moisture, the rain,

01:46:31.968 --> 01:46:35.133
you feel the humidity
almost oppressive against you

01:46:35.167 --> 01:46:38.567
and you feel your
essence being tugged,

01:46:38.601 --> 01:46:40.497
being pulled rapidly
in a direction.

01:46:40.497 --> 01:46:42.601
Amidst the cloud, you don't
know which direction it is,

01:46:42.634 --> 01:46:43.701
but it's pulled you quickly

01:46:43.734 --> 01:46:46.421
and suddenly you
emerge from the clouds

01:46:46.421 --> 01:46:47.767
and you're over ocean.

01:46:47.801 --> 01:46:50.567
Um, over ocean you
see in the distance

01:46:50.601 --> 01:46:54.667
just open waves,
no signs of land, just water.

01:46:54.701 --> 01:46:58.047
And then a singular island,
isolated, distant,

01:46:58.047 --> 01:46:59.200
far from everything.

01:46:59.234 --> 01:47:00.734
Your vision suddenly jumps,

01:47:00.767 --> 01:47:03.434
scats upright to the outside
of this cavern opening.

01:47:03.467 --> 01:47:07.234
You see--
skips, I meant to say.

01:47:07.267 --> 01:47:09.567
Nothing escapes Laura's mind.

01:47:09.601 --> 01:47:12.033
She is our
resident 13-year-old.

01:47:12.067 --> 01:47:13.934
-LIAM: It was me that time.
-LAURA: It was actually him.

01:47:13.968 --> 01:47:16.534
-It was him that time.
-MATT: You're twins, that's fine.

01:47:16.567 --> 01:47:17.734
LIAM: Poopy.

01:47:17.767 --> 01:47:19.067
MATT: Yes.

01:47:19.100 --> 01:47:22.467
Skips ahead to the
exterior of some sort of

01:47:22.501 --> 01:47:25.501
a mountain based cavern
that dips deep into the ground

01:47:25.534 --> 01:47:29.968
in the center of this very,
very thick jungle-like terrain.

01:47:30.000 --> 01:47:34.067
You can see portions
of the cavern here

01:47:34.100 --> 01:47:35.667
have been ruined
and broken down

01:47:35.701 --> 01:47:41.234
and there appears to be some
sort of geothermal activity

01:47:41.267 --> 01:47:42.267
in the vicinity.

01:47:42.300 --> 01:47:44.834
Your vision skips again
and you can see

01:47:44.868 --> 01:47:46.934
a deep series
of winding caverns

01:47:46.968 --> 01:47:50.501
that lead to what
looks to be like a stone--

01:47:50.534 --> 01:47:57.400
a very, very old
stone laboratory.

01:47:57.434 --> 01:47:58.467
You see cages.

01:47:58.501 --> 01:48:01.200
You see wooden furniture.

01:48:01.234 --> 01:48:05.234
You see what look to
be portions of bookshelves

01:48:05.267 --> 01:48:06.868
that are toppled over.

01:48:06.901 --> 01:48:11.544
And out of the blurry peripheral
of this one focal point

01:48:11.544 --> 01:48:13.400
where the spell
has taken you,

01:48:13.434 --> 01:48:16.701
you can see what looks
to be just out of sight,

01:48:16.734 --> 01:48:21.767
a large deep red crimson mass
that is just resting still.

01:48:23.501 --> 01:48:27.267
You also see what appear to be
to your other peripheral,

01:48:27.300 --> 01:48:33.801
two ovoid-like red shapes that
are kind of resting in the edge.

01:48:33.834 --> 01:48:37.701
And there at one
of the bookshelves

01:48:37.734 --> 01:48:42.400
you see a woman
with long dark green hair.

01:48:42.434 --> 01:48:45.400
Um, wounded and bleeding.

01:48:45.434 --> 01:48:49.367
Currently pulling books out
of the shelf and opening them

01:48:49.400 --> 01:48:52.868
and looking through and slamming
it closed and throwing it down

01:48:52.901 --> 01:48:55.534
and pulling another
book and going through.

01:48:55.567 --> 01:49:03.033
♪

01:49:03.067 --> 01:49:05.534
The vision recedes and your eyes
blink and come back to you

01:49:05.567 --> 01:49:07.634
and you're back
in the cavern of the lair.

01:49:07.667 --> 01:49:09.267
MARISHA: She's not in Whitestone.

01:49:09.300 --> 01:49:11.567
SAM: She was looking for the
third book of the trilogy

01:49:11.601 --> 01:49:13.133
of Patrick Rothfuss--

01:49:13.167 --> 01:49:18.033
(laughing)

01:49:21.734 --> 01:49:25.033
It couldn't be
found anywhere!

01:49:25.067 --> 01:49:28.968
Why can't I find
this fucking book?

01:49:29.000 --> 01:49:32.667
(laughing)

01:49:35.767 --> 01:49:37.684
MATT: And with that
we'll take our break.

01:49:37.684 --> 01:49:39.200
(cheering)

01:49:39.234 --> 01:49:40.567
That's your break, we'll--

01:49:40.601 --> 01:49:42.601
(laughing)

01:49:46.230 --> 01:49:48.200
Alright, we'll be back
here in a few minutes,

01:49:48.234 --> 01:49:49.601
take a restroom break
and a snack break,

01:49:49.634 --> 01:49:51.267
we'll see you
guys here shortly.

01:49:51.300 --> 01:49:52.400
Stay tuned.

01:49:52.434 --> 01:49:54.167
(laughing)

01:50:54.367 --> 01:58:20.801
♪

01:59:50.968 --> 02:03:36.934
♪

02:06:41.434 --> 02:06:44.167
Welcome back, ladies and
gentlemen, to Critical Role.

02:06:44.200 --> 02:06:47.200
(laughing)

02:06:49.767 --> 02:06:52.467
Well done, Liam, well done.

02:06:52.501 --> 02:06:56.100
(indistinct remarks)

02:06:56.133 --> 02:06:58.434
So welcome back.

02:06:58.467 --> 02:07:02.501
Jumping back into our adventure.

02:07:02.534 --> 02:07:06.067
(laughing)

02:07:06.100 --> 02:07:09.267
So as the armies
begin to filter in,

02:07:09.300 --> 02:07:13.234
word begins to spread
throughout the city that

02:07:13.267 --> 02:07:17.100
every Fire Giant that
stood beneath Thordak

02:07:17.133 --> 02:07:20.534
in the city has been slain.

02:07:20.567 --> 02:07:24.400
A multitude of the lizardfolk
that were under Thordak

02:07:24.434 --> 02:07:27.300
and the Conclaves barrier
have also been slain

02:07:27.334 --> 02:07:30.300
or have fled the city.

02:07:30.334 --> 02:07:33.434
The storm of the Ashari
has wandered and dissipated

02:07:33.467 --> 02:07:36.801
as the immediate threat
of the wyvern riding horde

02:07:36.834 --> 02:07:40.868
has fled towards the Stormcrest
Mountains to the Southeast,

02:07:40.901 --> 02:07:43.467
and are now out of sight.

02:07:43.501 --> 02:07:46.000
The armies have converged

02:07:46.033 --> 02:07:48.567
and have begun
searching for survivors

02:07:48.601 --> 02:07:51.467
and putting them
under their care.

02:07:51.501 --> 02:07:53.534
Members of the Clasp
have begun to rise up

02:07:53.567 --> 02:07:57.367
and meet with the
remaining armies

02:07:57.400 --> 02:08:00.701
in discussions of how to bring
most of the survivors out

02:08:00.734 --> 02:08:03.501
as the Clasp has actually been--
as they discussed before--

02:08:03.534 --> 02:08:06.300
taking many of the survivors
that aren't already bound

02:08:06.334 --> 02:08:10.000
to Thordak and keeping
them underground,

02:08:10.033 --> 02:08:13.234
and kind of building small
underground tent cities

02:08:13.267 --> 02:08:16.033
for them to live in while they
try and figure out what to do.

02:08:16.067 --> 02:08:18.167
It's very interesting
with those of you

02:08:18.200 --> 02:08:20.000
who've lived in Emon
for enough time

02:08:20.033 --> 02:08:22.300
to see so many different people

02:08:22.334 --> 02:08:23.868
and so many different
racial backgrounds,

02:08:23.901 --> 02:08:27.067
and so many different
cultural decrees

02:08:27.100 --> 02:08:31.133
all coming to one point
and all working together

02:08:31.167 --> 02:08:34.133
so quickly and so strongly
just for the sake

02:08:34.167 --> 02:08:38.634
of recovery, for aid and
there is an air of relief.

02:08:38.667 --> 02:08:41.234
Some people are gathering
the dead and identifying them,

02:08:41.267 --> 02:08:43.934
bringing them out into portions
of the streets to make sure

02:08:43.968 --> 02:08:47.167
that they are properly buried

02:08:47.200 --> 02:08:50.213
and the families are
given notification.

02:08:50.213 --> 02:08:52.734
You can see a lot of the
fires are being put out

02:08:52.767 --> 02:08:54.874
and people are doing the
best they can to salvage

02:08:54.874 --> 02:08:57.133
as much of the city
that still stands.

02:08:57.167 --> 02:08:59.334
And a lot of the city
still stands untouched.

02:08:59.367 --> 02:09:01.434
I'd say a good third
of it is gonna need

02:09:01.467 --> 02:09:04.501
some serious reconstruction
and rebuilding.

02:09:04.534 --> 02:09:07.248
And being one of the largest--
if not the largest city

02:09:07.248 --> 02:09:10.501
on the continent, it's
gonna take some time.

02:09:10.534 --> 02:09:12.234
You guys have begun

02:09:12.267 --> 02:09:16.801
to speak with the Warmaster

02:09:16.834 --> 02:09:19.033
as he approaches with his army,

02:09:19.067 --> 02:09:22.501
and kind of trade stories

02:09:22.534 --> 02:09:25.767
on what has transpired
on their end and yours.

02:09:25.801 --> 02:09:28.267
And as this is happening,

02:09:28.300 --> 02:09:32.133
a familiar face steps
into the district

02:09:32.167 --> 02:09:36.000
with a small group
of cloaked figures.

02:09:36.033 --> 02:09:37.701
LAURA: Oh shit.

02:09:37.734 --> 02:09:41.033
MATT: Standing before you,
you see a tall,

02:09:41.067 --> 02:09:44.234
scaled female Dragonborn,

02:09:44.267 --> 02:09:46.601
tailless, armored,

02:09:46.634 --> 02:09:48.667
Tofor Brotorus,

02:09:48.701 --> 02:09:51.033
looking harried and exhausted.

02:09:51.067 --> 02:09:53.534
She steps up and you
see what looks to be

02:09:53.567 --> 02:09:56.901
the cusp of a toothy grin

02:09:56.934 --> 02:09:59.801
at the edge of her mouth as
she catches your attention,

02:09:59.834 --> 02:10:03.167
raises one hand.

02:10:03.200 --> 02:10:06.100
"You have no idea how happy I am

02:10:06.133 --> 02:10:10.033
to see that you all live.

02:10:10.067 --> 02:10:13.567
So, if I'm to be told,
you are the ones

02:10:13.601 --> 02:10:16.534
that took down the Cinder King?"

02:10:16.567 --> 02:10:18.501
-TRAVIS: Yeah.
-TALIESIN: Yes.

02:10:18.534 --> 02:10:23.100
MARISHA: Us and with the aid of
many others, of course.

02:10:23.133 --> 02:10:26.694
MATT: "Then this is indeed
the turning point.

02:10:26.694 --> 02:10:29.667
Do you have access to any
of the members of the council?

02:10:29.701 --> 02:10:31.868
We've been cut off in
the Lyceum for months."

02:10:31.901 --> 02:10:33.767
-TRAVIS: Aye.
-LAURA: Yes.

02:10:33.801 --> 02:10:36.801
MARISHA: Allura is safe is
Whitestone currently.

02:10:36.834 --> 02:10:38.868
We can say Whitestone now right?

02:10:38.901 --> 02:10:40.801
-TALIESIN: We can say Whitestone now, yes.
-MARISHA: Okay.

02:10:40.834 --> 02:10:44.567
-She's safe in Whitestone.
-TRAVIS: Whitestone.

02:10:44.601 --> 02:10:47.367
-Sorry, are we not saying it?
-MARISHA: Whitestone, yeah.

02:10:47.400 --> 02:10:48.667
It's kinda nice saying it again.

02:10:48.701 --> 02:10:50.701
LAURA: Emperor Uriel's
wife and children

02:10:50.734 --> 02:10:52.701
are in Whitestone as well.

02:10:52.734 --> 02:10:55.424
MATT: "This is good to know,
I was worried about them

02:10:55.424 --> 02:10:57.701
after the initial attack.

02:10:57.734 --> 02:11:00.334
Okay, all right."

02:11:00.367 --> 02:11:03.901
MARISHA: Asum should still be
here as well, right?

02:11:03.934 --> 02:11:06.033
-TALIESIN: Back in Whitestone as well.
-MARISHA: Also back in Whitestone?

02:11:06.067 --> 02:11:08.133
SAM: Mhm, Whitestone.
I think--wait,

02:11:08.167 --> 02:11:10.901
Raishan was supposed
to take Asum somewhere.

02:11:10.934 --> 02:11:13.400
Did we ever--
did that ever happen?

02:11:13.434 --> 02:11:15.868
TRAVIS: I thought Asum came
down to the Ziggurat.

02:11:15.901 --> 02:11:18.634
-MARISHA: Yeah.
-SAM: Yeah, yeah, yeah.

02:11:18.667 --> 02:11:21.200
MARISHA: Raishan brought Asum back to us.

02:11:21.234 --> 02:11:25.367
-LAURA: Yeah, that.
-LIAM: Sound of confidence.

02:11:25.400 --> 02:11:28.100
-TALIESIN: It was like a month ago.
-MATT: "Very well.

02:11:28.133 --> 02:11:31.167
With Warmaster's aid, and
any of you who are able to,

02:11:31.200 --> 02:11:33.467
we'll begin to do
the best we can

02:11:33.501 --> 02:11:35.434
to restructure some semblance

02:11:35.467 --> 02:11:37.434
of law and order
here within the city."

02:11:37.467 --> 02:11:40.000
MARISHA: And Kima's in there,
she's kind of guarding

02:11:40.033 --> 02:11:43.601
the treasury, if you will.

02:11:43.634 --> 02:11:46.634
-SAM: Solo.
-MARISHA: Solo, by herself.

02:11:46.667 --> 02:11:49.400
LIAM: We were hoping to peel
off some of the troops,

02:11:49.434 --> 02:11:51.601
maybe some of Syngorn's
troops to help

02:11:51.634 --> 02:11:54.200
keep an eye on things in there.

02:11:54.234 --> 02:11:57.634
MATT: "Well, master, could
you make that happen?"

02:11:57.667 --> 02:12:01.434
You see Mikael Daxio
who is currently

02:12:01.467 --> 02:12:03.467
in the midst of giving orders
to a few of his soldiers

02:12:03.501 --> 02:12:05.367
kind of puts his hand
up and walks over.

02:12:05.400 --> 02:12:08.434
"I'm sorry, what?"

02:12:08.467 --> 02:12:10.501
"Mikael, if you would be able

02:12:10.534 --> 02:12:13.567
to offer some aid or
strength of your troops

02:12:13.601 --> 02:12:16.601
to guard what remains

02:12:16.634 --> 02:12:19.834
of the city's economy."

02:12:19.868 --> 02:12:21.734
And Mikael nods.

02:12:21.767 --> 02:12:22.801
"Should not be a worry.

02:12:22.834 --> 02:12:24.434
Of course, I'll uh--"

02:12:24.467 --> 02:12:26.167
and he begins to
talk with Tofor,

02:12:26.200 --> 02:12:27.701
and they begin to break
down and structure

02:12:27.734 --> 02:12:29.033
how people are gonna
go here and there.

02:12:29.067 --> 02:12:31.667
So the longer this progresses,
the more it gets

02:12:31.701 --> 02:12:33.907
into more logistical
conversations.

02:12:33.907 --> 02:12:35.601
What do you guys wanna do?

02:12:35.634 --> 02:12:39.657
MARISHA: I fill them in on
what I saw in scrying.

02:12:39.657 --> 02:12:42.300
More importantly, what
this means is that she

02:12:42.334 --> 02:12:44.234
is on this plane of existence.

02:12:44.267 --> 02:12:48.734
I can't scry if she's on
another plane, so she's here.

02:12:48.767 --> 02:12:51.767
LIAM: Do you know where
that island is?

02:12:51.801 --> 02:12:54.000
♪

02:12:54.033 --> 02:12:56.634
MARISHA: I could attempt to think

02:12:56.667 --> 02:12:59.667
really hard about it.

02:12:59.701 --> 02:13:00.767
I could attempt to think.

02:13:00.767 --> 02:13:03.540
SAM: The Marisha Ray Story.

02:13:03.540 --> 02:13:05.334
LIAM: Scrying doesn't
give any direction.

02:13:05.334 --> 02:13:07.434
MATT: I mean even the
visuals I'm giving

02:13:07.467 --> 02:13:10.000
from a narrative standpoint
are like a little more

02:13:10.033 --> 02:13:11.868
than the spell should,
but it's for fun.

02:13:11.901 --> 02:13:15.000
MARISHA: Can I do like a--can
I do a roll to see--

02:13:15.033 --> 02:13:18.467
-MATT: Make an intelligence check.
-MARISHA: Oh, geez.

02:13:18.501 --> 02:13:21.434
Thanks for your vote
of confidence, Sam.

02:13:21.467 --> 02:13:23.434
That's not good,
that's not good.

02:13:23.467 --> 02:13:25.133
-SAM: For the dice.
-MARISHA: This is your fault.

02:13:25.167 --> 02:13:27.667
-It's a five total.
-SAM: Yeah, it is.

02:13:27.701 --> 02:13:30.501
MARISHA: Wait, wait, wait, no, just a
straight intelligence check?

02:13:30.534 --> 02:13:33.634
-MATT: Yup, intelligence modifier.
-MARISHA: Yeah, it's five.

02:13:33.667 --> 02:13:36.801
MATT: Yeah, you've--you,
for lack of a better term,

02:13:36.834 --> 02:13:39.267
are the homeschooled
one of the bunch,

02:13:39.300 --> 02:13:42.868
and you only recently left the--

02:13:42.901 --> 02:13:47.100
well, before meeting the
rest of these adventurers,

02:13:47.133 --> 02:13:49.167
you know, left Zephra to go

02:13:49.200 --> 02:13:50.501
and see what the
world was about.

02:13:50.534 --> 02:13:53.000
So, unfortunately, you don't
have as much worldly experience

02:13:53.033 --> 02:13:54.767
as other people
on your team would.

02:13:54.801 --> 02:13:57.767
So the visuals you
have clear in your mind,

02:13:57.801 --> 02:14:02.434
you have no personal life
experience or any place

02:14:02.467 --> 02:14:05.033
that you've seen that you
can connect the dots to.

02:14:05.067 --> 02:14:07.033
MARISHA: I turned to Pike and asked--

02:14:07.067 --> 02:14:09.667
and tell her of the island,

02:14:09.701 --> 02:14:12.467
and ask if she has
encountered anything

02:14:12.501 --> 02:14:16.400
like this in her travels.

02:14:16.434 --> 02:14:19.667
MATT: She closes her eyes for a second
and kinda winces a little bit,

02:14:19.701 --> 02:14:22.701
her tongue kinda peaks outside
her mouth for a second.

02:14:22.734 --> 02:14:26.734
"Uh, no.

02:14:26.767 --> 02:14:29.133
Wide ocean, you said, right?"

02:14:29.167 --> 02:14:33.767
MARISHA: Big, nothing but ocean, except
for that one singular island.

02:14:33.801 --> 02:14:36.534
It looked like there was
geothermal activity going on,

02:14:36.567 --> 02:14:41.067
so it must be near a
volcano or something.

02:14:41.100 --> 02:14:44.100
MATT: "Most of my sailing was
done in the Ozmit Sea."

02:14:44.133 --> 02:14:45.601
MARISHA: Nothing like that?

02:14:45.634 --> 02:14:47.617
MATT: "Nothing that I've seen.

02:14:47.617 --> 02:14:49.294
Sorry."

02:14:50.267 --> 02:14:52.834
MARISHA: It's okay, Pikey.

02:14:52.868 --> 02:14:55.267
PATRICK: I'll throw a Hail Mary,
like how wide-ranging

02:14:55.300 --> 02:14:57.667
was I back in the day

02:14:57.701 --> 02:14:59.701
when I was doing
this for my career?

02:14:59.734 --> 02:15:01.801
Any of this sound
familiar to me?

02:15:01.834 --> 02:15:04.567
-MATT: Roll an intelligence check.
-LAURA: Come on!

02:15:04.601 --> 02:15:08.133
(mixed remarks)

02:15:08.167 --> 02:15:11.067
Natural 20!

02:15:11.100 --> 02:15:13.067
-PATRICK: Eighteen.
-MATT: Eighteen?

02:15:13.100 --> 02:15:15.334
Plus your intelligence modifier?

