to as a runechild.

02:28:08.434 --> 02:28:10.601
LAURA: What does that,
what does that mean?

02:28:10.634 --> 02:28:13.734
-MATT: You don't know.
-LAURA: I know, what does it mean?

02:28:13.767 --> 02:28:16.300
-MATT: Go and make a history check.
-LAURA: Okay.

02:28:16.334 --> 02:28:18.400
♪

02:28:18.434 --> 02:28:20.601
-Oh no, I don't know.
-TRAVIS: You don't know shit.

02:28:20.634 --> 02:28:22.667
-You know less than me.
-TALIESIN: What's a child?

02:28:22.701 --> 02:28:25.400
(laughing)

02:28:25.434 --> 02:28:29.100
MATT: Who are you, who am I?

02:28:29.133 --> 02:28:32.801
TRAVIS: I've got a new weapon
down in the, in the lair.

02:28:32.834 --> 02:28:35.000
Can you identify this?

02:28:35.033 --> 02:28:37.767
-MATT: "I can."
-TRAVIS: Just take a look at it.

02:28:37.801 --> 02:28:42.267
MATT: "I've got a few low level spells
still available, certainly.

02:28:42.300 --> 02:28:45.100
Oh, this is quite
a fancy endeavor."

02:28:45.133 --> 02:28:46.767
TRAVIS: It's really pretty.

02:28:46.801 --> 02:28:49.000
MATT: "Oh, it's not just pretty,
it'll perform for you.

02:28:49.033 --> 02:28:51.200
This, my friend,
is a dancing sword."

02:28:51.234 --> 02:28:53.367
SAM: A dancing sword?

02:28:53.400 --> 02:28:55.601
-MARISHA: How does it work?
-LAURA: How do you make it work?

02:28:55.634 --> 02:28:58.067
TRAVIS: I throw it on the ground.

02:28:58.100 --> 02:29:00.067
SAM: I start playing a ditty.

02:29:00.100 --> 02:29:02.367
(imitating instrument playing)

02:29:02.400 --> 02:29:05.467
-MATT: Okay, what'd you do, Grog?
-TRAVIS: I threw it on the ground.

02:29:05.501 --> 02:29:08.701
I throw it on the ground!

02:29:08.734 --> 02:29:11.997
I don't need your dancing!

02:29:13.300 --> 02:29:16.534
MATT: My weapon's not a sword!

02:29:16.567 --> 02:29:18.667
TRAVIS: Duh!

02:29:18.701 --> 02:29:22.234
(laughing)

02:29:22.267 --> 02:29:26.400
MATT: I'm not part of
your feudal system!

02:29:26.434 --> 02:29:29.400
All right, so you throw
the sword on the ground.

02:29:29.434 --> 02:29:31.167
-TRAVIS: Yeah.
-MATT: Okay.

02:29:31.200 --> 02:29:33.221
-TRAVIS: It's gonna kill me.
-LIAM: Clang-a-lang-a-lang.

02:29:33.221 --> 02:29:36.567
-TRAVIS: Clang-a-lang-a-lang.
-MATT: Here we go.

02:29:36.601 --> 02:29:39.367
(humming)

02:29:39.400 --> 02:29:42.267
The sword goes clang-clang.

02:29:42.300 --> 02:29:45.400
The music's playing,
sword just stays there.

02:29:45.434 --> 02:29:47.267
LAURA: I don't think that's
how it works, Grog.

02:29:47.300 --> 02:29:49.701
SAM: ♪ Dancing sword ♪

02:29:49.734 --> 02:29:51.834
♪ Feel the-- ♪♪

02:29:51.868 --> 02:29:54.534
TRAVIS: I feel moved by Scanlan's
tunes, and I go over

02:29:54.567 --> 02:29:57.834
and I pick up the sword and...

02:29:57.868 --> 02:30:00.601
(singing gibberish)

02:30:00.634 --> 02:30:02.767
SAM: Maybe it has to lead, Grog.

02:30:02.801 --> 02:30:05.334
(crosstalk)

02:30:05.367 --> 02:30:08.834
(laughing)

02:30:08.868 --> 02:30:14.667
SAM: ♪ I know this much is true ♪♪

02:30:14.701 --> 02:30:17.968
MATT: As Grog slowly rotates,
caressing the back

02:30:18.000 --> 02:30:21.934
of this ornate scimitar,
the music emanating

02:30:21.968 --> 02:30:26.334
from Scanlan's fantastic shaum.

02:30:26.367 --> 02:30:29.334
A number of nearby military
begin to slowly turn

02:30:29.367 --> 02:30:33.300
and just kind of cock
their heads and watch

02:30:33.334 --> 02:30:35.334
as an unexpected
display presents itself

02:30:35.367 --> 02:30:37.467
amongst the Cloudtop ruins.

02:30:37.501 --> 02:30:40.534
♪

02:30:40.567 --> 02:30:42.634
TRAVIS: Perverts.

02:30:42.667 --> 02:30:44.234
MATT: Gilmore leans in,

02:30:44.267 --> 02:30:47.367
"You might wanna spend
some time with it first.

02:30:47.400 --> 02:30:48.968
I don't think it
trusts you yet."

02:30:49.000 --> 02:30:52.534
-SAM: Take it to dinner.
-TRAVIS: Yeah, but it's very sharp.

02:30:52.567 --> 02:30:54.601
LAURA: Sit down and
compliment it a lot.

02:30:54.634 --> 02:30:57.534
LIAM: I think you have to hang out in
the shitter with it for a while.

02:30:57.567 --> 02:31:00.667
TRAVIS: Oh right, shitter, compliments,
take it to dinner.

02:31:00.701 --> 02:31:02.934
MARISHA: Conjure some wine in your jug.

02:31:02.968 --> 02:31:05.300
-LAURA: Oh, good call.
-TRAVIS: For it or for me?

02:31:05.334 --> 02:31:06.801
-LAURA: Both, both.
-TRAVIS: Okay.

02:31:06.834 --> 02:31:08.734
MATT: "Once it likes you it'll
tell you a magic word.

02:31:08.767 --> 02:31:11.067
Use the word and that
sword fights on its own."

02:31:11.100 --> 02:31:13.634
-SAM: On its own?
-TRAVIS: Really?

02:31:13.667 --> 02:31:15.934
-TALIESIN: Like a Warner Brothers cartoon.
-LAURA: So you can fight--

02:31:15.968 --> 02:31:18.587
it can fight and he can
fight with another thing?

02:31:18.587 --> 02:31:20.234
(gasping and laughing)

02:31:20.267 --> 02:31:22.334
-You should give it to Scanlan.
-TRAVIS: What?

02:31:22.367 --> 02:31:25.367
LAURA: I'm sorry.

02:31:25.400 --> 02:31:28.717
TRAVIS: She forgets herself
sometimes, it's all right.

02:31:29.501 --> 02:31:30.968
Thank you, Gilmore.

02:31:31.000 --> 02:31:32.934
MATT: "Of course, anything
else you need?"

02:31:32.968 --> 02:31:35.100
MARISHA: Back to the runechild thing.

02:31:35.133 --> 02:31:37.033
-MATT: "Yes?"
-MARISHA: What's that about?

02:31:37.067 --> 02:31:39.234
LIAM: What's a runechild, Shaun?

02:31:39.267 --> 02:31:41.717
LAURA: You don't have to tell us if
you don't want to, but please.

02:31:41.717 --> 02:31:43.400
MATT: "Well, I just--

02:31:43.434 --> 02:31:46.300
it's, um,

02:31:46.334 --> 02:31:50.734
it's a natural thing that
some people are born with.

02:31:50.767 --> 02:31:53.634
It's a gift, it's, um--"

02:31:53.667 --> 02:31:56.067
MARISHA: Like scoliosis?

02:31:56.100 --> 02:31:59.133
-MATT: "Adjacent."
-LIAM: That means I had it.

02:31:59.167 --> 02:32:02.000
MATT: "But no, it's--there
aren't many of us,

02:32:02.033 --> 02:32:06.200
and let's just say,
in times past, we were--

02:32:06.234 --> 02:32:10.167
runechildren
were sought after.

02:32:10.200 --> 02:32:14.033
Not always by the
best of intentions.

02:32:14.067 --> 02:32:16.501
So I'd like to keep
this information--"

02:32:16.534 --> 02:32:19.133
-MARISHA: Sure.
-LAURA: Of course.

02:32:19.167 --> 02:32:22.834
LIAM: Was that a problem even in Emon
or just where you hail from?

02:32:22.868 --> 02:32:24.968
TALIESIN: Another threat we need to
deal with at some point.

02:32:25.000 --> 02:32:27.601
MATT: "It pervaded the
entire Age of Arcanum,

02:32:27.634 --> 02:32:31.834
but, um, it's not that it's--

02:32:31.868 --> 02:32:35.367
it's just not well
understood, and, uh,

02:32:35.400 --> 02:32:38.801
um, just please."

02:32:38.834 --> 02:32:41.334
TRAVIS: Your word is safe with
us because I don't know

02:32:41.367 --> 02:32:43.167
what you're talking about.

02:32:43.200 --> 02:32:44.734
MATT: "That's why I like you, Grog.

02:32:44.767 --> 02:32:48.434
The details go nowhere."

02:32:48.467 --> 02:32:51.200
MARISHA: Gilmore, in your time
in growing up on Marquet,

02:32:51.234 --> 02:32:55.133
did you ever hear any tale
of someone named Opesh?

02:32:55.167 --> 02:32:58.033
-LAURA: Opash.
-MATT: "Opash?"

02:32:58.067 --> 02:33:00.467
-MARISHA: He's a necromancer.
-LAURA: Terrible necromancer.

02:33:00.501 --> 02:33:03.434
-MATT: "Hmm."
-TRAVIS: Don't tell him.

02:33:03.467 --> 02:33:06.167
MATT: "Can't say I have, I'm sorry.

02:33:06.200 --> 02:33:08.901
I wasn't really a
history buff, sorry."

02:33:08.934 --> 02:33:10.767
LAURA: Damn, I bet J'Mon
would've known.

02:33:10.801 --> 02:33:12.400
TALIESIN: We have to go back anyway.

02:33:12.434 --> 02:33:15.434
-LAURA: We have a hand to deliver.
-TALIESIN: We do, we have many things.

02:33:15.467 --> 02:33:18.884
If anything else, the next order
of business is to make a list.

02:33:18.884 --> 02:33:21.067
SAM: That's what I'm doing right now.

02:33:21.100 --> 02:33:23.531
TALIESIN: I'm not actually
going to build a list,

02:33:23.531 --> 02:33:25.367
we're just gonna make--

02:33:25.400 --> 02:33:29.300
MARISHA: How much longer do you think
Raishan will stay there?

02:33:29.334 --> 02:33:31.734
Especially if she's not finding
what she's looking for.

02:33:31.767 --> 02:33:34.033
-TRAVIS: Not long.
-TALIESIN: I think it'll be a base

02:33:34.067 --> 02:33:35.667
of operations, that's
what I would do.

02:33:35.701 --> 02:33:37.534
If I thought that I was
going to be safe somewhere,

02:33:37.567 --> 02:33:40.300
I would stay there
and simply hunt out,

02:33:40.334 --> 02:33:43.000
much as we did with Whitestone.

02:33:43.033 --> 02:33:44.634
Safe until it's not.

02:33:44.667 --> 02:33:47.801
LAURA: Do you think she knew
you were scrying on her?

02:33:47.834 --> 02:33:49.840
MARISHA: She didn't seem to notice.

02:33:49.840 --> 02:33:51.367
A lot of times
you can kinda tell.

02:33:51.400 --> 02:33:55.200
-LAURA: Yeah.
-MARISHA: She seemed distracted.

02:33:55.234 --> 02:33:58.067
-TALIESIN: She's been beaten pretty badly.
-MARISHA: Yeah.

02:33:58.100 --> 02:34:02.234
LAURA: We should get to Whitestone.

02:34:02.267 --> 02:34:04.734
SAM: Is here taken care of?

02:34:04.767 --> 02:34:07.868
And do we need to stop
in on our home, our keep,

02:34:07.901 --> 02:34:10.234
and do anything there
before we leave?

02:34:10.267 --> 02:34:13.133
LIAM: I mean, can--aren't
we all tapped out?

02:34:13.167 --> 02:34:15.534
Can you get us
to Whitestone now?

02:34:15.567 --> 02:34:17.767
LAURA: Maybe we spend the
night in the keep

02:34:17.801 --> 02:34:19.868
-for old time's sake.
-SAM: For old time's sake.

02:34:19.901 --> 02:34:23.467
-TRAVIS: The old hangout!
-MARISHA: I could get us to--

02:34:23.501 --> 02:34:27.400
back to Whitestone using
my last seventh level spell,

02:34:27.434 --> 02:34:31.100
and then that's it,
I'm done, done, done.

02:34:31.133 --> 02:34:33.767
-TALIESIN: We could go home.
-SAM: You couldn't get all of us,

02:34:33.801 --> 02:34:36.734
-right, I mean--
-MARISHA: No, transport via plants.

02:34:36.767 --> 02:34:40.000
SAM: But like Jarrett,
and Kima, and Gilmore--

02:34:40.033 --> 02:34:42.267
-MARISHA: It lasts six seconds.
-MATT: "If we all go quickly, yeah."

02:34:42.300 --> 02:34:44.767
-LIAM: We could get in a line.
-MARISHA: I think my record was like

02:34:44.801 --> 02:34:47.334
25 people when we were
moving refugees through.

02:34:47.367 --> 02:34:50.834
Yeah, it was pretty good,
still trying to break that.

02:34:50.868 --> 02:34:54.033
MATT: "I would recommend not
really trying to break it."

02:34:54.067 --> 02:34:55.767
PATRICK: We don't wanna
get 25 and a half.

02:34:55.801 --> 02:34:57.868
(laughing)

02:34:57.901 --> 02:35:00.234
MATT: "You've seen it
happen, I can tell."

02:35:00.267 --> 02:35:03.033
(mixed remarks)

02:35:03.067 --> 02:35:06.334
"Well, I'm glad I'm alive,
I'm glad you're all alive."

02:35:06.367 --> 02:35:08.734
-LAURA: Thank you for helping.
-LIAM: Thank you, Shaun.

02:35:08.767 --> 02:35:11.367
MATT: "It's the least I could do,
and if anything, it's really--

02:35:11.400 --> 02:35:14.868
this experience has helped me
come to terms with the fact

02:35:14.901 --> 02:35:18.767
that I should not be
on the battlefield.

02:35:18.801 --> 02:35:21.434
I need to stay in
the shop, and I--"

02:35:21.467 --> 02:35:24.167
TRAVIS: That is not true, that finger
of yours is very powerful.

02:35:24.200 --> 02:35:26.934
MATT: "Yes, and I was
also on fire a lot.

02:35:26.968 --> 02:35:28.634
-I want to avoid that."
-TRAVIS: That's true.

02:35:28.667 --> 02:35:30.734
TALIESIN: Are you gonna be
rebuilding your shop here

02:35:30.767 --> 02:35:33.234
or are we gonna see you
in Whitestone as well?

02:35:33.267 --> 02:35:35.334
MATT: "You know, my intent
a while back

02:35:35.367 --> 02:35:39.067
was to start a franchise.

02:35:39.100 --> 02:35:41.667
We'll see how the winds carry
me, after all, I think--"

02:35:41.701 --> 02:35:44.234
And he kinda tugs open this
large heavy sack and satchel

02:35:44.267 --> 02:35:47.033
that's on his side now,
and to the other side you see

02:35:47.067 --> 02:35:51.467
a small compact bag of
holding, and he goes,

02:35:51.501 --> 02:35:53.467
"I think I've got
it taken care of."

02:35:53.501 --> 02:35:56.534
(laughing)

02:35:56.567 --> 02:35:57.868
-LAURA: Nice.
-TRAVIS: Brilliant.

02:35:57.901 --> 02:36:00.367
We wish you well, Gilmore.

02:36:00.400 --> 02:36:01.801
MATT: "Well, I mean, if you're
going to Whitestone,

02:36:01.834 --> 02:36:04.534
-I'm coming with you."
-TRAVIS: No, you gotta stay.

02:36:04.567 --> 02:36:06.200
I'm just kidding, you can come.

02:36:06.234 --> 02:36:08.734
(laughing)

02:36:08.767 --> 02:36:11.868
LAURA: Ker, are you gonna come
to Whitestone with us?

02:36:11.901 --> 02:36:15.167
♪

02:36:15.200 --> 02:36:17.300
LIAM: Stay the night and
have a drink with us.

02:36:17.334 --> 02:36:19.868
-SAM: Are we going now?
-LAURA: We can bounce you back.

02:36:19.901 --> 02:36:23.767
SAM: We're not even gonna go to
our keep for a little bit.

02:36:23.801 --> 02:36:25.901
-Did we go there?
-TALIESIN: We did, we came in.

02:36:25.934 --> 02:36:28.267
-Stopped by the ruins.
-SAM: All right.

02:36:28.300 --> 02:36:31.267
TRAVIS: Heyo, heyo, Ker, heyo.

02:36:31.300 --> 02:36:33.634
PATRICK: I could use a drink,
I would love to.

02:36:33.667 --> 02:36:36.501
I would love to,
give me just a moment,

02:36:36.534 --> 02:36:39.267
and I head back to the troops

02:36:39.300 --> 02:36:42.467
and I talk to, like,
the couple of them

02:36:42.501 --> 02:36:45.167
that have kind
of like risen up--

02:36:45.200 --> 02:36:47.133
-LAURA: Samantha.
-PATRICK: Samantha, yeah,

02:36:47.167 --> 02:36:49.133
like fucking runs the
whole thing right now.

02:36:49.167 --> 02:36:51.934
-LIAM: Sam's pretty legit.
-PATRICK: Yeah.

02:36:51.968 --> 02:36:54.968
And so--and I also

02:36:55.000 --> 02:36:58.567
kind of circumspectly--

02:36:58.601 --> 02:37:03.133
I sort of distribute
a little bit of money.

02:37:03.167 --> 02:37:06.067
I give Samantha some,
and this is like--

02:37:06.100 --> 02:37:08.033
it's like if something happens,

02:37:08.067 --> 02:37:12.400
if I don't come back,
here's how long you stay,

02:37:12.434 --> 02:37:15.534
here's what to do
among the populous.

02:37:15.567 --> 02:37:19.534
Like--and I don't need to
give them the talk of like,

02:37:19.567 --> 02:37:22.434
No looting, 'cause they've
already had Daddy Ker

02:37:22.467 --> 02:37:24.977
like constantly lecturing them
about how to not be dicks.

02:37:24.977 --> 02:37:27.267
MATT: The kind of people that would
follow you into battle for this,

02:37:27.300 --> 02:37:29.400
as small as your group was,
the kind of people that you know

02:37:29.434 --> 02:37:31.200
you can trust this, and
Samantha with her like,

02:37:31.234 --> 02:37:33.634
kind of, you know, graying
hair that's pulled into

02:37:33.667 --> 02:37:36.200
this kind of hard topknot
on top, and her darker skin

02:37:36.234 --> 02:37:39.734
with the scar across her cheek,
and her breastplate of armor,

02:37:39.767 --> 02:37:41.634
she comes up and kind of
grabs your hand and goes,

02:37:41.667 --> 02:37:43.701
"Don't worry, I've got it
taken care of, it's fine."

02:37:43.734 --> 02:37:46.133
PATRICK: Right, yeah, it's right,
you've done it before.

02:37:46.167 --> 02:37:49.000
MATT: "We've gathered the dead, we'll
make sure with what you've given

02:37:49.033 --> 02:37:51.734
that we'll get it back to
the families that remain."

02:37:51.767 --> 02:37:55.067
PATRICK: Right, this is gonna be

02:37:55.100 --> 02:37:58.567
a tricky place for
a couple of weeks,

02:37:58.601 --> 02:38:02.000
and not only could our
people maybe use a rest,

02:38:02.033 --> 02:38:05.667
but maybe it would benefit from

02:38:05.701 --> 02:38:09.434
30 or 40 level-handed
people with swords

02:38:09.467 --> 02:38:12.200
maybe keeping an eye out,

02:38:12.234 --> 02:38:14.167
maybe traveling in
pairs around the city

02:38:14.200 --> 02:38:17.100
making sure nobody's
houses get broken into.

02:38:17.133 --> 02:38:19.400
Just--you can't take
care of everything,

02:38:19.434 --> 02:38:22.567
but it would not be bad to
camp out maybe for a week.

02:38:22.601 --> 02:38:24.868
Wait for me, and I'll be back,

02:38:24.901 --> 02:38:26.868
and if I'm not,
you know where to go.

02:38:26.901 --> 02:38:31.000
MATT: "Hey, I'm always down to
rough up some ruffians."

02:38:31.033 --> 02:38:34.817
PATRICK: It's--yeah, okay.

02:38:34.817 --> 02:38:37.367
-MATT: "Ker, go with your friends."
-PATRICK: Okay.

02:38:37.400 --> 02:38:40.033
TRAVIS: Is Samantha attractive?

02:38:40.067 --> 02:38:43.100
LAURA: Should we--just ignore.

02:38:43.133 --> 02:38:46.901
She has that breastplate.

02:38:46.934 --> 02:38:50.000
MATT: Yeah, I mean, she
looks like she could

02:38:50.033 --> 02:38:52.801
definitely bruise you in
the face with a left hook.

02:38:52.834 --> 02:38:54.801
So, for you, yeah.

02:38:54.834 --> 02:38:56.367
TRAVIS: Awesome, hey, Ker, Ker.

02:38:56.400 --> 02:38:59.534
-PATRICK: Hm?
-TRAVIS: Put in a good word.

02:38:59.567 --> 02:39:02.801
PATRICK: I--she--I...

02:39:02.834 --> 02:39:06.334
(laughing)

02:39:06.367 --> 02:39:08.267
TRAVIS: Hey.

02:39:08.300 --> 02:39:11.434
♪

02:39:11.467 --> 02:39:13.100
MATT: "He's going with you, right?"

02:39:13.133 --> 02:39:16.234
-PATRICK: Yeah.
-MATT: "Great, okay."

02:39:16.267 --> 02:39:18.033
LAURA: Does Kima wanna come with us?

02:39:18.067 --> 02:39:20.267
MATT: Yeah, Kima's ready
to go, she's like,

02:39:20.300 --> 02:39:22.701
"All right, we're going
back to Whitestone?"

02:39:22.734 --> 02:39:24.133
LAURA: Does everything look
like it's in order

02:39:24.167 --> 02:39:25.901
with Daxio, with everyone here?

02:39:25.934 --> 02:39:27.300
-MATT: "Sure."
-LAURA: Are we good to leave?

02:39:27.334 --> 02:39:30.334
MATT: "I don't do the
whole council thing,

02:39:30.367 --> 02:39:34.501
but they assure me it's fine,
Allie's gonna know what to do.

02:39:34.534 --> 02:39:38.167
I just--this is
really depressing me."

02:39:40.133 --> 02:39:44.133
LAURA: I look at Daxio, is everything
okay, can we cut out--

02:39:44.167 --> 02:39:45.701
MATT: He's in the middle
of a conversation.

02:39:45.734 --> 02:39:48.000
"Yes, yes, we've got it covered.

02:39:48.033 --> 02:39:49.667
Let Allura know
as soon as she can,

02:39:49.701 --> 02:39:53.067
come to us, we have
a lot to discuss."

02:39:53.100 --> 02:39:55.501
-LAURA: Will do.
-MATT: "Everyone, thank you."

02:39:55.534 --> 02:39:56.934
-LAURA: Thank you.
-MATT: "And from me,

02:39:56.968 --> 02:40:00.300
from all the civilians
of the city,

02:40:00.334 --> 02:40:03.567
from Tal'Dorei proper,

02:40:03.601 --> 02:40:06.200
we all owe you a great
debt of gratitude."

02:40:06.234 --> 02:40:08.400
LAURA: Thank you for having our back.

02:40:08.434 --> 02:40:10.734
MATT: "Thank you for having ours.

02:40:10.767 --> 02:40:13.067
Now, off with you, you
know where to find us."

02:40:13.100 --> 02:40:15.197
LIAM: Kima, come on, let's
get you back to Allie.

02:40:15.197 --> 02:40:18.400
-MARISHA: We gotta find a tree.
-SAM: Might I just--

02:40:18.434 --> 02:40:20.601
-TALIESIN: We have a tree at the keep.
-MARISHA: We do have a tree at the keep

02:40:20.634 --> 02:40:22.000
if we wanted to make
a stop at the keep.

02:40:22.033 --> 02:40:25.133
SAM: So we are now
stiffing The Clasp.

02:40:25.167 --> 02:40:26.400
-LAURA: No.
-TALIESIN: No.

02:40:26.434 --> 02:40:28.501
LAURA: By the way, Daxio...

02:40:28.534 --> 02:40:31.000
(laughing)

02:40:31.033 --> 02:40:33.067
I'm sure you're aware, but--

02:40:33.100 --> 02:40:35.667
and we'll let Allura
know as well--The Clasp

02:40:35.701 --> 02:40:39.367
was instrumental in keeping
survivors alive here in Emon.

02:40:39.400 --> 02:40:43.367
-They definitely deserve a bit of the pot.
-TALIESIN: Compensation.

02:40:43.400 --> 02:40:46.901
-SAM: Handsome reward.
-MATT: "We'll discuss with them.

02:40:46.934 --> 02:40:50.300
I do believe that we've already
had a few conversations

02:40:50.334 --> 02:40:53.701
with a few operatives during
our arrival within the city,

02:40:53.734 --> 02:40:56.567
and they've been
very forthcoming

02:40:56.601 --> 02:41:01.200
with information,
and willing to aid us.

02:41:01.234 --> 02:41:05.701
So, yes, I appreciate
the acknowledgement."

02:41:05.734 --> 02:41:08.501
LAURA: We wouldn't have made
it here without them.

02:41:08.534 --> 02:41:12.534
SAM: Please let them know
that we vouched for them.

02:41:12.567 --> 02:41:16.033
LIAM: They've at least earned
the old status quo.

02:41:16.067 --> 02:41:17.434
-TRAVIS: What is that?
-MATT: "Very well."

02:41:17.467 --> 02:41:20.000
LAURA: I have no idea.

02:41:20.033 --> 02:41:22.400
PATRICK: And just to mention,

02:41:22.434 --> 02:41:25.334
if you take people like that

02:41:25.367 --> 02:41:29.534
and give them, in a place

02:41:29.567 --> 02:41:32.968
in your town,

02:41:33.000 --> 02:41:36.567
you can keep an eye on them.

02:41:36.601 --> 02:41:40.067
MATT: He eyes kinda narrow a little
bit, he nods towards you.

02:41:40.100 --> 02:41:43.234
"Indeed.

02:41:43.267 --> 02:41:46.133
Well, I'll take it from here.

02:41:46.167 --> 02:41:48.934
Return when you can.

02:41:48.968 --> 02:41:50.801
Get Allura back to us,

02:41:50.834 --> 02:41:54.267
and stay safe."

02:41:54.300 --> 02:41:58.367
And he turns back to
handle some more business.

02:41:58.400 --> 02:41:59.901
What do you guys wanna do?

02:41:59.934 --> 02:42:02.801
-TRAVIS: Make for Greyskull Keep--
-LAURA: Where our giant tree is

02:42:02.834 --> 02:42:05.267
so we can go to
our other giant tree.

02:42:05.300 --> 02:42:08.033
-MATT: Okay.
-MARISHA: What they said.

02:42:08.067 --> 02:42:10.763
MATT: You guys make your
way walking southward

02:42:10.763 --> 02:42:13.000
through Emon, and--

02:42:13.033 --> 02:42:15.734
LAURA: Just loot everything
along the way, like--

02:42:15.767 --> 02:42:18.801
-MARISHA: Just like decking children.
-LAURA: Every person you see.

02:42:18.834 --> 02:42:22.501
(crosstalk)

02:42:22.534 --> 02:42:26.634
LIAM: Matt starts rolling
random encounters.

02:42:26.667 --> 02:42:29.200
MATT: Six episodes just
getting out of Emon.

02:42:29.234 --> 02:42:31.367
(laughing)

02:42:31.400 --> 02:42:34.300
TRAVIS: Why the hell did we walk?

02:42:34.334 --> 02:42:37.133
MATT: You guys make your way
through, and as you do,

02:42:37.167 --> 02:42:40.133
it's, it's an emotional journey,

02:42:40.167 --> 02:42:43.734
because as you walk through
the city that became your home

02:42:43.767 --> 02:42:46.968
as you all became a family,

02:42:47.000 --> 02:42:48.767
you can see familiar sights,

02:42:48.801 --> 02:42:53.067
you can see familiar
thoroughfares,

02:42:53.100 --> 02:42:57.167
and streetsides, and taverns,

02:42:57.200 --> 02:42:59.400
many of which have
sustained severe damage,

02:42:59.434 --> 02:43:03.067
many that have been reduced
to nothing but rubble and ash.

02:43:03.100 --> 02:43:04.968
And some that still
stand defiantly

02:43:05.000 --> 02:43:08.267
versus all the
difficulty, and stress,

02:43:08.300 --> 02:43:12.601
and strenuous struggle
that has existed

02:43:12.634 --> 02:43:15.601
for weeks and weeks
and weeks here.

02:43:15.634 --> 02:43:17.767
You see people slowly
emerging from the shadows

02:43:17.801 --> 02:43:20.501
to try and reclaim what
remains of their life,

02:43:20.534 --> 02:43:22.133
but you also see them
helping each other.

02:43:22.167 --> 02:43:26.234
You also see a comparison

02:43:26.267 --> 02:43:29.000
between the busy bustle

02:43:29.033 --> 02:43:31.334
and kind of general
selfish lifestyle

02:43:31.367 --> 02:43:34.734
that most people in a well-off
capital city exist in

02:43:34.767 --> 02:43:37.767
replaced with a newly
understood sense of kinship

02:43:37.801 --> 02:43:40.133
and looking out for each other.

02:43:40.167 --> 02:43:43.067
You see the guards
themselves beginning

02:43:43.100 --> 02:43:47.334
to really understand,

02:43:47.367 --> 02:43:49.467
in their lifetime,
the first true,

02:43:49.501 --> 02:43:51.968
large-scale victory
for the betterment

02:43:52.000 --> 02:43:54.167
of their people and
what that means to them.

02:43:54.200 --> 02:43:58.300
And there's kinda
a sense of pride

02:43:58.334 --> 02:44:00.734
through the sadness that
many of the armed soldiers

02:44:00.767 --> 02:44:03.400
you've come across
probably never had.

02:44:03.434 --> 02:44:06.334
♪

02:44:06.367 --> 02:44:08.334
It gives you hope,

02:44:08.367 --> 02:44:10.434
though to see it in
such a state in itself

02:44:10.467 --> 02:44:14.567
is harrowing in its own right.

02:44:14.601 --> 02:44:16.801
You can already begin to
see through this energy

02:44:16.834 --> 02:44:20.167
and through the
slow crawling return

02:44:20.200 --> 02:44:24.133
to life that you've
helped ensure

02:44:24.167 --> 02:44:27.267
that Emon still has a future,

02:44:27.300 --> 02:44:30.018
let alone Tal'Dorei itself.

02:44:30.018 --> 02:44:32.834
No one catches your
attention as you leave,

02:44:32.868 --> 02:44:36.667
but a number of eyes train
onto you as you exit.

02:44:36.701 --> 02:44:39.501
And many of them flash
with recognition,

02:44:39.534 --> 02:44:42.534
their face going bright,

02:44:42.567 --> 02:44:46.667
and then with just a solemn nod

02:44:46.701 --> 02:44:49.801
of, "Thank you."

02:44:49.834 --> 02:44:52.767
Eventually you find yourself
to the southern gates of Emon

02:44:52.801 --> 02:44:57.000
exiting out into the charred
fields that once were green

02:44:57.033 --> 02:45:01.601
and lush with grain and grass.

02:45:01.634 --> 02:45:04.667
Eventually coming upon the
exterior of Greyskull Keep,

02:45:04.701 --> 02:45:07.167
the home of Vox Machina.

02:45:07.200 --> 02:45:11.000
Just as you left it, abandoned,
the front gate partially ajar.

02:45:11.033 --> 02:45:12.934
There stands the keep.

02:45:12.968 --> 02:45:15.100
Mighty, defiant,

02:45:15.133 --> 02:45:18.367
and somewhere there is a jar
of no-longer-magical poop.

02:45:18.400 --> 02:45:21.267
(laughing)

02:45:21.300 --> 02:45:23.634
Making your way inside, there
is the garden that you left

02:45:23.667 --> 02:45:25.801
within the Temple to Sarenrae

02:45:25.834 --> 02:45:27.801
and the large central
tree that you use

02:45:27.834 --> 02:45:30.734
for most of your transport
to and from, Keyleth.

02:45:30.767 --> 02:45:34.467
-MARISHA: How's the garden look?
-MATT: Looks as good as you left it.

02:45:34.501 --> 02:45:36.467
It was far enough from
the battle to where

02:45:36.501 --> 02:45:38.901
it didn't seem to suffer
any sort of blows or issues.

02:45:38.934 --> 02:45:41.200
You guys managed to basically
focus everything within

02:45:41.234 --> 02:45:44.834
the city's walls, so,
good on you for that.

02:45:47.734 --> 02:45:50.234
MARISHA: Okay, anybody need anything?

02:45:50.267 --> 02:45:52.133
SAM: Not gonna go through the--

02:45:52.167 --> 02:45:54.467
need anything from
your rooms or anything?

02:45:54.501 --> 02:45:57.267
-LAURA: We'll be back here.
-SAM: Change of underwear?

02:45:57.300 --> 02:46:00.968
-TRAVIS: What's that?
-LAURA: It's all at Whitestone.

02:46:01.000 --> 02:46:03.033
We have everyone with us.

02:46:03.067 --> 02:46:05.133
Jarrett, Kash, Zahra.

02:46:05.167 --> 02:46:07.901
MATT: They've all kinda
walked along with you.

02:46:07.934 --> 02:46:09.734
LIAM: I'm just gonna
pluck another flower

02:46:09.767 --> 02:46:12.033
and tuck it behind my ear.

02:46:12.067 --> 02:46:15.200
MATT: Okay.

02:46:15.234 --> 02:46:17.534
As Keyleth steps forward
and places her hands

02:46:17.567 --> 02:46:19.868
across the base of
the tree, she focuses

02:46:19.901 --> 02:46:23.601
and it's almost like
grasping two ends of a bag

02:46:23.634 --> 02:46:26.534
and then pulling it open
with alternating zippers.

02:46:26.567 --> 02:46:30.033
You watch the bark split,
and as it opens up

02:46:30.067 --> 02:46:33.434
and crawls from floor
to the seven-foot apex,

02:46:33.467 --> 02:46:36.234
a doorway is opened temporarily,
and on the other side

02:46:36.267 --> 02:46:39.734
you immediately see the,

02:46:39.767 --> 02:46:43.400
the slow morning sun
beginning to rise

02:46:43.434 --> 02:46:47.033
in Whitestone across the city.

02:46:47.067 --> 02:46:50.834
-SAM: Jump in.
-MARISHA: Six seconds, go, go, go!

02:46:50.868 --> 02:46:52.667
MATT: You all go charging through
as fast as you can,

02:46:52.701 --> 02:46:54.601
all emerging into the center

02:46:54.634 --> 02:46:57.968
of Whitestone's central area,

02:46:58.000 --> 02:47:01.801
the twilight being slowly
cast away by the rising sun.

02:47:01.834 --> 02:47:05.501
The Sun Tree at your back as
the doorway closes behind you,

02:47:05.534 --> 02:47:09.000
and the cold air

02:47:09.033 --> 02:47:10.501
immediately catches your lungs.

02:47:10.534 --> 02:47:14.267
You've been amongst
the heat and the clouds

02:47:14.300 --> 02:47:18.434
of smoke and soot
of Emon for so long

02:47:18.467 --> 02:47:22.133
amongst the struggle,
the cold crisp air is almost

02:47:22.167 --> 02:47:25.968
a welcome moment of respite
from that experience.

02:47:26.000 --> 02:47:28.033
You look around you and
the little bits of grass

02:47:28.067 --> 02:47:31.968
have broken the cobblestone
and floor of the open area,

02:47:32.000 --> 02:47:35.868
have bits of frozen dew
across their surface,

02:47:35.901 --> 02:47:39.000
and it's this beautiful
crystal moment

02:47:39.033 --> 02:47:42.901
of peace that you didn't realize

02:47:42.934 --> 02:47:46.267
you've been seeking
for quite some time.

02:47:46.300 --> 02:47:48.801
You can see the gentle bit
of light beginning to crest

02:47:48.834 --> 02:47:51.701
over the mountains, hitting
Castle Whitestone ahead of you.

02:47:51.734 --> 02:47:54.033
You've returned.

02:47:54.067 --> 02:47:55.634
What do you wanna do?

02:47:55.667 --> 02:47:57.734
LAURA: Well, I thought it would a
be a nightcap, but it seems

02:47:57.767 --> 02:48:00.601
like it's a morning cap instead.

02:48:00.634 --> 02:48:03.467
-LIAM: That's our specialty.
-TALIESIN: It's night somewhere.

02:48:03.501 --> 02:48:06.300
LIAM: That is our specialty.

02:48:06.334 --> 02:48:08.200
LAURA: Head to the castle,
have a drink,

02:48:08.234 --> 02:48:11.400
-tell Allura what's going on.
-MARISHA: Should find Allura.

02:48:11.434 --> 02:48:13.634
And Cassandra.

02:48:13.667 --> 02:48:16.200
TALIESIN: Yes, let's head to the castle.

02:48:16.234 --> 02:48:19.334
♪

02:48:19.367 --> 02:48:20.767
-LAURA: Hey, Ker.
-PATRICK: Hm?

02:48:20.801 --> 02:48:22.267
LAURA: Wanna see where we live?

02:48:22.300 --> 02:48:25.367
PATRICK: I will admit to a
passing curiosity.

02:48:25.400 --> 02:48:27.701
TALIESIN: Let's give him a tour.

02:48:27.734 --> 02:48:30.801
LIAM: This place was full
of fucking vampires.

02:48:30.834 --> 02:48:33.734
They were everywhere,
they were giants.

02:48:33.767 --> 02:48:36.267
It was terrible,
we've renovated, yeah.

02:48:36.300 --> 02:48:39.868
SAM: We led a rebellion and I was
the general, it was amazing.

02:48:39.901 --> 02:48:43.267
-TALIESIN: We let him say that.
-LAURA: He was a dinosaur.

02:48:43.300 --> 02:48:45.267
LIAM: Any beret you see one
someone's head right now

02:48:45.300 --> 02:48:47.601
is because of this
man right here.

02:48:47.634 --> 02:48:50.467
LAURA: Oh, and that flat part
of land, that's mine.

02:48:50.501 --> 02:48:53.067
(laughing)

02:48:53.100 --> 02:48:54.868
TRAVIS: I thought they said
that was the wastelands.

02:48:54.901 --> 02:48:56.033
LAURA: No, it's mine.

02:48:56.067 --> 02:48:57.267
TRAVIS: Isn't that where
they bury all the shit?

02:48:57.300 --> 02:48:58.901
-SAM: Yup.
-TRAVIS: Yup.

02:48:58.934 --> 02:49:01.968
(laughing)

02:49:02.000 --> 02:49:05.033
♪

02:49:05.067 --> 02:49:07.834
MATT: As you guys walk your way up

02:49:07.868 --> 02:49:10.367
the path to Castle Whitestone,

02:49:10.400 --> 02:49:13.567
the Pale Guard morning shift

02:49:13.601 --> 02:49:15.767
has already begun to
walk across the grounds.

02:49:15.801 --> 02:49:18.133
They greet you, you're
let into the castle,

02:49:18.167 --> 02:49:21.200
and from your perspective,
this hillside,

02:49:21.234 --> 02:49:24.601
this small mountain that
marks the northern side

02:49:24.634 --> 02:49:27.901
of Whitestone, the city that
sits in the central valley

02:49:27.934 --> 02:49:32.133
surrounded by the
thick Parchwood Forest,

02:49:32.167 --> 02:49:34.434
you see this beautiful castle.

02:49:34.467 --> 02:49:38.234
Not too large, but enough
to have once housed

02:49:38.267 --> 02:49:42.334
a very respectable royal family,

02:49:42.367 --> 02:49:46.667
if you will, of at least
lord and lady blood.

02:49:46.701 --> 02:49:49.690
Made of a dull pale gray.

02:49:49.690 --> 02:49:52.167
You've never been to Whitestone,
you've heard about it,

02:49:52.200 --> 02:49:54.300
and you immediately assume that,
Well, this is what they call it

02:49:54.334 --> 02:49:57.067
'cause the castle itself
has a little bit of white.

02:49:57.100 --> 02:50:00.667
Entering inside, it's
slowly beginning to rouse.

02:50:00.701 --> 02:50:03.100
You sense some energy
with the sunrise.

02:50:03.133 --> 02:50:05.434
People begin to make breakfast

02:50:05.467 --> 02:50:08.234
and guards begin to walk past.

02:50:08.267 --> 02:50:10.767
Eventually, with you guys
taking a moment to kind of rest

02:50:10.801 --> 02:50:13.000
and even grab a
little bit of food,

02:50:13.033 --> 02:50:15.267
as early as it is,
Cassandra enters.

02:50:15.300 --> 02:50:18.234
You watch as a woman in her--
what you can only imagine

02:50:18.267 --> 02:50:22.133
to be late teens,
early twenties physically,

02:50:22.167 --> 02:50:26.734
but her eyes carry
the wisdom that only

02:50:26.767 --> 02:50:31.267
years of trauma
and survival can hold.

02:50:31.300 --> 02:50:33.667
Her dark brunette hair with
a single shock of white

02:50:33.701 --> 02:50:35.400
that kind of curls to the back.

02:50:35.434 --> 02:50:39.267
Walks in, consciousness--

02:50:39.300 --> 02:50:41.467
as much as you could
expect from a girl

02:50:41.501 --> 02:50:44.601
that early in the morning.

02:50:44.634 --> 02:50:47.767
Has her hands kinda
clasped at her chest.

02:50:47.801 --> 02:50:52.300
"Well, um, back
so soon, are we?"

02:50:52.334 --> 02:50:55.067
MARISHA: Is it soon?

02:50:55.100 --> 02:50:58.300
It feels like we've been--
at least two weeks.

02:50:58.334 --> 02:51:00.434
(sighing)

02:51:00.467 --> 02:51:03.968
(laughing)

02:51:04.000 --> 02:51:06.234
LIAM: More like five.

02:51:06.267 --> 02:51:08.300
MARISHA: That's true.

02:51:08.334 --> 02:51:09.934
Like a holiday break happened.

02:51:09.968 --> 02:51:12.667
LAURA: Thordak is dead.

02:51:12.701 --> 02:51:14.934
MATT: "Then it is done,
I'm proud of you all."

02:51:14.968 --> 02:51:18.033
-LAURA: It's not done.
-LIAM: It's not done.

02:51:18.067 --> 02:51:21.501
TALIESIN: But it's a victory.

02:51:21.534 --> 02:51:25.367
-We've had a good day.
-MARISHA: We're not dead.

02:51:25.400 --> 02:51:28.501
MATT: "I can see that,
and I'm quite thankful.

02:51:28.534 --> 02:51:31.934
Um, your friend, I don't
believe I've had the honor."

02:51:31.968 --> 02:51:35.868
-MARISHA: Oh yeah, this is Ker.
-PATRICK: Am I still like--

02:51:35.901 --> 02:51:39.501
do I look like Brian Blessed
who's just been through,

02:51:39.534 --> 02:51:42.567
like, a bloody fucking massacre?

02:51:42.601 --> 02:51:44.901
-Am I still like--
-MATT: All of you do.

02:51:44.934 --> 02:51:48.801
All of you right now
are just wrecked.

02:51:48.834 --> 02:51:52.400
-PATRICK: Okay.
-MATT: Like still,

02:51:52.434 --> 02:51:54.801
still shiny from
like oils and sweat.

02:51:54.834 --> 02:51:59.033
There's still like
smeared ash and--

02:51:59.067 --> 02:52:03.067
PATRICK: It's probably not until
right then where I'm like,

02:52:03.100 --> 02:52:06.300
I am, I am a fucking mess.

02:52:06.334 --> 02:52:10.501
I'm like up to
elbows bloody, yeah.

02:52:10.534 --> 02:52:13.601
-TALIESIN: You fit right in here.
-PATRICK: Yeah, okay.

02:52:13.634 --> 02:52:15.701
MATT: "I've not had the pleasure."

02:52:15.734 --> 02:52:17.601
PATRICK: Ker, it's a pleasure
to meet you.

02:52:17.634 --> 02:52:19.868
LAURA: How did you know we
were here, Cassandra?

02:52:19.901 --> 02:52:23.868
MATT: "The guards went
and summoned me.

02:52:23.901 --> 02:52:26.200
To be perfectly honest,
I don't usually rouse

02:52:26.234 --> 02:52:30.000
so early in the morning,
but this is good news.

02:52:30.033 --> 02:52:31.934
And to be perfectly honest,
the last few times

02:52:31.968 --> 02:52:33.467
the guards have summoned
me with your arrival,

02:52:33.501 --> 02:52:35.868
they've been with
a bit of a scare.

02:52:35.901 --> 02:52:39.300
So, um, it's an absolute
pleasure to make

02:52:39.334 --> 02:52:42.467
your acquaintance, Ker,
you are welcome here.

02:52:42.501 --> 02:52:45.801
Any friends of my friends
are a friend of mine."

02:52:45.834 --> 02:52:49.100
LAURA: Can we roll an insight check
to see if it's really her?

02:52:49.133 --> 02:52:50.601
-LIAM: Sure.
-MATT: Sure, roll an insight check.

02:52:50.634 --> 02:52:53.667
-LAURA: I don't trust anybody now.
-TRAVIS: Me too, it was my idea.

02:52:53.701 --> 02:52:57.133
LIAM: You've burned us too
many times, Matt.

02:52:57.167 --> 02:53:00.968
-LAURA: Twenty-five.
-LIAM: She's a beholder.

02:53:01.000 --> 02:53:02.767
TRAVIS: Four.

02:53:02.801 --> 02:53:06.167
(laughing)

02:53:06.200 --> 02:53:08.200
-LAURA: This is just a ruse.
-SAM: Secrets!

02:53:08.234 --> 02:53:11.734
LAURA: It's not gonna be Raishan.

02:53:11.767 --> 02:53:14.767
(laughing)

02:53:19.734 --> 02:53:22.234
Go team.

02:53:22.267 --> 02:53:25.267
MATT: Suddenly suffers how much psychic damage?

02:53:29.567 --> 02:53:32.033
-SAM: Vex.
-LAURA: Huh?

02:53:32.067 --> 02:53:34.734
Do you think this would be my
reaction if it was Raishan?

02:53:34.767 --> 02:53:37.367
(laughing)

02:53:37.400 --> 02:53:40.834
MATT: "Well, rest."

02:53:40.868 --> 02:53:43.634
TALIESIN: Have a bit a of drink,
we're going to rest, and then--

02:53:43.667 --> 02:53:46.934
MATT: "Well, you know where
we keep the wine."

02:53:46.968 --> 02:53:49.601
LAURA: ♪ Bloody Marys ♪

02:53:49.634 --> 02:53:52.467
♪ Mimosas ♪♪

02:53:52.501 --> 02:53:54.701
MATT: "Are we expecting more
or is it just you?"

02:53:54.734 --> 02:53:58.100
-TALIESIN: Did Vex just do that?
-SAM: It's just us for now.

02:53:58.133 --> 02:54:01.590
-I think--
-TRAVIS: It's just us, yeah.

02:54:01.590 --> 02:54:04.200
SAM: They never gave our
airship any instructions.

02:54:04.234 --> 02:54:08.234
I guess it's just
roaming the countryside.

02:54:08.267 --> 02:54:11.334
TRAVIS: It's just us this time, I know
we usually have a lot in tow--

02:54:11.367 --> 02:54:13.734
SAM: Oh, and we don't need to--
well, do we need to keep

02:54:13.767 --> 02:54:15.734
the force field up
around the city anymore?

02:54:15.767 --> 02:54:19.067
TALIESIN: No, everything's--we can
stand down at this point.

02:54:19.100 --> 02:54:21.734
It's time for everything
to rest briefly.

02:54:21.767 --> 02:54:24.834
-LAURA: We need to wake Allura.
-TALIESIN: We do need to wake Allura.

02:54:24.868 --> 02:54:27.400
MATT: "All right, I'll
have her roused.

02:54:27.434 --> 02:54:30.200
The rest of you, if you wish,
I could have baths drawn.

02:54:30.234 --> 02:54:32.968
I think you could use it."

02:54:33.000 --> 02:54:36.601
-TALIESIN: What are you trying to imply?
-MATT: "Brother."

02:54:36.634 --> 02:54:39.067
TALIESIN: I know, I know,
you owe me--I owe one.

02:54:39.100 --> 02:54:42.033
LIAM: You don't like
Dragon Age splatter?

02:54:42.067 --> 02:54:45.534
(laughing)

02:54:45.567 --> 02:54:47.434
TRAVIS: Paintbrush of gore.

02:54:47.467 --> 02:54:51.267
MATT: "I mean no disrespect,
but as a lady

02:54:51.300 --> 02:54:55.100
of esteemed blood, you
are all a terrible mess."

02:54:55.133 --> 02:54:59.701
TALIESIN: I am going to walk right up
to her, give her a big hug.

02:54:59.734 --> 02:55:02.434
MATT: "No, no, no, no!"

02:55:02.467 --> 02:55:04.964
And for a second, for
a second you see a glimmer

02:55:04.964 --> 02:55:07.767
of the young sister
that grew up with Percy

02:55:07.801 --> 02:55:10.934
fighting him off,
and she pushes him off.

02:55:10.968 --> 02:55:13.834
(laughing)

02:55:13.868 --> 02:55:16.400
"Thank you."

02:55:16.434 --> 02:55:20.667
TALIESIN: I am going to be owed for much
more than that, I'm well aware.

02:55:20.701 --> 02:55:23.234
MATT: "Yes, yes, you are.

02:55:23.267 --> 02:55:25.834
-I'm glad you're back."
-TALIESIN: It's good to be home.

02:55:25.868 --> 02:55:28.734
MATT: "All right, I'll have
Allura brought to you.

02:55:28.767 --> 02:55:31.400
Rest well, should you
require anything, I'll be

02:55:31.434 --> 02:55:35.367
in my chambers
waking properly."

02:55:35.400 --> 02:55:37.067
She leaves the room.

02:55:37.100 --> 02:55:40.267
♪

02:55:40.300 --> 02:55:43.133
Though you had--brought
little scraps of food

02:55:43.167 --> 02:55:45.300
as they were available,
a full breakfast meal

02:55:45.334 --> 02:55:49.367
is properly prepared
for you, warm food.

02:55:49.400 --> 02:55:51.667
LAURA: This is post bath
and we're clean?

02:55:51.701 --> 02:55:55.901
MATT: Yeah, you guys take time
just being cleaned properly.

02:55:55.934 --> 02:55:57.567
TALIESIN: We're spying, we're spying.

02:55:57.601 --> 02:56:00.300
MARISHA: My hair is still
singed short again.

02:56:00.334 --> 02:56:03.067
SAM: Before we part
ways with Jarrett,

02:56:03.100 --> 02:56:06.434
I'd like to pull him
aside a little bit.

02:56:06.467 --> 02:56:08.901
MATT: As you pull Jarrett aside,
you get but a few steps away

02:56:08.934 --> 02:56:10.767
and he goes, "I'm
not doing it again."

02:56:10.801 --> 02:56:13.434
SAM: I know, I know.

02:56:13.467 --> 02:56:16.567
I just wanted to thank
you for your efforts,

02:56:16.601 --> 02:56:20.167
and, you know, it really
meant a lot to me,

02:56:20.200 --> 02:56:23.734
and I'm gonna cast
an eighth level

02:56:23.767 --> 02:56:26.267
modify memory on you.

02:56:26.300 --> 02:56:29.500
(laughing)

02:56:29.500 --> 02:56:31.501
-TALIESIN: What?
-TRAVIS: I love him so much.

02:56:31.534 --> 02:56:33.857
MARISHA: You still have an
eighth level spell?

02:56:33.857 --> 02:56:36.100
(laughing)

02:56:36.133 --> 02:56:38.310
LAURA: You have an eighth
level spell left?

02:56:38.310 --> 02:56:41.767
SAM: Yeah.

02:56:41.801 --> 02:56:45.501
(crosstalk)

02:56:45.534 --> 02:56:47.033
MATT: Okay, okay.

02:56:47.067 --> 02:56:49.534
LAURA: I don't even feel
bad that he died now.

02:56:49.567 --> 02:56:52.133
MATT: Is this through the hand cone,
because that's a whole--

02:56:52.167 --> 02:56:54.400
-that's not subtle.
-SAM: No, it would not be subtle,

02:56:54.434 --> 02:56:57.267
-so I cannot do the hand cone.
-MATT: That's okay, he rolled a five.

02:56:57.300 --> 02:57:00.167
So, what are you modifying?

02:57:00.200 --> 02:57:04.701
SAM: When he delivered
the suude to me,

02:57:04.734 --> 02:57:07.734
I thanked him for it
and I went into a--

02:57:07.767 --> 02:57:10.067
I'm implanting this
memory in his head.

02:57:10.100 --> 02:57:12.501
I told him why I
needed it so badly,

02:57:12.534 --> 02:57:15.167
and it was a very sad tale

02:57:15.200 --> 02:57:18.400
of how a goblin killed my
mother and the image haunts me

02:57:18.434 --> 02:57:21.767
to this day and I can't
get through a night--

02:57:21.801 --> 02:57:25.567
I can't function without
some sort of sustenance.

02:57:25.601 --> 02:57:29.701
He felt terrible for me and
vowed to get me more, much more.

02:57:29.734 --> 02:57:31.767
(laughing)

02:57:31.801 --> 02:57:34.367
And at that time,

02:57:34.400 --> 02:57:37.434
I gave him 50 platinum.

02:57:37.467 --> 02:57:40.701
TRAVIS: Holy shit, you're
turning into a drug lord.

02:57:40.734 --> 02:57:45.067
SAM: Which he finds in his pocket
now, because I gave it to him.

02:57:45.100 --> 02:57:48.133
TALIESIN: We have met the
enemy, oh my god.

02:57:48.167 --> 02:57:50.434
-MARISHA: You're going full Heisenberg.
-SAM: And he feels for me.

02:57:50.467 --> 02:57:53.634
-TRAVIS: He is Heisenberg.
-TALIESIN: He is the one that knocks.

02:57:53.667 --> 02:57:57.067
(laughing)

02:57:57.100 --> 02:57:59.100
(crosstalk)

02:58:01.234 --> 02:58:04.133
SAM: I broke down and he's never
seen me break down like that.

02:58:04.167 --> 02:58:06.033
-MATT: No, he hasn't.
-SAM: In his mind anyway.

02:58:06.067 --> 02:58:08.534
-MATT: He hasn't, and--
-TALIESIN: Wow!

02:58:08.567 --> 02:58:11.667
-TRAVIS: Outstanding.
-TALIESIN: I can't--what?

02:58:11.701 --> 02:58:13.868
-MATT: Okay.
-SAM: That's that.

02:58:13.901 --> 02:58:16.601
MATT: All right, and at which
point you watch as his eyes

02:58:16.634 --> 02:58:19.094
kind of glaze over for a moment.

02:58:19.094 --> 02:58:22.000
He was about to make his way
towards getting his own shower.

02:58:22.033 --> 02:58:24.901
He let everybody else go first,
and he kinda stops for a second

02:58:24.934 --> 02:58:28.200
and his eyes glaze over, and
he kinda blinks for a second.

02:58:28.234 --> 02:58:31.100
"Well, I understand these
have been very trying days.

02:58:31.133 --> 02:58:34.300
If there's anything I can
do to help, let me know."

02:58:34.334 --> 02:58:36.334
SAM: You know how to help.

02:58:36.367 --> 02:58:39.334
(laughing)

02:58:39.367 --> 02:58:42.234
MATT: And you see the look in his
eyes that you've seen before,

02:58:42.267 --> 02:58:45.367
which is the, I don't do this,

02:58:45.400 --> 02:58:47.601
I barely know how to do this,

02:58:47.634 --> 02:58:50.367
and the connections I have,

02:58:50.400 --> 02:58:52.901
it's, it's gonna be hard.

02:58:52.934 --> 02:58:55.234
And you see this look, but
as opposed--where previously

02:58:55.267 --> 02:58:57.367
it was, I can't
do this anymore.

02:58:57.400 --> 02:58:59.901
He goes--he reaches up,
touches your shoulder and goes,

02:58:59.934 --> 02:59:02.133
"I'll do what I can."

02:59:02.167 --> 02:59:04.167
SAM: That's all I ask.

02:59:04.200 --> 02:59:06.367
LIAM: Yeah, Mr. Shorthalt, yeah.

02:59:06.400 --> 02:59:09.734
-TRAVIS: Meat man coming.
-MARISHA: What the fuck?

02:59:09.767 --> 02:59:12.300
SAM: Rest well, Jarrett, thank
you for your brave battle.

02:59:12.334 --> 02:59:16.000
MARISHA: Oh my god, oh my god.

02:59:16.033 --> 02:59:20.534
MATT: "Just so you know, I'm
expecting a raise, 'cause, uh,

02:59:20.567 --> 02:59:23.601
I kinda almost died like twice.

02:59:23.634 --> 02:59:25.033
It's ridiculous."

02:59:25.067 --> 02:59:26.734
SAM: You should've seen me.

02:59:26.767 --> 02:59:27.948
I did.

02:59:30.000 --> 02:59:32.067
MATT: "I'll see what I can do."

02:59:32.100 --> 02:59:34.334
Then he goes and
leaves to take a bath.

02:59:34.367 --> 02:59:36.267
LIAM: We were all taking baths, right?

02:59:36.300 --> 02:59:39.367
And they're like big royal baths
'cause this is Whitestone?

02:59:39.400 --> 02:59:42.000
MATT: Yeah, there's maybe four
at any given point in time.

02:59:42.033 --> 02:59:44.100
So you guys still have
to kinda take turns.

02:59:44.133 --> 02:59:47.934
LIAM: Excellent, I take
mine very quickly,

02:59:47.968 --> 02:59:52.167
and walk in the buck, and
I find Percival's bath,

02:59:52.200 --> 02:59:54.901
and silently walk
in while he's bathing,

02:59:54.934 --> 02:59:57.901
and I sit in the bath
on the other side,

02:59:57.934 --> 03:00:00.467
and just stare for a minute.

03:00:00.501 --> 03:00:01.968
TALIESIN: You know you're getting weirder.

03:00:02.000 --> 03:00:04.667
(laughing)

03:00:06.400 --> 03:00:08.167
LIAM: Um...

03:00:08.200 --> 03:00:10.467
♪

03:00:10.501 --> 03:00:13.033
You and I are very different.

03:00:13.067 --> 03:00:15.701
♪

03:00:15.734 --> 03:00:19.701
TALIESIN: I would agree, although,
again, I'm in a bath

03:00:19.734 --> 03:00:21.334
at the moment...

03:00:22.934 --> 03:00:24.300
Cut to it, I think,

03:00:24.334 --> 03:00:26.188
I was really
working on something.

03:00:26.188 --> 03:00:27.501
(laughing)

03:00:27.534 --> 03:00:32.400
LIAM: I didn't think you were,
uh, so meek.

03:00:32.434 --> 03:00:34.400
Umm...

03:00:34.434 --> 03:00:40.467
Anyway, I still plan
to honor your request,

03:00:40.501 --> 03:00:42.100
but, um...

03:00:43.601 --> 03:00:46.133
I want you to know...

03:00:47.601 --> 03:00:52.801
that you are like
a brother to me.

03:00:52.834 --> 03:00:54.677
♪

03:00:54.677 --> 03:00:56.968
Now I have a sister,
and we fight constantly,

03:00:57.000 --> 03:00:58.667
so I expect to do that with you.

03:00:58.701 --> 03:01:00.667
TALIESIN: I'd hope so.

03:01:00.701 --> 03:01:03.834
♪

03:01:03.868 --> 03:01:06.601
LIAM: I'm glad I have you
around still.

03:01:06.634 --> 03:01:08.868
TALIESIN: Me as well, I--

03:01:08.901 --> 03:01:11.901
I like this family,
I'd like to keep it.

03:01:11.934 --> 03:01:17.884
♪

03:01:17.884 --> 03:01:19.734
LIAM: Don't say another word.

03:01:19.767 --> 03:01:21.667
I show him my ass
and I leave.

03:01:21.701 --> 03:01:23.100
LAURA: As soon as he leaves,

03:01:23.133 --> 03:01:25.834
I come up from the water
and go, Ugh!

03:01:25.868 --> 03:01:27.701
(laughing)

03:01:27.734 --> 03:01:29.968
I thought he'd never leave!

03:01:34.167 --> 03:01:35.400
TRAVIS: Amazing!

03:01:35.434 --> 03:01:37.968
Amazing!

03:01:38.000 --> 03:01:40.854
TALIESIN: I was so hoping
you were gonna do that.

03:01:40.854 --> 03:01:43.133
MARISHA: How big are
these fucking bathtubs!

03:01:43.167 --> 03:01:45.968
-TALIESIN: They're big bathtubs!
-LIAM: That is so gross!

03:01:46.000 --> 03:01:48.167
That was like a minute long!

03:01:48.200 --> 03:01:50.501
TALIESIN: I love you,
that was wonderful.

03:01:50.534 --> 03:01:52.701
LIAM: So gross!

03:01:52.734 --> 03:01:54.934
(laughing continues)

03:01:57.267 --> 03:01:58.267
Oh, my--

03:01:58.300 --> 03:02:01.727
My opinion of you has changed!

03:02:01.727 --> 03:02:03.067
LAURA: You don't know!

03:02:03.100 --> 03:02:05.100
You don't know, you're gone!

03:02:05.133 --> 03:02:07.701
TALIESIN: She was just tickling
on the back of my knee

03:02:07.734 --> 03:02:09.434
the entire time.

03:02:09.467 --> 03:02:11.000
LIAM: I'm not talking about Vex!

03:02:11.033 --> 03:02:12.834
Vex can pork him all she wants,

03:02:12.868 --> 03:02:15.033
I don't give a fuck!

03:02:15.067 --> 03:02:18.434
That is a twisted
D&amp;amp;D choice, man!

03:02:18.467 --> 03:02:21.901
MATT: That is--that is
an amazing D&amp;amp;D choice.

03:02:21.934 --> 03:02:23.400
LIAM: That is crazier--

03:02:23.434 --> 03:02:27.100
that shit is crazier
than the broom to me, Laura.

03:02:27.133 --> 03:02:29.334
Holy shit.

03:02:29.367 --> 03:02:31.133
Boosh!

03:02:31.167 --> 03:02:34.300
-Hit me up top!
-MATT: Hey, Laura--

03:02:34.334 --> 03:02:37.133
TRAVIS: I'm working on something here,
cut to the chase.

03:02:37.167 --> 03:02:38.734
MARISHA: I'm working on something.

03:02:38.767 --> 03:02:40.200
SAM: We gotta speed this up!

03:02:40.234 --> 03:02:42.868
(laughing)

03:02:45.267 --> 03:02:48.200
MATT: In hindsight,
that changes everything.

03:02:48.234 --> 03:02:51.634
-Wow.
-LIAM: Yes, yes and!

03:02:51.667 --> 03:02:54.267
(laughing)

03:02:56.027 --> 03:02:58.033
MARISHA: Is that where those
water-breathing potions

03:02:58.067 --> 03:03:00.067
-have gone to?
-TALIESIN: Literally--

03:03:00.100 --> 03:03:03.234
we are actually
bathing in them, ironically.

03:03:03.267 --> 03:03:05.000
In the water flow.

03:03:05.033 --> 03:03:06.701
MATT: It's like The Abyss.

03:03:06.734 --> 03:03:09.067
(laughing)

03:03:09.100 --> 03:03:11.133
LIAM: Percy, what is that
really cheesy music

03:03:11.167 --> 03:03:13.667
that's playing in here?

03:03:13.701 --> 03:03:15.667
MATT: All right, so...

03:03:16.538 --> 03:03:18.334
unless you have
any more particular

03:03:18.367 --> 03:03:22.040
bath-based shenanigans
to encounter...

03:03:22.040 --> 03:03:24.234
TALIESIN: I will leave that
to peoples' imaginations.

03:03:24.267 --> 03:03:26.200
LIAM: I need a shower with lye, man!

03:03:26.234 --> 03:03:27.767
(laughing)

03:03:27.801 --> 03:03:28.934
TRAVIS: Amazing.

03:03:28.968 --> 03:03:30.634
MATT: ...and that might work better.

03:03:30.667 --> 03:03:32.734
TALIESIN: ...while that was happening.

03:03:32.767 --> 03:03:35.300
Let me remind you of that.

03:03:35.334 --> 03:03:36.334
LIAM: It looks just like us.

03:03:36.367 --> 03:03:38.868
PATRICK: I heard somebody
has alter-memory spells,

03:03:38.901 --> 03:03:41.200
if you can hit me with that.

03:03:41.234 --> 03:03:43.801
MATT: No, he only does it to people
that don't deserve it.

03:03:43.834 --> 03:03:45.534
LIAM: Oh, man!

03:03:45.567 --> 03:03:47.767
I can barely remember
those dragons right now.

03:03:49.334 --> 03:03:53.901
MATT: So, after you've all come--

03:03:53.934 --> 03:03:56.167
finished bathing, come down
to get your breakfast,

03:03:56.200 --> 03:03:57.601
and you've all kinda
gathered around the table

03:03:57.634 --> 03:04:00.701
and there's, you know, chatter,
that sort of,

03:04:00.734 --> 03:04:02.701
the release after
so many nerves built up

03:04:02.734 --> 03:04:04.734
even though there is
still things to tackle,

03:04:04.767 --> 03:04:07.868
there is a moment
of kinship and respite

03:04:07.901 --> 03:04:10.317
and, honestly, Ker,

03:04:10.317 --> 03:04:12.167
it's a little strange
for you at first.

03:04:12.200 --> 03:04:16.467
You--such jovial atmosphere

03:04:16.501 --> 03:04:19.234
in the face of such...

03:04:19.267 --> 03:04:23.634
you know, recent tragedy
and trauma

03:04:23.667 --> 03:04:26.400
reminds you of back
when you used to do this.

03:04:26.434 --> 03:04:29.334
And it's weirdly welcome.

03:04:29.367 --> 03:04:31.033
You know, it's very humanizing,

03:04:31.067 --> 03:04:35.567
and there's a brotherhood
that comes after battle

03:04:35.601 --> 03:04:38.041
that you can only describe
if you've been there.

03:04:38.041 --> 03:04:39.667
And it's been a while
since you've had

03:04:39.701 --> 03:04:41.033
this type of brotherhood.

03:04:41.067 --> 03:04:43.494
And even though you're quiet
amongst their chatter,

03:04:43.494 --> 03:04:46.033
and they are a family
that you're outside of,

03:04:46.067 --> 03:04:47.868
you can't fight the smile.

03:04:47.901 --> 03:04:50.033
PATRICK: Oh, no, it's--this is--

03:04:50.067 --> 03:04:52.667
and actually it's, you know,

03:04:52.701 --> 03:04:56.467
it's very nice to watch
like, you know--

03:04:56.501 --> 03:04:59.701
It did not stay
like this for me,

03:04:59.734 --> 03:05:02.267
and it's obviously
staying like this for them.

03:05:02.300 --> 03:05:04.534
And so, yeah, I'm very happy.

03:05:04.567 --> 03:05:08.200
And honestly,
if there is liquor here,

03:05:08.234 --> 03:05:10.734
I probably do not stay
very quiet for long.

03:05:10.767 --> 03:05:13.868
(laughing)

03:05:13.901 --> 03:05:15.033
LAURA: So much liquor.

03:05:15.067 --> 03:05:16.701
MATT: Breakfast wine!

03:05:18.834 --> 03:05:20.234
TALIESIN: One of my Brit friends--

03:05:20.267 --> 03:05:22.267
actually, were you at
that breakfast at Comic Con

03:05:22.300 --> 03:05:23.501
where we went to the pub

03:05:23.534 --> 03:05:24.968
and he said, Do you have
any breakfast beer?

03:05:25.000 --> 03:05:26.934
What do you have on
the breakfast beer menu?

03:05:26.968 --> 03:05:28.400
TRAVIS: Yeah, if Ker
is with the liquor

03:05:28.434 --> 03:05:29.901
and not being quiet,

03:05:29.934 --> 03:05:32.000
-I'm probably with him.
-MATT: All right, well,

03:05:32.033 --> 03:05:36.968
you watch as Ker comes back
with two bottles

03:05:37.000 --> 03:05:40.727
after being given directions
as to where the...

03:05:40.727 --> 03:05:41.667
(bottle pops)

03:05:41.667 --> 03:05:42.901
Just like that.

03:05:42.934 --> 03:05:45.033
(laughing)

03:05:46.968 --> 03:05:49.934
A bottle in each hand,
and each of you grab a bottle,

03:05:49.968 --> 03:05:53.467
and kinda toast
the bottle itself.

03:05:53.501 --> 03:05:55.144
You're gonna drink.

03:05:55.144 --> 03:05:56.868
Is there anything
you guys wanna discuss

03:05:56.901 --> 03:05:58.637
while you're having breakfast?

03:05:59.901 --> 03:06:01.501
TRAVIS: We're not worried
about the spinning

03:06:01.534 --> 03:06:02.801
dirt button of death, right?

03:06:02.834 --> 03:06:05.000
It's fine down there,
like it's--

03:06:05.033 --> 03:06:06.400
TALIESIN: I think it's on the list,

03:06:06.434 --> 03:06:09.634
but we have a list,
we can slow down a bit.

03:06:09.667 --> 03:06:12.934
SAM: What is our list,
'cause, I mean--

03:06:12.968 --> 03:06:15.234
so here's what
I got on my list.

03:06:15.267 --> 03:06:16.601
It's not very long.

03:06:16.634 --> 03:06:19.434
Bury a hand in Vasselheim.

03:06:19.467 --> 03:06:21.534
LAURA: No, bury ashes in Vasselheim.

03:06:21.567 --> 03:06:22.601
SAM: Oh, what was the hand?

03:06:22.634 --> 03:06:24.667
LAURA: The hand was return the hand.

03:06:24.701 --> 03:06:26.467
SAM: Oh, return the hand to Marquet.

03:06:26.501 --> 03:06:27.667
MARISHA: Marquet, yeah.

03:06:27.701 --> 03:06:32.443
-SAM: Return hand...Marquet.
-PATRICK: An actual hand.

03:06:32.443 --> 03:06:34.400
I don't need to know,
I just wanted to see

03:06:34.434 --> 03:06:38.334
-if I was doing it right.
-SAM: Bury ashes in Vasselheim.

03:06:38.367 --> 03:06:41.400
-Find Opash, go to--
-TALIESIN: Island of Opash.

03:06:41.434 --> 03:06:44.033
-SAM: Go to Wildmount.
-LAURA: Both, yes.

03:06:44.067 --> 03:06:46.434
-SAM: Is that the same thing?
-LAURA: No.

03:06:46.467 --> 03:06:49.467
SAM: Well, what--which one do we do?

03:06:49.501 --> 03:06:51.167
LAURA: Well, Vasselheim is--

03:06:51.200 --> 03:06:53.601
is Vasselheim north--
close to Wildmount?

03:06:53.634 --> 03:06:55.200
-TALIESIN:Nothing is north--
-MATT: No, opposite side.

03:06:55.234 --> 03:06:58.901
-LAURA: Oh, well, shit.
-MATT: Vasselheim's to the northwest.

03:06:58.934 --> 03:07:02.734
Wildmount is the east--
northeast of Tal'Dorei.

03:07:02.767 --> 03:07:05.467
TRAVIS: We may find more
about Opash in Wildmount.

03:07:05.501 --> 03:07:07.901
LAURA: Zahra's from Wildmount.

03:07:07.934 --> 03:07:08.934
MATT: Uhh.

03:07:08.968 --> 03:07:11.067
-TRAVIS: Is she?
-LAURA: Originally, I think.

03:07:11.100 --> 03:07:12.801
MATT: Maybe--you'd have
to check with Zahra.

03:07:12.834 --> 03:07:15.801
LAURA: I think she is--when she told me
her history, I think it was.

03:07:15.834 --> 03:07:17.033
MATT: Sure, there we go.

03:07:17.067 --> 03:07:19.400
TRAVIS: What else is on your list?

03:07:19.434 --> 03:07:21.834
-SAM: Uh--
-LAURA: Ooh, and the boys!

03:07:21.868 --> 03:07:23.734
The boys.

03:07:23.767 --> 03:07:25.200
SAM: Oh, the little boys!

03:07:25.234 --> 03:07:28.300
LAURA: Yeah, the little angel babies,
they're from Wildmount.

03:07:28.334 --> 03:07:29.834
SAM: Where are they--
where did we leave them?

03:07:29.868 --> 03:07:31.834
-LAURA: They're here.
-SAM: Oh, okay.

03:07:31.868 --> 03:07:34.000
TRAVIS: Where did we leave them?

03:07:34.033 --> 03:07:35.634
TALIESIN: On the side of the road.

03:07:35.667 --> 03:07:37.400
SAM: Any other to-do list items?

03:07:37.434 --> 03:07:39.501
TALIESIN: We have a demon.

03:07:39.534 --> 03:07:41.400
LAURA: Oh, God, we have Hotis,

03:07:41.434 --> 03:07:46.300
and the other demon that
we fought in the City of Brass.

03:07:46.334 --> 03:07:50.400
LIAM: We've got time on that--
how long has it been Hotis-wise?

03:07:50.434 --> 03:07:53.934
MATT: Hotis-wise,
it's been a few weeks.

03:07:53.968 --> 03:07:55.868
-LIAM: We've got time.
-SAM: Is there another one?

03:07:55.901 --> 03:07:57.834
-TALIESIN: No.
-LAURA: The ambassador

03:07:57.868 --> 03:08:01.267
to the Nine Hells
was in the City of Brass,

03:08:01.300 --> 03:08:04.133
and we killed him,
and he's gonna hate us.

03:08:04.167 --> 03:08:06.191
-SAM: Wait, he can come back?
-LAURA: I think so!

03:08:06.191 --> 03:08:07.834
-TRAVIS: Hotis, oh, yeah.
-SAM: Well, we can't do anything

03:08:07.868 --> 03:08:09.767
about that.

03:08:10.968 --> 03:08:13.267
MATT: Make an arcana check, Sam.

03:08:15.834 --> 03:08:19.634
SAM: Uh, more than 20--23.

03:08:19.667 --> 03:08:21.000
MATT: Twenty-three.

03:08:21.033 --> 03:08:25.868
Umm, best that you know,

03:08:25.901 --> 03:08:30.534
as far as like hierarchies
and devils in that plane,

03:08:30.567 --> 03:08:35.100
a devil as high-ranking as
the one that you guys fought

03:08:35.133 --> 03:08:37.834
that got its ass handed to it
by a bunch of random people

03:08:37.868 --> 03:08:42.200
in the City of Brass
is considered such a slight

03:08:42.234 --> 03:08:45.400
in the eyes of the hierarchy
of the Nine Hells,

03:08:45.434 --> 03:08:48.634
that devil probably
has been punished

03:08:48.667 --> 03:08:50.767
stripped of its power,

03:08:50.801 --> 03:08:55.400
and is not something you
probably need to worry about.

03:08:55.434 --> 03:08:57.801
LAURA: Oh, shit!

03:08:57.834 --> 03:09:01.033
(cross talk)

03:09:01.067 --> 03:09:02.534
Nice!

03:09:02.567 --> 03:09:04.701
TALIESIN: He does not get
to come back next week.

03:09:04.734 --> 03:09:06.801
SAM: We've done something
on our to-do list.

03:09:06.834 --> 03:09:09.000
TALIESIN: I have a bit of...

03:09:09.033 --> 03:09:11.334
I have a bit of work to do
around the house, so to speak.

03:09:11.367 --> 03:09:13.534
There's a few matters
that have to be tended to here

03:09:13.567 --> 03:09:15.834
that we should at least
get up and started, but...

03:09:15.868 --> 03:09:18.968
-MARISHA: I mean, I feel like...
-TALIESIN: ...nothing's urgent.

03:09:19.000 --> 03:09:22.367
MARISHA: I feel like the giant
green dragon in the room

03:09:22.400 --> 03:09:23.801
is pretty urgent.

03:09:23.834 --> 03:09:25.868
TALIESIN: It's the top of the list,
but it's not something

03:09:25.901 --> 03:09:27.701
that's going to be
solved tomorrow.

03:09:27.734 --> 03:09:28.901
It's not something
that's necessarily

03:09:28.934 --> 03:09:30.133
going to bite us tomorrow.

03:09:30.167 --> 03:09:32.100
I think it's going
to bite us, honestly--

03:09:32.133 --> 03:09:33.701
if we left it alone,
I think we would be

03:09:33.734 --> 03:09:36.000
reaping the damage of it
in six months.

03:09:36.033 --> 03:09:37.634
MATT: "Preferably no biting at all."

03:09:37.667 --> 03:09:39.133
As you look,
you see at the table,

03:09:39.167 --> 03:09:41.701
her hair kinda pulled up
into these small circles

03:09:41.734 --> 03:09:44.968
at the bottom of her head--
you see Allura, um,

03:09:45.000 --> 03:09:47.267
with just kinda
like a nightrobe on.

03:09:47.267 --> 03:09:49.033
LAURA: She has fun buns.

03:09:49.067 --> 03:09:51.200
MATT: She steps in...

03:09:51.234 --> 03:09:56.434
you see a woman standing
with blondish, light hair

03:09:56.467 --> 03:09:58.167
that's been braided
into long braids

03:09:58.200 --> 03:09:59.267
and then curled up into

03:09:59.300 --> 03:10:02.334
these small little balls
underneath

03:10:02.367 --> 03:10:07.033
with like a dark blue--
almost shimmering materials

03:10:07.067 --> 03:10:09.901
are her robe.

03:10:09.934 --> 03:10:12.834
She steps in a sits down
across from you guys

03:10:12.868 --> 03:10:14.234
at the other end of the table

03:10:14.267 --> 03:10:15.367
and begins taking them out

03:10:15.400 --> 03:10:18.100
and begins kind of
rebraiding them.

03:10:18.133 --> 03:10:22.400
"I'm very happy to see
that you're all safe.

03:10:22.434 --> 03:10:25.767
From what I've also been told,
that there is no need

03:10:25.801 --> 03:10:30.501
to maintain the illusory barrier
over Whitestone,

03:10:30.534 --> 03:10:34.300
which is of great relief to me

03:10:34.334 --> 03:10:38.133
as that's been draining.

03:10:38.167 --> 03:10:41.701
I have also heard
that Thordak has fallen,

03:10:41.734 --> 03:10:44.300
so congratulations
are in order."

03:10:44.334 --> 03:10:48.734
SAM: We also found you
a replacement flying carpet.

03:10:48.767 --> 03:10:52.534
(laughing)

03:10:52.567 --> 03:10:55.133
If you'd like it.

03:10:55.167 --> 03:11:00.601
LAURA: Scanlan, you're on my list.

03:11:00.634 --> 03:11:03.968
SAM: Although we could use it
in our battles to come.

03:11:04.000 --> 03:11:08.000
MATT: "I'll tell you what--
when I have my tower rebuilt,

03:11:08.033 --> 03:11:10.467
then perhaps we'll find
the right place for it

03:11:10.501 --> 03:11:12.567
where it matches the rest
of the furniture.

03:11:12.601 --> 03:11:14.033
Until then, hold onto it."

03:11:14.067 --> 03:11:16.934
SAM: It's really
a tacky color, though.

03:11:16.968 --> 03:11:18.300
-MATT: "I can change that."
-LIAM: We won't let it come

03:11:18.334 --> 03:11:20.968
anywhere near acid at all.

03:11:21.000 --> 03:11:22.934
MATT: "Please, I would
appreciate that.

03:11:22.968 --> 03:11:24.801
In fact, any of my things
that you may've stolen

03:11:24.834 --> 03:11:26.367
or taken over
the past few years,

03:11:26.400 --> 03:11:29.667
keep them away from acid
in general, thank you."

03:11:29.701 --> 03:11:32.701
LAURA: Really the rug
was the only thing.

03:11:32.734 --> 03:11:35.968
TRAVIS: I took a couple pictures
while I was in that...

03:11:38.534 --> 03:11:41.534
(whistling and laughing)

03:11:41.567 --> 03:11:42.934
MARISHA: Um...

03:11:45.667 --> 03:11:49.734
Raishan is still at large,
and we have discovered

03:11:49.767 --> 03:11:53.400
that we think she is
on the island of Opash.

03:11:53.434 --> 03:11:55.968
TALIESIN: The island that Opash
was banished to, that is.

03:11:56.000 --> 03:12:00.467
LIAM: Dude what's name was Opash had an island.

03:12:00.501 --> 03:12:02.267
LAURA: Do you know anything of him?

03:12:02.300 --> 03:12:04.701
♪

03:12:04.734 --> 03:12:06.200
MATT: She thinks for a second.

03:12:06.234 --> 03:12:09.267
TALIESIN: They will probably be
in ... we'll check.

03:12:12.400 --> 03:12:13.968
MATT: "Do you remember
the name of the island

03:12:14.000 --> 03:12:18.000
that apparently
Thordak was ruling over

03:12:18.033 --> 03:12:22.767
when he was thought
lost at sea?"

03:12:22.801 --> 03:12:24.934
-LAURA: Do you?
-SAM: Notes--there's some notes

03:12:24.968 --> 03:12:27.033
to go through.

03:12:27.067 --> 03:12:29.934
MARISHA: When did you tell us
that information?

03:12:29.968 --> 03:12:32.567
MATT: "Uh, this was information
that Raishan gave you."

03:12:32.601 --> 03:12:34.000
LAURA: Right!

03:12:34.033 --> 03:12:36.300
(cross talk)

03:12:36.334 --> 03:12:39.334
...200 years ago.

03:12:39.367 --> 03:12:40.501
TALIESIN: Just think if we had some device

03:12:40.534 --> 03:12:42.234
that would make it searchable...

03:12:42.267 --> 03:12:43.534
LAURA: Could I--would I remember this?

03:12:43.567 --> 03:12:45.801
'Cause this was
remembering information

03:12:45.834 --> 03:12:47.534
based on a dragon.

03:12:47.567 --> 03:12:48.968
MATT: I would say yes for you.

03:12:49.000 --> 03:12:50.100
LAURA: Okay.

03:12:51.934 --> 03:12:53.200
MATT: Well lawyered.

03:12:53.234 --> 03:12:55.000
(laughing)

03:12:55.033 --> 03:12:57.868
LIAM: Because you are
so de-stressed right now,

03:12:57.901 --> 03:13:01.234
-your mind is so focused.
-LAURA: It's so clear.

03:13:02.634 --> 03:13:05.601
MATT: Yes, there was something--

03:13:05.634 --> 03:13:08.501
after Thordak
was long thought dead,

03:13:08.534 --> 03:13:11.734
Thordak seemingly
reemerged after spending

03:13:11.767 --> 03:13:16.667
a few--as far as you know--

03:13:16.701 --> 03:13:18.934
years, decades,

03:13:18.968 --> 03:13:23.968
centuries, possibly,
rebuilding his domain

03:13:24.000 --> 03:13:28.200
on what was called
the island of Viscon.

03:13:28.234 --> 03:13:29.367
MARISHA: Of Viscon?

03:13:29.400 --> 03:13:33.601
MATT: Viscon in the south
of the Lucidian Ocean.

03:13:33.634 --> 03:13:35.300
MARISHA: Lucidian Ocean.

03:13:40.234 --> 03:13:42.467
MATT: And so as you say--
as it comes to your mind,

03:13:42.501 --> 03:13:44.434
you're like--You say Viscon?

03:13:44.467 --> 03:13:47.934
Allura goes, "Viscon.

03:13:47.968 --> 03:13:53.667
Now, I know this island is--
it was part of our research

03:13:53.701 --> 03:13:55.567
when Thordak first
began to attack

03:13:55.601 --> 03:13:58.601
and assail the seven regions
of Tal'Dorei

03:13:58.634 --> 03:14:02.200
back when, you know,
me and Kima were adventuring.

03:14:02.234 --> 03:14:05.534
Um...I don't know much

03:14:05.567 --> 03:14:10.767
about this Opash figure
you speak of."

03:14:10.801 --> 03:14:14.133
LAURA: Did you find a laboratory
on the island?

03:14:14.167 --> 03:14:15.300
An abandoned one?

03:14:15.334 --> 03:14:18.801
MATT: "We did not go
to the actual island,

03:14:18.834 --> 03:14:22.534
we just had to discover
that was the--

03:14:22.567 --> 03:14:26.234
the historical creep
of Thordak's domain."

03:14:26.267 --> 03:14:27.868
LAURA: Right.

03:14:27.901 --> 03:14:29.501
MATT: "It was fiercely guarded,
and at the time,

03:14:29.534 --> 03:14:31.467
our focus was more
to banish the creature

03:14:31.501 --> 03:14:33.968
as opposed to trying to walk
into the center of its home,

03:14:34.000 --> 03:14:38.033
and none of us would be alive.

03:14:38.067 --> 03:14:42.634
That would be
a place to look."

03:14:42.667 --> 03:14:44.334
LAURA: Thank you.

