There is one tomb
that you went to

03:16:36.467 --> 03:16:40.033
that was steeped
in heavy necromancy

03:16:40.067 --> 03:16:42.200
and even just
a short journey in,

03:16:42.234 --> 03:16:44.501
you lost two friends,

03:16:44.534 --> 03:16:47.667
watching the life sucked
from their corpses,

03:16:47.701 --> 03:16:54.033
left behind just these
dust-skinned skeletal memories,

03:16:54.067 --> 03:16:56.367
and you fled--you
and the remaining members

03:16:56.400 --> 03:16:58.067
of your team.

03:16:59.701 --> 03:17:02.968
Since then, you've
been keenly aware

03:17:03.000 --> 03:17:05.167
of the awful effects
of necromancy,

03:17:05.200 --> 03:17:07.601
and it honestly scares you,

03:17:07.634 --> 03:17:09.467
and so the more
this discussion continues,

03:17:09.501 --> 03:17:13.400
the more and more just uneasy
you become with the discussion.

03:17:13.434 --> 03:17:18.467
Um, as far as the essence
of what Opash may have in store,

03:17:18.501 --> 03:17:21.868
uh, you're not
particularly sure,

03:17:21.901 --> 03:17:28.000
but, um, I mean, the domain
of necromancy is life and death.

03:17:28.033 --> 03:17:32.534
Um, and that central theme

03:17:32.567 --> 03:17:35.434
keeps reemerging
with Thordak, with Raishan,

03:17:35.467 --> 03:17:36.801
with whatever this dynamic is,

03:17:36.834 --> 03:17:38.601
there's something
about life and death

03:17:38.634 --> 03:17:40.300
that is cyclical
in this conversation

03:17:40.334 --> 03:17:42.934
that keeps you connected.

03:17:42.968 --> 03:17:49.968
♪

03:17:50.000 --> 03:17:56.501
PATRICK: Was that island
that you mentioned volcamic?

03:17:56.534 --> 03:17:58.467
LAURA: The island of Viscon?

03:17:58.501 --> 03:18:00.434
PATRICK: Volcanic.

03:18:02.200 --> 03:18:05.267
MATT: You should slow down on
the breakfast wine, friend.

03:18:05.300 --> 03:18:08.901
PATRICK: Kerrek is pronouncing
very deliberately at this point.

03:18:08.934 --> 03:18:11.567
(laughing)

03:18:13.701 --> 03:18:17.567
MATT: "The island of Viscon--

03:18:17.601 --> 03:18:22.400
it would be in a zone
that does see quite a bit

03:18:22.434 --> 03:18:26.467
of activity of that kind.

03:18:26.501 --> 03:18:29.467
There are a number of places
in the ocean that are known

03:18:29.501 --> 03:18:32.467
to just perpetually spire forth

03:18:32.501 --> 03:18:36.901
sulfur and other terrible fumes."

03:18:36.934 --> 03:18:39.934
TALIESIN: I wonder if a red dragon
had been living there.

03:18:39.968 --> 03:18:41.801
MATT: "Long before he came."

03:18:41.834 --> 03:18:43.701
TALIESIN: He would've certainly
encouraged it, though.

03:18:43.734 --> 03:18:47.734
MATT: "I'm--I don't doubt that.

03:18:47.767 --> 03:18:50.434
There is something
to be said for that, so--"

03:18:50.467 --> 03:18:52.133
SAM: More Lava, Keyleth.

03:18:52.167 --> 03:18:54.000
MARISHA: My favorite.

03:18:54.033 --> 03:18:56.667
TALIESIN: One day we're going
to meet a lava door.

03:18:58.033 --> 03:19:01.501
TRAVIS: Don't you put that evil on us.

03:19:01.534 --> 03:19:03.234
Don't even put it out there.

03:19:03.267 --> 03:19:04.968
LIAM: Matt hadn't even
thought of that!

03:19:05.000 --> 03:19:06.534
TALIESIN: Three times,
you say it three times.

03:19:06.567 --> 03:19:08.634
SAM: Door made of lava.

03:19:10.834 --> 03:19:12.567
MATT: "If you do decide to inquire,

03:19:12.601 --> 03:19:16.133
this island of Viscon,

03:19:16.167 --> 03:19:20.968
carefully, slowly, methodically,

03:19:21.000 --> 03:19:22.467
whether or not this has a tie

03:19:22.501 --> 03:19:28.868
or this is specifically
where the deceiver lives

03:19:28.901 --> 03:19:31.701
at the moment, who knows
how long they'll stay.

03:19:31.734 --> 03:19:34.801
You say she's seeking
something there?"

03:19:34.834 --> 03:19:37.033
LAURA: That's what Keyleth
said it seemed like.

03:19:37.067 --> 03:19:39.334
MARISHA: She seemed to be poring
through tomes and books

03:19:39.367 --> 03:19:40.434
looking for something.

03:19:40.467 --> 03:19:43.601
She seemed very frustrated.

03:19:43.634 --> 03:19:46.868
Question--oh, go ahead.

03:19:46.901 --> 03:19:48.234
MATT: "Let's just say,
what happens if she finds

03:19:48.267 --> 03:19:49.334
what she's looking for?"

03:19:49.367 --> 03:19:51.400
MARISHA: Exactly.

03:19:51.434 --> 03:19:57.033
PATRICK: Oh, she brings the dragon
back from the dead.

03:19:57.067 --> 03:20:00.067
TALIESIN: Or transfers her consciousness
into the dragon's body,

03:20:00.100 --> 03:20:02.033
reanimates an undead red dragon.

03:20:02.067 --> 03:20:04.000
LAURA: I don't know what necromancy
is capable of.

03:20:04.033 --> 03:20:05.734
TALIESIN: ...create some unholy monster.

03:20:05.767 --> 03:20:08.200
-PATRICK: You...
-SAM: There's also dragon babies.

03:20:08.234 --> 03:20:13.267
PATRICK: ...put into the--
into the eggs...

03:20:13.300 --> 03:20:16.501
LAURA: Hey, K, you remember when
I said you were really smart?

03:20:16.534 --> 03:20:19.534
(laughing)

03:20:19.567 --> 03:20:22.367
SAM: He makes wagon hitches,
all right?

03:20:22.400 --> 03:20:24.367
-Listen!
-LIAM: I like this guy.

03:20:24.400 --> 03:20:26.634
SAM: He's a simple man!

03:20:28.100 --> 03:20:30.334
He's a great wagon hitch maker.

03:20:30.367 --> 03:20:32.367
PATRICK: Well, I mean,
why do you take a body?

03:20:32.400 --> 03:20:34.033
I mean, well,

03:20:34.067 --> 03:20:36.267
and you're all like,
"Well, I died Tuesday,

03:20:36.300 --> 03:20:38.534
I died Thursday!"

03:20:38.567 --> 03:20:42.701
Like, and then you killed--
how bad did you kill the dragon?

03:20:42.734 --> 03:20:45.434
Because if you didn't
kill it real bad--

03:20:45.467 --> 03:20:46.501
LAURA: It could be brought back.

03:20:46.534 --> 03:20:48.267
PATRICK: Like Tuesday, right?

03:20:48.300 --> 03:20:50.567
LAURA: At least
the gem was shattered--

03:20:50.601 --> 03:20:52.100
the gem was shattered.

03:20:52.133 --> 03:20:53.367
-MATT: "It was?"
-LAURA: Yes.

03:20:53.400 --> 03:20:54.534
MATT: "You destroyed the Soul Anchor?"

03:20:54.567 --> 03:20:56.000
LAURA: Yeah, and Thordak shrunk!

03:20:56.033 --> 03:20:59.601
He was huge, and then
he was like normal after that.

03:20:59.634 --> 03:21:01.567
MATT: "Well, that's something at least."

03:21:01.601 --> 03:21:03.067
TRAVIS: Yeah, it's something.

03:21:03.100 --> 03:21:06.434
SAM: I don't think that she's trying
to reanimate Thordak.

03:21:06.467 --> 03:21:08.567
I think she's
trying to probe him

03:21:08.601 --> 03:21:10.000
for knowledge of some sort.

03:21:10.033 --> 03:21:12.901
-TRAVIS: Probe.
-TALIESIN: I think she's attempting--

03:21:12.934 --> 03:21:14.434
SAM: She's trying to probe
his dead body.

03:21:14.467 --> 03:21:16.267
TRAVIS: Probe.

03:21:18.901 --> 03:21:24.200
MARISHA: Allura, if we scried
on this island,

03:21:24.234 --> 03:21:29.567
if you saw it again,
would you recognize it?

03:21:29.601 --> 03:21:32.267
MATT: "I'm--I haven't been there,

03:21:32.300 --> 03:21:36.400
-but if I were to scry..."
-MARISHA: Oh, I thought you said...

03:21:36.434 --> 03:21:39.400
MATT: "...what would you require--
what would you need?"

03:21:39.434 --> 03:21:41.100
MARISHA: I wanna confirm
if she actually is

03:21:41.133 --> 03:21:43.868
on the island
of Viscar--Viscon.

03:21:43.901 --> 03:21:46.300
MATT: "Well, I mean, I can attempt to.

03:21:46.334 --> 03:21:48.300
I've only heard of it, so..."

03:21:49.934 --> 03:21:52.300
SAM: Do you--what if we--

03:21:52.334 --> 03:21:55.400
would it help you to scry
if we gave you some blood

03:21:55.434 --> 03:21:58.534
of the thing that
we're scrying on?

03:21:58.567 --> 03:22:00.100
LAURA: Thordak?

03:22:00.133 --> 03:22:03.100
MARISHA: But she would still see
the same thing that I would--

03:22:03.133 --> 03:22:04.267
that I would've seen.

03:22:04.300 --> 03:22:06.467
-It wouldn't confirm the island.
-LAURA: Oh, right.

03:22:06.501 --> 03:22:09.133
TALIESIN: It also might mean
that we would be discovered.

03:22:09.167 --> 03:22:11.234
SAM: Keyleth, don't you have some spell

03:22:11.267 --> 03:22:13.000
where you say
the name of a place

03:22:13.033 --> 03:22:15.033
and it shows you
the way there or something?

03:22:15.067 --> 03:22:17.167
LIAM: Well, can you look
for trees on that island?

03:22:17.200 --> 03:22:20.200
MARISHA: I could try and scry...

03:22:21.868 --> 03:22:25.693
on Viscar--Viscon.

03:22:25.693 --> 03:22:27.801
Right? If I know
enough about Viscon,

03:22:27.834 --> 03:22:30.234
I could try and scry
on a location, correct?

03:22:30.267 --> 03:22:31.701
SAM: No, you can only scry
on a person.

03:22:31.734 --> 03:22:33.367
MATT: Yup, you can scry
on a location.

03:22:33.400 --> 03:22:34.767
That was my fault
in the past, by the way.

03:22:34.801 --> 03:22:36.667
I completely--I--
very into the spell.

03:22:36.701 --> 03:22:39.567
SAM: But no, don't you have
like a directions spell?

03:22:39.601 --> 03:22:42.501
-MARISHA: Find the path, yeah.
-SAM: What does that do?

03:22:42.534 --> 03:22:45.100
MATT: Yeah, if you have
secondhand knowledge,

03:22:45.133 --> 03:22:46.701
and you've heard of the target,
you can still scry to it,

03:22:46.734 --> 03:22:49.067
it just has a modifier--
if it's a target.

03:22:49.100 --> 03:22:53.234
If it's a location, um...

03:22:53.267 --> 03:22:55.601
LAURA: But, 'cause I--will it--

03:22:55.634 --> 03:22:57.167
I mean, we lucked out
the first time

03:22:57.200 --> 03:22:58.767
that she didn't catch on.

03:22:58.801 --> 03:23:00.701
What if she realizes?

03:23:00.734 --> 03:23:03.767
MARISHA: If I scry on the island,
she won't notice.

03:23:03.801 --> 03:23:05.300
-LAURA: Okay.
-MARISHA: It's only if I scry on her.

03:23:05.334 --> 03:23:07.501
SAM: ...you're looking
at some leaves and trees.

03:23:07.534 --> 03:23:09.434
TALIESIN: But we'll get an idea
of where to go.

03:23:09.467 --> 03:23:12.067
-MARISHA: I could look--
-LIAM: You saw it once already,

03:23:12.100 --> 03:23:13.934
and you would know it--
you'd probably recognize it

03:23:13.968 --> 03:23:16.501
-a second time.
-MARISHA: Would I?

03:23:16.534 --> 03:23:18.167
-TRAVIS: Would you?
-LIAM: It's worth a fucking shot.

03:23:18.200 --> 03:23:22.400
MARISHA: If I--if I scried on Viscon,

03:23:22.434 --> 03:23:24.200
could I recognize, yeah,

03:23:24.234 --> 03:23:26.534
this looks like
the similar island?

03:23:26.567 --> 03:23:27.534
MATT: You could try, yeah.

03:23:27.567 --> 03:23:29.467
LAURA: Yeah, you could certainly try.

03:23:29.501 --> 03:23:31.434
MATT: You can certainly try.

03:23:31.467 --> 03:23:32.711
Thank you, Laura.

03:23:32.711 --> 03:23:34.155
I needed a little goose.

03:23:34.155 --> 03:23:35.690
-MARISHA: All right.
-MATT: Needed a little ...

03:23:35.690 --> 03:23:37.701
MARISHA: Last fifth-level
spell of the day.

03:23:37.734 --> 03:23:39.801
(cross talk)

03:23:42.033 --> 03:23:45.334
LAURA: Ker, you should try this wine
that Grog got from--

03:23:45.334 --> 03:23:47.033
-TRAVIS: Yes!
-MARISHA: You should try it!

03:23:47.067 --> 03:23:49.968
-TRAVIS: Oh, it's really good!
-MARISHA: It's so tasty!

03:23:50.000 --> 03:23:54.033
-TRAVIS: ...sand dunes of terribleness.
-LIAM: I mean, you don't want to--

03:23:54.067 --> 03:23:55.434
I haven't tried it either.

03:23:55.467 --> 03:23:57.328
You don't want
to finish your life

03:23:57.328 --> 03:23:58.868
without trying this bug juice.

03:23:58.901 --> 03:24:00.467
It's the nickname
we have for it.

03:24:00.501 --> 03:24:02.701
TRAVIS: I pop the top,
and I hand the bottle to him.

03:24:02.734 --> 03:24:04.868
LAURA: Just small--small amounts.

03:24:04.901 --> 03:24:08.200
TRAVIS: What is it, sand keg, sand...

03:24:08.234 --> 03:24:11.634
-LIAM: Bug juice.
-TRAVIS: Yeah, that stuff.

03:24:11.667 --> 03:24:14.167
(cross talk)

03:24:14.200 --> 03:24:15.567
LIAM: I take the bottle,
and I put my thumb over it

03:24:15.601 --> 03:24:16.601
and pretend like
I'm drinking--go--

03:24:16.601 --> 03:24:18.667
MATT: Sleight-of-hand.

03:24:18.667 --> 03:24:20.734
LIAM: That's great, sure.

03:24:22.868 --> 03:24:25.934
LIAM: Sure, sure, sure.

03:24:25.968 --> 03:24:28.267
LIAM: That is a 26.

03:24:28.300 --> 03:24:31.400
MATT: For the hell of it, Kerrek,
go ahead and roll--

03:24:31.434 --> 03:24:34.734
roll a perception check.

03:24:34.767 --> 03:24:37.734
PATRICK: Uh, no, not by--
not by a country mile.

03:24:37.767 --> 03:24:39.234
MATT: He took a mighty swig.

03:24:39.267 --> 03:24:40.901
PATRICK: Yeah, well, it's--

03:24:40.934 --> 03:24:44.033
-LAURA: Don't take a swig that big.
-PATRICK: It's that good?

03:24:44.067 --> 03:24:45.901
-LIAM: It's smooth.
-TRAVIS: It has really got

03:24:45.934 --> 03:24:47.934
-some balls on it.
-LIAM: It goes down smooth.

03:24:47.968 --> 03:24:50.200
PATRICK: You gotta shake the flavor in.

03:24:50.234 --> 03:24:51.767
(laughing)

03:24:51.801 --> 03:24:55.100
'Cause the flavor goes
slowly to the bottom.

03:24:55.133 --> 03:24:57.300
-LAURA: Oh, God, oh, no.
-PATRICK: It's 'cause of the gravity.

03:24:57.334 --> 03:24:58.868
LAURA: What if he realized
something we didn't?

03:24:58.901 --> 03:25:00.267
MARISHA: See, I told you see was wise.

03:25:00.300 --> 03:25:01.834
LIAM: I wish it could be
my first time again.

03:25:01.868 --> 03:25:05.334
MATT: So as the liquid hits
your lips, it's thick.

03:25:05.367 --> 03:25:06.801
It's like...

03:25:06.834 --> 03:25:09.033
(laughing)

03:25:09.067 --> 03:25:10.968
PATRICK: Too much flavor.

03:25:12.767 --> 03:25:14.601
MATT: It doesn't pour
like wine or liquor,

03:25:14.634 --> 03:25:16.234
it pours more like a--

03:25:16.267 --> 03:25:18.868
like a light honey.

03:25:18.901 --> 03:25:25.367
But it has
a very acrid, um...

03:25:25.400 --> 03:25:29.167
pungent, immediate flavor
as it hits your tongue.

03:25:29.200 --> 03:25:31.767
I need you to roll
a constitution saving throw.

03:25:31.801 --> 03:25:38.067
PATRICK: So is this like when I left
that glass of Surge out

03:25:38.100 --> 03:25:42.400
for so long that it
evaporated in the cup down?

03:25:42.434 --> 03:25:43.868
-TRAVIS: Just, like, ...
-MATT: Kind of, yeah.

03:25:43.901 --> 03:25:48.501
PATRICK: And then because there
was no mold growing on it,

03:25:48.534 --> 03:25:50.968
and I am a scientist at heart...

03:25:51.000 --> 03:25:52.100
TRAVIS: It's all clear.

03:25:52.133 --> 03:25:53.734
TALIESIN: You went where mold
feared to tread.

03:25:53.767 --> 03:25:55.667
PATRICK: I, uh--I thought,

03:25:55.701 --> 03:25:57.834
when will I ever have
this opportunity again?

03:25:57.868 --> 03:25:59.467
MATT: When the most basic
forms of life

03:25:59.501 --> 03:26:01.701
eschew existing on a substance,

03:26:01.734 --> 03:26:03.767
that's when you
have to drink it.

03:26:03.801 --> 03:26:05.634
TRAVIS: Agreed.

03:26:05.667 --> 03:26:09.033
TALIESIN: Yes, yes!

03:26:09.067 --> 03:26:11.801
PATRICK: That's gonna be
my best role all year.

03:26:11.834 --> 03:26:14.267
MATT: So--so--

03:26:14.300 --> 03:26:16.334
LIAM: Wait, can I point out

03:26:16.367 --> 03:26:19.033
that this is the best game
in existence?

03:26:19.067 --> 03:26:19.847
(laughing)

03:26:19.847 --> 03:26:20.927
MATT: You may.

03:26:23.367 --> 03:26:24.667
As it fills your gullet,

03:26:24.701 --> 03:26:26.868
the warm, burning sensation
you're used to

03:26:26.901 --> 03:26:29.200
with fine,
heavy liquors is surpassed

03:26:29.234 --> 03:26:35.000
by the ever-burning sensation
of fire within your lungs,

03:26:35.033 --> 03:26:37.300
and as the heartburn
begins to kick in,

03:26:37.334 --> 03:26:39.334
you stop for a second and
realize that the burn goes away

03:26:39.367 --> 03:26:41.367
and everything goes numb.

03:26:41.400 --> 03:26:42.701
Everything goes numb.

03:26:42.734 --> 03:26:47.167
Your tongue...your jaw...

03:26:47.200 --> 03:26:48.834
LAURA: How do you feel, Ker?

03:26:53.200 --> 03:26:55.200
(indistinct speech)

03:26:55.234 --> 03:26:57.567
(laughing)

03:27:00.467 --> 03:27:02.067
LIAM: One more time?

03:27:05.501 --> 03:27:07.400
SAM: Beard got in the way.

03:27:10.267 --> 03:27:12.934
(indistinct speech)

03:27:12.968 --> 03:27:16.167
(laughing)

03:27:16.200 --> 03:27:17.901
LAURA: He likes it--
I think he likes it.

03:27:17.934 --> 03:27:19.267
LIAM: I would've thought that as well.

03:27:19.300 --> 03:27:20.334
TALIESIN: Ladies and gentlemen,
Burning Man,

03:27:20.367 --> 03:27:21.400
ladies and gentlemen.

03:27:21.434 --> 03:27:23.267
Welcome to Burning Man.

03:27:23.300 --> 03:27:25.434
TRAVIS: That is good shit.

03:27:25.467 --> 03:27:27.667
MARISHA: The fire has passed through you.

03:27:27.701 --> 03:27:31.267
(laughing)

03:27:31.300 --> 03:27:33.734
It's gonna go
all the way through you.

03:27:33.767 --> 03:27:35.534
So be careful when it
comes out the other end.

03:27:35.567 --> 03:27:37.300
LIAM: Good reincorporation!

03:27:37.334 --> 03:27:39.300
(laughing)

03:27:41.934 --> 03:27:43.701
TALIESIN: I remember this.

03:27:43.734 --> 03:27:46.367
LAURA: But you're still conscious,
and that is saying something.

03:27:46.400 --> 03:27:48.601
TRAVIS: Really impressive.

03:27:48.634 --> 03:27:50.033
LAURA: I wouldn't drink
any more of it, though.

03:27:50.067 --> 03:27:51.167
TRAVIS: No, no, no, yeah,
you gotta warm up

03:27:51.200 --> 03:27:52.367
-and then take another one.
-LIAM: No, no, no,

03:27:52.400 --> 03:27:54.901
I mean, that's all fun
and games, but come on.

03:27:56.701 --> 03:27:58.200
MATT: As this is happening,
you all look over

03:27:58.234 --> 03:28:00.133
and glance that, as Allura
has cleared the table

03:28:00.167 --> 03:28:02.667
and begun to set a space
for the scry ritual,

03:28:02.701 --> 03:28:04.934
-is just staring at you all.
-LAURA: Oh, shit, right.

03:28:04.968 --> 03:28:07.601
MARISHA: Thanks for setting
this up for us, Allura.

03:28:07.634 --> 03:28:09.601
-MATT: "Oh, please, keep going."
-TRAVIS: We didn't mean to be rude.

03:28:09.634 --> 03:28:10.868
MATT: "This is the most fun
I've had in days."

03:28:10.901 --> 03:28:13.300
TRAVIS: Do you want some?

03:28:13.334 --> 03:28:14.467
TALIESIN: After!

03:28:14.501 --> 03:28:17.434
(yelling)

03:28:17.467 --> 03:28:20.400
LIAM: No, that's a bad idea,
don't do it!

03:28:20.434 --> 03:28:21.801
-TRAVIS: Do it.
-SAM: She needs to do the spell!

03:28:21.834 --> 03:28:24.133
LIAM: Do it later--
that shit's fucked up.

03:28:24.167 --> 03:28:25.801
TRAVIS: Don't listen to him.

03:28:25.834 --> 03:28:26.934
MARISHA: Wait, I thought
I was doing the spell.

03:28:26.968 --> 03:28:28.734
We could do it together.

03:28:28.767 --> 03:28:30.834
TRAVIS: We're trustworthy.
Open the bottle.

03:28:30.868 --> 03:28:33.501
-Down the hatch.
-MATT: She pops it off, and goes,

03:28:33.534 --> 03:28:36.067
"Look, it's morning,
we're all alive.

03:28:36.100 --> 03:28:37.334
What's the point if
we're not celebrating?"

03:28:37.367 --> 03:28:39.244
-TRAVIS: That's what I'm saying!
-LIAM: That will turn

03:28:39.244 --> 03:28:41.234
your blonde hair green!

03:28:41.267 --> 03:28:43.133
TALIESIN: No!

03:28:43.167 --> 03:28:44.274
MATT: Ah.

03:28:45.667 --> 03:28:46.834
"Not my favorite flavor."

03:28:46.868 --> 03:28:48.133
(gasping)

03:28:48.167 --> 03:28:50.024
-LIAM: She's got magic.
-SAM: She's so strong!

03:28:50.024 --> 03:28:52.067
LAURA: Constitutions for days!

03:28:52.067 --> 03:28:53.367
LIAM: She's so cool.

03:28:53.400 --> 03:28:55.901
TRAVIS: Will you teach me
your sorcerous ways?

03:28:55.934 --> 03:28:57.834
LAURA: Keep talking, keep talking.

03:28:57.868 --> 03:28:59.234
TRAVIS: How do you feel?

03:28:59.267 --> 03:29:01.300
MATT: "I feel fine."

03:29:01.334 --> 03:29:03.267
TRAVIS: I don't--I don't
know what to say.

03:29:03.300 --> 03:29:05.934
-LIAM: Fucking magic.
-SAM: She's amazing.

03:29:05.968 --> 03:29:07.634
MARISHA: You're awesome.

03:29:07.667 --> 03:29:10.601
LIAM: Can you say red leather,
yellow leather?

03:29:14.434 --> 03:29:15.901
What about--

03:29:15.934 --> 03:29:17.133
(laughing)

03:29:17.167 --> 03:29:19.667
What about--try saying
three times in a row

03:29:19.701 --> 03:29:22.100
can you say Irish wristwatch?

03:29:22.133 --> 03:29:24.033
(laughing)

03:29:27.267 --> 03:29:30.834
PATRICK: Three times in a row.

03:29:30.868 --> 03:29:35.834
LIAM: This is to Ker or Patrick--
Irish wristwatch

03:29:35.868 --> 03:29:37.968
as fast as you can
three times in a row.

03:29:38.000 --> 03:29:39.634
I have faith in you.

03:29:43.300 --> 03:29:45.000
PATRICK: Irish wr--

03:29:45.033 --> 03:29:48.534
(laughing)

03:29:48.567 --> 03:29:50.934
Irish wr--

03:29:59.234 --> 03:30:02.200
Irish wish--

03:30:02.234 --> 03:30:04.367
LIAM: You know, thank you for playing.

03:30:06.267 --> 03:30:08.133
That was a valiant effort.

03:30:10.634 --> 03:30:12.567
Hey, let's scry on a dragon!

03:30:14.667 --> 03:30:15.801
MATT: "All right."

03:30:15.834 --> 03:30:17.834
(laughing)

03:30:20.501 --> 03:30:21.701
TRAVIS: Were you in a motorcycle gang?

03:30:21.734 --> 03:30:25.033
How did she do that?

03:30:25.067 --> 03:30:27.801
-LIAM: Warrior!
-SAM: She's immune to alcohol.

03:30:27.834 --> 03:30:29.767
MATT: She sits across the table
from you and puts her hands out.

03:30:29.801 --> 03:30:31.667
SAM: Oh, yeah, let's do this.

03:30:31.701 --> 03:30:34.200
MARISHA: Oh, man, it just feels
like old days, Allura!

03:30:34.234 --> 03:30:36.167
MATT: "That it does--simpler times."

03:30:36.200 --> 03:30:37.868
MARISHA: Yes, it was.

03:30:37.901 --> 03:30:39.400
MATT: As you both close your eyes

03:30:39.434 --> 03:30:44.167
and you all watch as Allura
and Keyleth close their eyes.

03:30:45.267 --> 03:30:48.601
A moment passes,
a second moment,

03:30:48.634 --> 03:30:52.501
and across the smooth,
polished wood table surface

03:30:52.534 --> 03:30:53.834
of which you've been
having breakfast,

03:30:53.868 --> 03:30:57.100
you watch as the grain
begins to shift.

03:30:57.133 --> 03:31:01.868
Almost these small lines
of light blue and white

03:31:01.901 --> 03:31:04.734
sparkling, tiny arcane ley lines

03:31:04.767 --> 03:31:07.300
begin to just curl
a circle around the table.

03:31:07.334 --> 03:31:11.000
In the center,
their arms are clenched.

03:31:11.033 --> 03:31:13.267
You watch as it
carves two circles--

03:31:13.300 --> 03:31:14.868
one smaller one
within the other--

03:31:14.901 --> 03:31:17.300
and then begin to form
these various, rigid,

03:31:17.334 --> 03:31:21.000
star-like patterns within,
and as soon as the two points

03:31:21.033 --> 03:31:22.701
eventually connect
in the center,

03:31:22.734 --> 03:31:24.901
there's a flash,
and both Keyleth and Allura

03:31:24.934 --> 03:31:27.267
open their eyes,
but there is no pupil,

03:31:27.300 --> 03:31:29.267
there is no iris,
it is just white.

03:31:29.300 --> 03:31:31.434
-TRAVIS: Creepy.
-PATRICK: Fuck.

03:31:31.467 --> 03:31:35.200
(laughing)

03:31:35.234 --> 03:31:38.868
TALIESIN: That was the most Brian Blessed
fuck I've ever...

03:31:38.901 --> 03:31:39.968
It was amazing.

03:31:40.000 --> 03:31:42.033
(laughter continues)

03:31:45.167 --> 03:31:46.567
MATT: The two of you share a vision--

03:31:46.601 --> 03:31:49.901
a vision of water,
a vision of endless ocean--

03:31:49.934 --> 03:31:51.434
a familiar vision
of endless ocean.

03:31:51.467 --> 03:31:54.934
You see small pillars of steam

03:31:54.968 --> 03:31:57.501
rising out of the center
of this expanse,

03:31:57.534 --> 03:31:58.901
clusters of them in places,

03:31:58.934 --> 03:32:01.167
occasionally a few rocks
breaking the surface,

03:32:01.200 --> 03:32:03.367
and beyond that,
you see an island

03:32:03.400 --> 03:32:07.067
isolated out in the ocean,
covered with green.

03:32:07.100 --> 03:32:10.234
You see a large mountain
set across one side

03:32:10.267 --> 03:32:13.734
as your vision flashes inward
to an overhead view,

03:32:13.767 --> 03:32:15.567
you see a familiar island.

03:32:16.968 --> 03:32:19.067
SAM: ♪ And the line where
the sea meets the sky ♪

03:32:19.100 --> 03:32:21.133
♪ It's blinding ♪♪

03:32:21.167 --> 03:32:24.067
(laughing)

03:32:24.100 --> 03:32:26.000
MATT: The vision fades,
you both return,

03:32:26.033 --> 03:32:28.767
the circular glyphs
on the table

03:32:28.801 --> 03:32:30.067
kind of sparkle out

03:32:30.100 --> 03:32:32.467
leaving the smooth surface
untouched.

03:32:32.501 --> 03:32:34.234
Both of their eyes clarify,

03:32:34.267 --> 03:32:36.901
their irises
and pupils returning,

03:32:36.934 --> 03:32:39.234
and they both take
a simultaneous breath,

03:32:39.267 --> 03:32:41.334
and then release
each other's hands.

03:32:43.367 --> 03:32:45.634
MARISHA: Holy shit.

03:32:45.667 --> 03:32:47.167
-LAURA: So yeah?
-MARISHA: Yeah.

03:32:47.200 --> 03:32:48.234
We know where she is.

03:32:48.267 --> 03:32:50.067
(gasping)

03:32:50.100 --> 03:32:51.267
It's the island.

03:32:51.300 --> 03:32:52.868
LAURA: Do we know how to get
to the island?

03:32:52.901 --> 03:32:54.767
MARISHA: I can tree stride us there.

03:32:54.801 --> 03:32:56.334
I saw a tree--did I see
a tree big enough?

03:32:56.367 --> 03:32:57.734
-MATT: There were a number of trees.
-LAURA: Oh, geez!

03:32:57.767 --> 03:32:59.033
SAM: Palm trees?

03:32:59.067 --> 03:33:01.667
LAURA: Oh, my God, we need
to rest and get there.

03:33:01.701 --> 03:33:04.100
-MARISHA: We need to rest and get there.
-LIAM: We need to go the fuck to bed.

03:33:04.133 --> 03:33:05.367
PATRICK: Let's go right now!

03:33:05.400 --> 03:33:07.501
(cross talk)

03:33:10.367 --> 03:33:12.100
That was a joke.

03:33:12.133 --> 03:33:15.501
(laughing)

03:33:15.534 --> 03:33:16.701
LAURA: Shit, we need to rest!

03:33:16.734 --> 03:33:18.100
MARISHA: Oh, my God, yeah.

03:33:18.133 --> 03:33:20.734
-LAURA: And go!
-MARISHA: We need to rest and go.

03:33:20.767 --> 03:33:22.234
LIAM: We should go right away.

03:33:22.267 --> 03:33:25.400
What a to-do to die today
at a minute or two 'til two.

03:33:25.434 --> 03:33:27.267
SAM: Trippingly off the tongue.

03:33:28.834 --> 03:33:31.100
-MATT: "You get two options."
-LAURA: Okay.

03:33:31.133 --> 03:33:34.267
MATT: "And I defer to
your judgment on this.

03:33:34.300 --> 03:33:35.934
You rest and prepare,

03:33:35.968 --> 03:33:38.033
that leaves her
to rest and prepare."

03:33:38.067 --> 03:33:40.167
-LAURA: Yes.
-MATT: "You don't rest,

03:33:40.200 --> 03:33:42.067
she doesn't rest.

03:33:42.100 --> 03:33:44.017
The choice is yours
as to which you think

03:33:44.017 --> 03:33:46.634
leaves you in the more
advantageous position.

03:33:46.667 --> 03:33:50.167
MARISHA: I--I--I cannot...

03:33:50.200 --> 03:33:52.167
get us there.

03:33:52.200 --> 03:33:54.467
-LAURA: We need to rest.
-LIAM: Can you get us there?

03:33:54.501 --> 03:33:57.033
MATT: "I've unfortunately
already used my spell

03:33:57.067 --> 03:34:00.100
to get you to..."

03:34:00.133 --> 03:34:02.167
LIAM: But you're say--I understand
what you're saying.

03:34:02.200 --> 03:34:03.868
-She's got nothing--
-MATT: She stops and goes,

03:34:03.901 --> 03:34:06.567
"I've seen it, actually,
with the vision.

03:34:06.601 --> 03:34:10.100
And I did rest--I do--I could.

03:34:10.133 --> 03:34:12.467
I could get you there."

03:34:12.501 --> 03:34:14.501
SAM: To what end?

03:34:14.534 --> 03:34:16.901
-MATT: "The choice is yours."
-SAM: I have nothing.

03:34:16.934 --> 03:34:20.467
LIAM: But Scanlan, pluses and minuses.

03:34:20.501 --> 03:34:23.000
She has nothing.

03:34:23.033 --> 03:34:27.167
SAM: I can't die, Vax.

03:34:27.200 --> 03:34:28.701
I've already died once today,

03:34:28.734 --> 03:34:29.934
I can't do it again.

03:34:29.968 --> 03:34:31.234
LAURA: We don't have any healing.

03:34:31.267 --> 03:34:34.868
If anybody dies,
we can't come back.

03:34:34.901 --> 03:34:36.701
TRAVIS: I've got two healing potions.

03:34:36.734 --> 03:34:40.100
MARISHA: Okay, all right.

03:34:40.133 --> 03:34:41.934
(humming)

03:34:41.968 --> 03:34:45.534
Is there a way, do you know,
where we can maybe, like,

03:34:45.567 --> 03:34:48.234
restore ourselves faster?

03:34:50.534 --> 03:34:53.033
(laughing)

03:34:53.067 --> 03:34:55.367
MATT: "I wouldn't recommend that."

03:34:55.400 --> 03:34:57.133
TRAVIS: Oh?

03:34:57.167 --> 03:34:59.801
LAURA: Oh!

03:34:59.834 --> 03:35:01.501
MATT: "But nevertheleth..."

03:35:01.534 --> 03:35:02.934
(laughing)

03:35:02.968 --> 03:35:04.901
TRAVIS: Amazing.

03:35:04.934 --> 03:35:07.567
PATRICK: Say, Irish wr--wr--

03:35:07.601 --> 03:35:09.868
(laughing)

03:35:09.901 --> 03:35:11.334
TALIESIN: Hard, isn't it?

03:35:17.567 --> 03:35:19.673
MATT: She goes back to
braiding her hair.

03:35:19.673 --> 03:35:21.934
(laughing)

03:35:21.968 --> 03:35:24.834
MARISHA: What is the minimum amount
of time we could sleep?

03:35:24.868 --> 03:35:26.334
MATT: Eight hours.

03:35:26.367 --> 03:35:27.868
(grumbling)

03:35:27.901 --> 03:35:29.167
TRAVIS: Let's do it, let's sleep.

03:35:29.200 --> 03:35:31.701
LIAM: So if we rest,
she gets her meteors,

03:35:31.734 --> 03:35:33.000
she gets her everything.

03:35:33.033 --> 03:35:34.901
-LAURA: She gets it all back.
-SAM: And she could leave.

03:35:37.234 --> 03:35:40.067
LIAM: She's gonna rest, too,
to get all her shit back.

03:35:40.100 --> 03:35:44.167
If we go now,
having had a breather

03:35:44.200 --> 03:35:46.033
with this drunk guy...

03:35:47.567 --> 03:35:50.300
-LAURA: No!
-LIAM: I'm not saying what we do.

03:35:50.334 --> 03:35:52.400
You can decide what we do
because you're the smart one,

03:35:52.434 --> 03:35:53.734
but I'm just talking it out.

03:35:53.767 --> 03:35:55.434
She--it would be
a physical fight

03:35:55.467 --> 03:35:57.634
with none of her magic.

03:35:57.667 --> 03:36:00.467
TALIESIN: If we had--if we had
a dragon with us, I'd say yes.

03:36:00.501 --> 03:36:03.014
LIAM: You two brainiacs
can make the decision,

03:36:03.014 --> 03:36:06.133
but she's got no meteors,
she's got a lot less.

03:36:06.167 --> 03:36:08.267
LAURA: Look, we took on Thordak
with full health,

03:36:08.300 --> 03:36:11.267
and we made it out pretty well.

03:36:11.300 --> 03:36:13.167
MARISHA: I mean, once again,
unless we do this--

03:36:13.200 --> 03:36:16.267
unless we get to the island,

03:36:16.300 --> 03:36:20.133
try and scout out--
find Raishan...

03:36:20.167 --> 03:36:24.767
...island,
that way if she moves...

03:36:24.801 --> 03:36:26.667
we won't let her leave?

03:36:27.834 --> 03:36:29.701
What Grog, what?

03:36:29.734 --> 03:36:33.067
SAM: I can't camp on the island,
I don't have the mansion.

03:36:33.100 --> 03:36:36.934
MARISHA: We can camp like we did
old school style.

03:36:36.968 --> 03:36:38.467
TALIESIN: She would know
that we were there--

03:36:38.501 --> 03:36:41.801
LAURA: Wait a minute,
you said you had it left.

03:36:41.834 --> 03:36:44.200
TALIESIN: And if we go there...

03:36:44.234 --> 03:36:45.834
LAURA: Scanlan, you said you
still had the spell left

03:36:45.868 --> 03:36:47.701
-so we could--
-MARISHA: No, he used it

03:36:47.734 --> 03:36:51.534
to change Jarrett's mind, right?

03:36:51.567 --> 03:36:52.868
MATT: Well, you don't know that.

03:36:52.901 --> 03:36:55.133
MARISHA: Well.

03:36:55.167 --> 03:36:57.634
LAURA: Oh, well, shit.

03:36:57.667 --> 03:36:59.868
SAM: I used it in the battle,
fuck off.

03:36:59.901 --> 03:37:01.968
(laughing)

03:37:04.434 --> 03:37:05.968
TALIESIN: If--if we were to go right now,

03:37:06.000 --> 03:37:07.467
I would almost recommend

03:37:07.501 --> 03:37:09.868
that Scanlan
and Keyleth stay behind

03:37:09.901 --> 03:37:12.300
because they would be
nothing but targets.

03:37:13.667 --> 03:37:15.467
TRAVIS: Ooh, how does that feel?

03:37:15.501 --> 03:37:16.834
LIAM: Well, then, we won't do that.

03:37:16.868 --> 03:37:18.067
TALIESIN: Which is why we shouldn't go,

03:37:18.100 --> 03:37:21.334
because if we go, it is...
the four of us.

03:37:21.367 --> 03:37:24.367
TRAVIS: Strangely, I agree with Percy.

03:37:24.400 --> 03:37:27.100
TALIESIN: And if we wait a day?

03:37:29.267 --> 03:37:31.667
It's six--it's at least
six, seven, eight of us--

03:37:31.701 --> 03:37:32.834
however many was can bring,

03:37:32.868 --> 03:37:35.234
but every magic user
right now is--

03:37:35.267 --> 03:37:37.434
-LAURA: Tapped.
-LIAM: Allura.

03:37:37.467 --> 03:37:38.667
-MATT: "Yes."
-LAURA: Except for her.

03:37:38.701 --> 03:37:41.734
LIAM: I kinda wanted to bring you
in the beginning.

03:37:41.767 --> 03:37:44.434
Are you willing to come with us?

03:37:44.467 --> 03:37:47.634
MATT: "There's no need for me
to maintain the illutho--

03:37:47.667 --> 03:37:50.950
-the illusory barrier on the thity."

03:37:50.950 --> 03:37:52.470
-PATRICK: Wristwatch.

03:37:52.470 --> 03:37:54.767
(laughing)

03:37:54.801 --> 03:37:57.100
MARISHA: You did it!

03:37:57.133 --> 03:37:58.701
MATT: "That's rather imprethive."

03:38:01.200 --> 03:38:04.534
MARISHA: Okay, well, look,
if we wanted to go now,

03:38:04.567 --> 03:38:08.234
I still have my beast shaping back.

03:38:08.267 --> 03:38:10.934
TALIESIN: That's a bit...

03:38:10.968 --> 03:38:14.334
MARISHA: I have one first-level spell,
two third-level spells,

03:38:14.367 --> 03:38:17.767
and one fourth-level spell.

03:38:17.801 --> 03:38:19.100
-LAURA: Oh, my God.
-SAM: That's enough to kill a dragon.

03:38:19.133 --> 03:38:23.267
LIAM: Do we have--here's a question.

03:38:23.300 --> 03:38:25.801
Do we have some
healing potions banked

03:38:25.834 --> 03:38:27.968
-at Whitestone right now?
-TRAVIS: No.

03:38:28.000 --> 03:38:29.534
-LAURA: We took them all.
-MATT: "To be perfectly honetht,

03:38:29.567 --> 03:38:31.300
we've given you
everything we have."

03:38:31.334 --> 03:38:32.868
(laughing)

03:38:32.901 --> 03:38:34.834
-LAURA: Are there any--
-MATT: "Don't laugh at me, Vex'thahlia."

03:38:34.868 --> 03:38:37.033
LAURA: I'm not, darling, I'm not.

03:38:37.067 --> 03:38:39.133
MARISHA: I haven't used any of my health.

03:38:39.167 --> 03:38:42.534
LAURA: Are there any steal-- heal--(stammering)

03:38:42.567 --> 03:38:45.100
LAURA: Are there any healers
within the castle?

03:38:45.133 --> 03:38:48.367
PATRICK: I am relatively fresh
in terms of healing.

03:38:48.400 --> 03:38:50.601
I could heal some.

03:38:50.634 --> 03:38:52.133
-LAURA: Would you wanna go with us?
-LIAM: Yes, but are you

03:38:52.167 --> 03:38:54.200
in Burbank next week, though?

03:38:54.234 --> 03:38:56.300
(laughing)

03:38:56.334 --> 03:38:58.290
SAM: Pike is out!

03:38:58.290 --> 03:39:00.400
LAURA: Pike is done.

03:39:00.400 --> 03:39:03.100
She's got two 
first-level spells left.

03:39:03.133 --> 03:39:04.234
That's it.

03:39:04.267 --> 03:39:06.901
SAM: I have one fifth and one fourth.

03:39:06.934 --> 03:39:08.200
No, two fourths.

03:39:08.234 --> 03:39:09.901
LAURA: I think I've got two
first-levels spells left,

03:39:09.934 --> 03:39:12.234
-but that's it.
-TALIESIN: It's--

03:39:12.267 --> 03:39:13.767
TRAVIS: Let's be honest.

03:39:13.801 --> 03:39:15.868
We're not quite at our best,

03:39:15.901 --> 03:39:19.968
and it's one diseased
deceiver in a cave

03:39:20.000 --> 03:39:21.834
with another
dead dragon that might

03:39:21.868 --> 03:39:25.667
or might not come back to life,
and two baby little eggs.

03:39:25.701 --> 03:39:29.501
We rest, and then
we give 'em hell!

03:39:29.534 --> 03:39:33.801
PATRICK: The brass dragon, I feel,
made a great point

03:39:33.834 --> 03:39:39.367
that if you let
someone of that...

03:39:39.400 --> 03:39:43.801
-SAM: Power.
-PATRICK: ...power choose

03:39:43.834 --> 03:39:46.167
the rules of engagement...

03:39:48.801 --> 03:39:50.334
-LAURA: Right.
-LIAM: That's a good point,

03:39:50.367 --> 03:39:52.634
and Allura makes a good point.

03:39:54.234 --> 03:39:56.968
TRAVIS: Plus she doesn't know
that we know where she is.

03:39:57.000 --> 03:40:00.167
She thinks she's got
all the time in the world.

03:40:00.200 --> 03:40:01.467
SAM: You wanna go now?

03:40:01.501 --> 03:40:03.267
TRAVIS: No, I wanna wait.

03:40:03.300 --> 03:40:04.834
TALIESIN: Go tomorrow.

03:40:04.868 --> 03:40:07.601
LAURA: I think we rest
and we go tonight.

03:40:07.634 --> 03:40:09.868
We sleep eight hours,
it's only in the morning--

03:40:09.901 --> 03:40:11.901
we go as soon as we're rested.

03:40:11.934 --> 03:40:14.267
LIAM: She's gonna have
everything tomorrow.

03:40:14.267 --> 03:40:18.567
MARISHA: Can we, like, do,
like, six hours...

03:40:18.601 --> 03:40:19.834
SAM: She won't be
expecting us at all.

03:40:19.868 --> 03:40:21.667
MARISHA: ...and chug some coffee?

03:40:21.701 --> 03:40:23.434
MATT: Nope, need a full
eight hour rest.

03:40:23.467 --> 03:40:25.133
SAM: She won't be
expecting us at all.

03:40:25.167 --> 03:40:26.868
We'll still have
the element of surprise,

03:40:26.901 --> 03:40:29.801
she won't have a lair to defend.

03:40:29.834 --> 03:40:32.834
She won't have any other
fire giants to protect her.

03:40:32.868 --> 03:40:34.367
TALIESIN: There might be a lair.

03:40:34.400 --> 03:40:38.868
TRAVIS: Maybe, but we are fucking tits
against lairs, come on.

03:40:38.901 --> 03:40:40.734
SAM: You have a dancing
fucking sword.

03:40:40.767 --> 03:40:42.234
LAURA: That's right.

03:40:42.267 --> 03:40:43.534
LIAM: Percy, what do you think?

03:40:43.567 --> 03:40:48.667
TALIESIN: I think we--honestly,
I think that we--

03:40:48.701 --> 03:40:50.434
I think if we go
right now, we win,

03:40:50.467 --> 03:40:52.400
and at least one of us dies.

03:40:52.434 --> 03:40:55.634
And if we go tomorrow,
we're probably going to win,

03:40:55.667 --> 03:40:58.834
and probably most of us
are going to survive.

03:40:58.868 --> 03:41:04.567
PATRICK: Unless she is merely
scrounging there.

03:41:04.601 --> 03:41:06.167
TALIESIN: I think she might be scrounging,

03:41:06.200 --> 03:41:08.667
but I think if she's scrounging,
that's a lot to look through.

03:41:08.701 --> 03:41:10.567
I think that
she thinks she's safe.

03:41:10.601 --> 03:41:13.734
LAURA: Did it look like there was
a lot of books there, Keyleth?

03:41:13.767 --> 03:41:15.100
MATT: There were quite a number.

03:41:15.133 --> 03:41:17.234
Probably 100 at the very least.

03:41:17.267 --> 03:41:19.067
SAM: We don't even know what she is.

03:41:19.100 --> 03:41:21.968
-Didn't you see a woman?
-LIAM: But that was her.

03:41:22.000 --> 03:41:23.734
MARISHA: That's Raishan
in her female form.

03:41:23.767 --> 03:41:26.634
LIAM: So she can look at books so
she doesn't fucking mangle them.

03:41:26.667 --> 03:41:28.934
TRAVIS: Keyleth, are you worried
if we wait,

03:41:28.968 --> 03:41:31.901
you're going to lose
the chance to kill Raishan?

03:41:33.968 --> 03:41:36.977
MARISHA: I don't think we're gonna lose
the chance to kill Raishan,

03:41:36.977 --> 03:41:40.601
it's just a matter
of who's killing who first.

03:41:40.634 --> 03:41:42.567
TALIESIN: I say that we take
eight hours' sleep,

03:41:42.601 --> 03:41:44.968
and we go there immediately.

03:41:46.467 --> 03:41:48.567
TRAVIS: She thinks she's got cover,
but she doesn't.

03:41:48.601 --> 03:41:51.033
TALIESIN: It will have
only been ten hours at best

03:41:51.067 --> 03:41:52.267
by the time we get there.

03:41:52.300 --> 03:41:54.467
MARISHA: Allura, since you know
of the island,

03:41:54.501 --> 03:41:56.234
and we know where she is,
is there any way

03:41:56.267 --> 03:41:58.100
where we can keep an eye
on the island

03:41:58.133 --> 03:42:00.701
magically from afar?

03:42:00.734 --> 03:42:04.267
If Raishan moves, we know?

03:42:04.300 --> 03:42:11.534
MATT: "I mean, I can incrementally
scry on an island

03:42:11.567 --> 03:42:14.167
and keep an eye on the vicinity,

03:42:14.200 --> 03:42:18.300
but if I scry
directly on Raishan--"

03:42:18.334 --> 03:42:19.767
-MARISHA: She could sense it.
-TALIESIN: She'll sense it.

03:42:19.801 --> 03:42:21.601
MATT: "Well, there's a chance."

03:42:21.634 --> 03:42:23.534
MARISHA: Yeah, let's not do that.

03:42:25.067 --> 03:42:27.100
TRAVIS: Don't you wanna be at your best?

03:42:27.133 --> 03:42:31.167
Don't you wanna be some fucking
wicked badass from the sky?

03:42:31.200 --> 03:42:33.100
Or do you wanna limp in?

03:42:33.133 --> 03:42:34.901
-LAURA: Right?
-TRAVIS: Yeah.

03:42:34.934 --> 03:42:37.067
LAURA: Plus, if she's got
100 books to go through,

03:42:37.100 --> 03:42:38.601
that's gonna take
more than two hours.

03:42:38.634 --> 03:42:41.434
TALIESIN: She may not--it's possible
she may not even rest.

03:42:41.467 --> 03:42:42.968
She might just be
so angry that she's--

03:42:43.000 --> 03:42:44.901
LAURA: She might not be fully rested
by the time we get there.

03:42:44.934 --> 03:42:47.033
TRAVIS: I know it feels like
an advantage to press,

03:42:47.067 --> 03:42:49.834
but we were five down
at one point.

03:42:49.868 --> 03:42:51.701
LAURA: I can't die again.

03:42:51.734 --> 03:42:54.501
TRAVIS: You can, but it's not advisable.

03:42:56.434 --> 03:42:57.767
TALIESIN: Let's not let that happen.

03:42:57.801 --> 03:43:00.634
MARISHA: She has none of her legendary
resistances right now.

03:43:00.667 --> 03:43:02.601
TRAVIS: No, I'm not worried about those.

03:43:02.634 --> 03:43:06.300
TALIESIN: She--we may
interrupt her mid-slumber.

03:43:06.334 --> 03:43:10.300
MARISHA: How long did it take when, um,

03:43:10.334 --> 03:43:15.467
we injured...was that Vorugal?

03:43:15.501 --> 03:43:17.868
Who retreated
and started healing?

03:43:17.901 --> 03:43:21.334
-LIAM: Umbrasyl.
-MARISHA: Umbrasyl.

03:43:21.367 --> 03:43:24.100
-TRAVIS: In his lair.
-MARISHA: In his lair.

03:43:24.133 --> 03:43:26.100
Doing nothing
but sleeping right?

03:43:26.133 --> 03:43:28.767
MATT: Well, you came upon
a number of empty potions--

03:43:28.801 --> 03:43:31.300
things that were part
of Umbrasyl's hoard.

03:43:31.334 --> 03:43:32.767
LAURA: So Raishan might not have that.

03:43:32.801 --> 03:43:34.100
TALIESIN: Or she might.

03:43:34.133 --> 03:43:36.100
LIAM: But we're gonna get--
if we wait till tomorrow--

03:43:36.133 --> 03:43:38.534
TALIESIN: Which, if she does have it,
she's already taken them.

03:43:38.567 --> 03:43:40.601
LIAM: You all can decide,
but if we go tomorrow,

03:43:40.634 --> 03:43:45.167
she's fully stacked,
she's in her lair.

03:43:45.200 --> 03:43:46.868
If we go tonight--I'm just--

03:43:46.901 --> 03:43:48.267
LAURA: I don't wanna
fucking go tonight.

03:43:48.300 --> 03:43:49.701
I don't wanna go tonight.

03:43:49.734 --> 03:43:51.434
-I don't wanna die again.
-TALIESIN: It's the morning,

03:43:51.467 --> 03:43:53.167
we sleep through the day,
we go tonight.

03:43:53.200 --> 03:43:54.534
LIAM: Well then, there's
nothing to talk about.

03:43:54.567 --> 03:43:56.701
-TALIESIN: I think that's the way to go.
-TRAVIS: Agreed.

03:43:58.033 --> 03:43:59.100
LAURA: We sleep, we go tonight.

03:43:59.133 --> 03:44:00.567
TALIESIN: We sleep, we go tonight.

03:44:00.601 --> 03:44:03.133
She may spend all of today
going through those books,

03:44:03.167 --> 03:44:04.934
and then sleep tonight.

03:44:04.968 --> 03:44:07.100
TRAVIS: Keyleth, we know
what we're asking of you.

03:44:07.133 --> 03:44:08.934
We're asking you to wait, again.

03:44:08.968 --> 03:44:10.934
(chuckling)

03:44:10.968 --> 03:44:13.400
MARISHA: I...

03:44:13.434 --> 03:44:16.827
I think in recent events,
I can wait.

03:44:18.300 --> 03:44:20.934
-SAM: Then at dusk...
-TRAVIS: We plan.

03:44:20.968 --> 03:44:23.334
SAM: Yes.

03:44:23.367 --> 03:44:25.534
(mixed remarks)

03:44:25.567 --> 03:44:28.801
TRAVIS: It's actually dawn--sorry.

03:44:29.801 --> 03:44:31.734
MARISHA: How much do you...

03:44:31.767 --> 03:44:35.234
how much do you heal up
overnight, generally?

03:44:35.267 --> 03:44:37.767
MATT: At night, you get full points,

03:44:37.801 --> 03:44:42.434
and you get back half of your--

03:44:42.467 --> 03:44:45.067
half of your hit dice
that were spent.

03:44:45.100 --> 03:44:46.634
MARISHA: Okay.

03:44:50.334 --> 03:44:53.000
TRAVIS: Make the call, Keyleth.

03:44:53.033 --> 03:44:54.801
MARISHA: We'd better get sleeping,
I guess.

03:44:54.834 --> 03:44:56.801
LAURA: Let's go to bed.

03:44:56.834 --> 03:44:59.067
SAM: Instead of fighting,
we're going to sleep.

03:44:59.100 --> 03:45:00.534
MARISHA: Well, what do you want, Scanlan?

03:45:00.567 --> 03:45:02.634
-TALIESIN: You can go.
-MARISHA: You have been devil's advocate

03:45:02.667 --> 03:45:04.501
this whole time--
"I don't wanna die again,

03:45:04.534 --> 03:45:06.667
but she could kill us!"

03:45:06.701 --> 03:45:08.534
What do you want, Scanlan?

03:45:08.567 --> 03:45:09.834
SAM: I don't wanna die.

03:45:09.868 --> 03:45:12.734
-LAURA: Then let's sleep.
-TALIESIN: Then sleep.

03:45:12.767 --> 03:45:14.367
MARISHA: I don't wanna die either,

03:45:14.400 --> 03:45:17.267
and I don't wanna watch
any of you die again.

03:45:17.300 --> 03:45:19.601
TALIESIN: But if we go right now,
you're going to die.

03:45:21.634 --> 03:45:24.234
LAURA: We need your spells
to protect us--

03:45:24.267 --> 03:45:26.133
you're clutch in a fight--

03:45:26.167 --> 03:45:28.934
and without them,
you're kind of just a--

03:45:28.968 --> 03:45:31.434
a dude.

03:45:31.467 --> 03:45:33.667
TALIESIN: Who's very good
at becoming a target.

03:45:35.400 --> 03:45:37.801
SAM: I'm so much more than a dude.

03:45:37.834 --> 03:45:39.801
(laughing)

03:45:39.834 --> 03:45:41.934
TALIESIN: One day you may be a bro.

03:45:43.634 --> 03:45:45.598
SAM: Someday.

03:45:46.901 --> 03:45:48.200
MATT: And on that note,

03:45:48.234 --> 03:45:51.901
you begin to put
your things together,

03:45:51.934 --> 03:45:58.934
your plots, your preparations
for getting to rest...

03:45:59.871 --> 03:46:01.901
Did you have
something you wanna do?

03:46:01.934 --> 03:46:04.200
LIAM: It feels like you're
going to wind down.

03:46:05.534 --> 03:46:08.534
Before we do that,
if everyone's going to bed...

03:46:09.767 --> 03:46:13.834
back in your room, I plunk down
a bottle of whatever,

03:46:13.868 --> 03:46:19.234
and I take out Whisper--
have a seat.

03:46:19.267 --> 03:46:24.133
-MARISHA: Okay.
-LIAM: I take Whisper,

03:46:24.167 --> 03:46:27.200
and I just start
gently cutting away

03:46:27.234 --> 03:46:32.734
burnt edges of hair
on your already shorter hair

03:46:32.767 --> 03:46:34.334
so that the ends are clean.

03:46:34.367 --> 03:46:35.701
LAURA: Aww.

03:46:36.801 --> 03:46:38.834
MARISHA: Do you like it shorter?

03:46:40.167 --> 03:46:41.901
LIAM: I like you.

03:46:41.934 --> 03:46:44.367
♪

03:46:44.400 --> 03:46:48.300
And I see you doubting yourself.

03:46:48.334 --> 03:46:50.734
♪

03:46:50.767 --> 03:46:52.467
I see it, Kiki.

03:46:52.501 --> 03:46:55.834
♪

03:46:55.868 --> 03:46:57.634
I have no doubts in you.

03:46:57.667 --> 03:47:00.868
♪

03:47:00.901 --> 03:47:03.667
I've known you
for a long time now...

03:47:03.701 --> 03:47:06.901
♪

03:47:06.934 --> 03:47:11.667
and I have seen
the strength in you growing.

03:47:11.701 --> 03:47:15.067
♪

03:47:15.100 --> 03:47:16.634
And I'm a fan.

03:47:16.667 --> 03:47:20.367
♪

03:47:20.400 --> 03:47:23.200
You're gonna make
a great leader some day.

03:47:23.234 --> 03:47:27.327
♪

03:47:27.327 --> 03:47:29.767
MARISHA: I just feel like
there's so many people

03:47:29.801 --> 03:47:31.167
I could easily disappoint.

03:47:31.200 --> 03:47:32.834
I don't want to.

03:47:32.868 --> 03:47:37.367
♪

03:47:37.400 --> 03:47:39.067
LIAM: You are doing
the very best you can

03:47:39.100 --> 03:47:41.400
with what you've been given,

03:47:41.434 --> 03:47:43.934
and I've seen you rise
again and again

03:47:43.968 --> 03:47:46.267
and not stop and not back down.

03:47:46.300 --> 03:47:48.267
♪

03:47:48.300 --> 03:47:50.000
And you fucking blow me away

03:47:50.033 --> 03:47:52.200
with the things
you can do out there.

03:47:54.033 --> 03:47:56.868
You are beautiful,
and you are talented,

03:47:56.901 --> 03:47:59.300
and you are strong as fuck.

03:47:59.334 --> 03:48:01.501
♪

03:48:01.534 --> 03:48:03.000
And I can't take
the doubt away--

03:48:03.033 --> 03:48:04.567
I can't do that.

03:48:04.601 --> 03:48:07.367
♪

03:48:07.400 --> 03:48:12.601
But mix in with that
my faith in you...

03:48:14.067 --> 03:48:16.467
Percy's faith in you...

03:48:17.767 --> 03:48:20.334
Grog's faith in you...

03:48:20.367 --> 03:48:22.634
Ker's...

03:48:22.667 --> 03:48:25.868
Vex'ahlia's, Scanlan's,

03:48:25.901 --> 03:48:27.634
Allura's...

03:48:28.968 --> 03:48:30.701
all of ours.

03:48:30.734 --> 03:48:33.534
♪

03:48:33.567 --> 03:48:38.667
We are all behind you,
and we all believe in you.

03:48:38.701 --> 03:48:40.734
And we all love you.

03:48:42.367 --> 03:48:46.167
And obviously, I love you.

03:48:46.200 --> 03:48:48.133
MARISHA: I love you.

03:48:49.767 --> 03:48:52.501
You know...

03:48:52.534 --> 03:48:54.734
everyone comes
from these backgrounds

03:48:54.767 --> 03:48:59.033
of having all
these well-ventured

03:48:59.067 --> 03:49:03.467
and traveled pasts.

03:49:03.501 --> 03:49:07.534
You were the first people
that I knew and met...

03:49:09.400 --> 03:49:12.701
so not only are you the longest,

03:49:12.734 --> 03:49:16.767
I don't really have
any other friends.

03:49:16.801 --> 03:49:18.968
You are my family.

03:49:19.000 --> 03:49:24.100
♪

03:49:24.133 --> 03:49:26.234
I'll try not to let you down.

03:49:27.634 --> 03:49:29.400
LIAM: I have no worries.

03:49:31.133 --> 03:49:33.234
Look at you.

03:49:34.501 --> 03:49:36.968
Don't you look like royalty.

03:49:37.000 --> 03:49:40.167
♪

03:49:40.200 --> 03:49:42.801
MARISHA: I'm not a princess, remember?

03:49:43.968 --> 03:49:45.734
LIAM: That's kinda what
I like about you.

03:49:45.767 --> 03:49:47.968
(laughing)

03:49:48.000 --> 03:49:50.100
Would you do me a favor?

03:49:50.133 --> 03:49:52.968
Down the line,
once all this is behind us...

03:49:55.267 --> 03:49:57.934
will you go back
to the theater with me?

03:49:59.071 --> 03:50:01.267
MARISHA: What is it with you
and the theater?

03:50:01.300 --> 03:50:03.200
(laughing)

03:50:03.234 --> 03:50:05.667
Why?

03:50:05.701 --> 03:50:07.501
LIAM: I don't understand it either.

03:50:07.534 --> 03:50:11.367
♪

03:50:11.400 --> 03:50:17.601
MARISHA: As long as you go back
to Zephra with me, maybe?

03:50:17.634 --> 03:50:19.467
LIAM: You don't have to ask.

03:50:23.167 --> 03:50:26.267
MARISHA: Does my hair look okay?

03:50:26.300 --> 03:50:28.000
LIAM: Are you kidding me?

03:50:28.033 --> 03:50:30.000
MARISHA: Does the short thing kinda work?

03:50:30.033 --> 03:50:32.567
Does it work with
my bone structure?

03:50:32.601 --> 03:50:34.801
The antlers aren't
overpowering it, right?

03:50:34.834 --> 03:50:38.067
The length kind of
balanced out this, you know?

03:50:38.100 --> 03:50:39.701
SAM: Bangs!

03:50:39.734 --> 03:50:41.567
MARISHA: Bangs.

03:50:41.601 --> 03:50:44.100
LAURA: Don't do it, don't do it,
you'll regret it.

03:50:44.133 --> 03:50:45.801
MARISHA: No bangs.

03:50:45.834 --> 03:50:47.534
LIAM: I shut her up with a kiss.

03:50:47.567 --> 03:50:48.834
MATT: Okay.

03:50:48.868 --> 03:50:51.801
SAM: (stammering)

03:50:51.834 --> 03:50:53.634
I'm in my room...

03:50:53.667 --> 03:50:55.801
♪

03:50:55.834 --> 03:50:59.300
I am taking Vax's letter

03:50:59.334 --> 03:51:02.868
and ripping it in half
and burning it.

03:51:02.901 --> 03:51:06.701
And I'm packing my pipe
for the morning.

03:51:06.734 --> 03:51:09.734
(mixed remarks)

03:51:09.767 --> 03:51:11.868
LAURA: This is for real, you guys.

03:51:11.901 --> 03:51:12.868
-LIAM: Wow.
-MATT: Alrighty.

03:51:12.901 --> 03:51:14.334
Prepared and ready to go.

03:51:14.367 --> 03:51:17.834
You have your next dose

03:51:17.868 --> 03:51:22.234
of brown suude prepared.

03:51:22.267 --> 03:51:24.067
MARISHA: I pass out
from sheer exhaustion.

03:51:24.100 --> 03:51:25.501
MATT: Okay.

03:51:25.534 --> 03:51:27.200
PATRICK: I am noisily sick.

03:51:27.234 --> 03:51:30.367
(laughing)

03:51:35.200 --> 03:51:37.334
And honestly...

03:51:38.901 --> 03:51:40.734
it took every ounce
of willpower I had

03:51:40.767 --> 03:51:42.968
to not do it in
the middle of your scene.

03:51:43.000 --> 03:51:45.701
(laughing)

03:51:45.734 --> 03:51:48.734
I feel like I've really grown
as a human being.

03:51:48.734 --> 03:51:51.067
TALIESIN: I think we've all
learned something tonight.

03:51:51.100 --> 03:51:53.567
MATT: The whole time, just like
slowly cut past the wall,

03:51:53.601 --> 03:51:57.167
and there's Ker just going--
holding it.

03:51:57.200 --> 03:52:00.234
(groaning)

03:52:00.267 --> 03:52:02.801
(laughing)

03:52:04.897 --> 03:52:06.901
-LIAM: We've all been there.
-LAURA: Before we go to bed,

03:52:06.934 --> 03:52:12.167
Allura, any chance
you'd be able to join us?

03:52:12.200 --> 03:52:14.367
I know you didn't get
to come the last time.

03:52:14.400 --> 03:52:17.100
MATT: "Oh, I'm there, don't worry."

03:52:17.133 --> 03:52:18.634
LAURA: Thank you.

03:52:20.334 --> 03:52:22.734
MATT: "So, you all get your rest.

03:52:26.367 --> 03:52:27.968
I'm honored, really.

03:52:32.300 --> 03:52:36.133
I was proud of you all for going
into that fray as you did.

03:52:36.167 --> 03:52:40.567
And you had many great
compatriots at your side.

03:52:40.601 --> 03:52:44.767
I was a little jealous."

03:52:44.801 --> 03:52:46.334
LAURA: Kima did wonderfully.

03:52:46.367 --> 03:52:48.000
MATT: "I'm sure she did."

03:52:48.033 --> 03:52:50.334
LAURA: I'm sure she'll want
to join us again.

03:52:50.367 --> 03:52:51.934
MATT: "I'm sure she'll
continue to complain

03:52:51.968 --> 03:52:53.701
about things that fly.

03:52:54.667 --> 03:52:57.167
It's never been her strong suit.

03:52:58.567 --> 03:53:01.367
But I'll be there with you,
do not worry.

03:53:03.534 --> 03:53:05.100
Rest well.

03:53:05.133 --> 03:53:09.567
I've had a full night's sleep,
I'm just gonna keep vigil

03:53:09.601 --> 03:53:15.601
and no longer drink things
you procure from your bags

03:53:15.634 --> 03:53:17.434
without inquiring."

03:53:20.767 --> 03:53:24.701
MARISHA: And we all set our alarms
for exactly eight hours.

03:53:24.734 --> 03:53:27.901
LAURA: No sleeping in, and just go.

03:53:27.934 --> 03:53:30.267
LIAM: Siri, wake me up
before Raishan wakes.

03:53:30.300 --> 03:53:32.367
(laughing)

03:53:32.400 --> 03:53:34.300
SAM: (barking)

03:53:34.334 --> 03:53:37.467
MATT: "I'm sorry, I didn't
understand that, Vax'ildan!"

03:53:37.501 --> 03:53:40.834
-TRAVIS: That stupid dog alarm.
-SAM: I love the dog alarm!

03:53:42.801 --> 03:53:45.334
MATT: All right, so as you all
find evening's rest,

03:53:45.367 --> 03:53:47.467
we'll go ahead and end
tonight's session there.

03:53:47.501 --> 03:53:48.968
(cheering)

03:53:49.000 --> 03:53:54.100
Preparing for whatever chaos
the next endeavor unfurls.

03:53:54.133 --> 03:53:56.167
LAURA: Oh, geez.

03:53:56.200 --> 03:53:57.801
-MARISHA: That was a good game.
-LIAM: Yeah.

03:53:57.834 --> 03:53:59.701
MATT: Well done, guys, it's fun.

03:53:59.734 --> 03:54:01.667
MARISHA: Yay, Kerr-bear!

03:54:01.701 --> 03:54:04.133
TRAVIS: Yeah, Patrick!

03:54:04.167 --> 03:54:05.601
PATRICK: It's such a treat--

03:54:05.634 --> 03:54:07.501
such a treat to be able
to come back.

03:54:07.534 --> 03:54:10.167
LIAM: Is there any chance
you'll be here next week?

03:54:10.200 --> 03:54:12.834
PATRICK: Honestly, I was already

03:54:12.868 --> 03:54:14.901
trying to figure
that out in my head.

03:54:14.934 --> 03:54:18.067
Like, it's--I mean,
I've flown places

03:54:18.100 --> 03:54:19.767
for dumber reasons.

03:54:19.801 --> 03:54:21.534
(laughing)

03:54:21.567 --> 03:54:26.734
You know, so I'll maybe
email with you a little bit

03:54:26.767 --> 03:54:27.901
to see how you feel about that.

03:54:27.934 --> 03:54:29.400
MATT: Let me know, I mean,
we'd love to have you.

03:54:29.434 --> 03:54:30.601
LIAM: Get you in some combat!

03:54:30.634 --> 03:54:33.000
-LAURA: Yeah!
-PATRICK: I will admit I've never--

03:54:33.033 --> 03:54:35.200
LAURA: You had a pretty
awesome hammer there!

03:54:35.234 --> 03:54:37.767
PATRICK: I, uh--I have yet
to actually take him

03:54:37.801 --> 03:54:40.067
for a test drive
in that way, so...

03:54:40.100 --> 03:54:44.334
LIAM: ♪ I'm just looking
for one divine hammer ♪♪

03:54:44.367 --> 03:54:47.000
(laughing)

03:54:47.033 --> 03:54:48.567
Breeders--that's
The Breeder's, man,

03:54:48.601 --> 03:54:49.634
-that's the '90s.
-MATT: We'll try and coordinate

03:54:49.667 --> 03:54:50.701
for that--hopefully
it works out,

03:54:50.734 --> 03:54:52.067
'cause that would be great.

03:54:52.100 --> 03:54:54.667
Otherwise, thank you guys
for kicking ass.

03:54:54.701 --> 03:54:58.501
Uhh...it's a great--
it's a great episode.

03:54:58.534 --> 03:54:59.834
Thank you guys for watching,

03:54:59.868 --> 03:55:02.567
thank you again for all
your amazing support.

03:55:02.601 --> 03:55:04.968
We're--we're taking
all the positivity

03:55:05.000 --> 03:55:07.968
we can force-feed into 2017.

03:55:08.000 --> 03:55:10.434
Um, but we love you guys.

03:55:10.467 --> 03:55:14.834
We'll see you in a week,
and is it Thursday yet?

03:55:14.868 --> 03:55:16.033
Take care, guys.

03:55:21.467 --> 03:55:41.300
♪

03:55:48.467 --> 04:00:49.901
